title: grits casserole
directions: Cook grits according to package directions.
Melt cheese with butter.
Mix eggs in a measuring cup and fill to top with milk. Mix together and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: oriental coleslaw
directions: Toss together the first 5 ingredients.
Mix well the remaining ingredients.
Pour dressing over cabbage and toss.
Add uncooked, broken Ramen noodles to individual portions at serving time.

title: chicken-artichoke salad
directions: Toss together chicken, onion, artichokes and tarragon in a large bowl.
Combine mayonnaise, sour cream, salt and pepper and pour over chicken mixture.
Gently blend.
Place lettuce leaf on each plate.
Using a teacup as a mold, put each serving of salad into the cup and turn out on the lettuce.
Sprinkle with almonds. Serves 6.

title: country-style steak
directions: Mix meat, 3-4 tablespoons of flour, and salt and shape into patties with a floured rolling pin on a floured board to about 1/4 inch thickness.
Brown on both sides in 3-4 tablespoons of fat. Remove meat and pour off all but 2-3 tablespoons of fat from frying.
Add 1/4 cup flour and allow to brown as it is stirred occasionally.
Add water and cook until thick.
Layer meat and gravy in a casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30-45 minutes.

title: mama's easy lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and garlic together; drain off grease. Combine this with tomato juice and paste; let simmer while the lasagna noodles cook (20 to 30 minutes).

title: french onion dip
directions: Mix well and refrigerate overnight.
Enjoy with chips or vegetables.

title: jana's disgustingly rich brownies
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
In mixing bowl, stir the cocoa and sugar together, then stir in melted butter.
Add eggs and vanilla and stir again.
Add flour and salt and mix until smooth. Add walnuts.
Bake in greased 8 or 9-inch pan at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat the first 5 ingredients together.
Put in ice cream freezer container.
Finish filling to line with homogenized milk.

title: beans and corn casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients except crackers.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Put crushed Ritz crackers on top. Drizzle butter over topping. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple torte
directions: Slice apples.
Put apples in pan.
Combine sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken marinade
directions: Bring water, vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper, garlic salt and Worcestershire sauce to a boil, then add butter.
Pour over chicken and marinate for about 12 hours or longer.
Discard marinade and grill chicken until tender.

title: spicy ham sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Take French rolls.
Split; spread a little butter on top, then spoon in mixture.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Place in an oven just long enough to melt the cheese.

title: potato candy
directions: Peel potatoes; mash in large mixing bowl.
Add sugar and vanilla gradually until mixture is consistency of dough.
Roll out on wax paper.
Spread generously with peanut butter.
Roll into a log chill several hours or overnight.
Slice and serve.

title: crockpot lasagna
directions: Brown meat and onion in skillet.
Drain off the fat.
Next add the jar of spaghetti sauce and simmer for 7-10 minutes (if the sauce is too thick you may want to add up to 1/2 c. of water).

title: white wonder icing-finger
directions: Mix in top of double boiler.
Stir with finger until too warm for finger.
Remove from heat and beat until it stands in peaks. Add vanilla.
This is good to use for a coconut cake.

title: great and easy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Empty cake mix in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and oil until all lumps are gone.
Add in chocolate chips and walnuts.
Bake in oven at 350° for 7 to 9 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.
Great hot with Cool Whip.
Enjoy.

title: dirt cake
directions: Cover bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan with crushed cookies, saving some for garnish.
Mix together milk and instant pudding mix in a bowl.
In a separate bowl, mix remaining ingredients.
Combine both mixtures and stir well.
Pour over crushed cookies in pan and sprinkle with reserved crumbs.
Refrigerate.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Let set for awhile before serving.

title: cinnamon cream cheese bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Place 1 can crescent rolls in bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Mix 1 cup sugar with softened cream cheese. Spread over crescent rolls. Place second can of crescent rolls over cheese mixture. Mix 1/2 cup sugar and softened butter. Spread over crescent rolls and sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: kraut brot
directions: Brown bacon with onion; brown hamburger and combine with drained sauerkraut.
Divide thawed bread in half; roll bread sections out into separate parts.
Put half of mixture in the middle of each section; pinch dough over and pinch shut.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Combine banana and lemon juice.
Add buttermilk and shortening.
Stir in the eggs and vanilla.
Combine the flour, baking powder, baking soda, sugar and salt.
Add to liquid mixture, mixing well.
Stir in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 2 (8-inch) layers.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and nuts.
Set aside.
Combine and beat well eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour mixture alternately with zucchini. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes until well done.
This makes 2 loaf pans of bread.

title: cake dessert for a crowd
directions: Pour can of undrained fruit cup into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkel 1 box Duncan Hines yellow cake mix (dry) over fruit cup.
Dribble 1 stick melted margarine over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with Cool Whip.
Serves 12 to 15.
Good dessert for a crowd.
Several people can each make dessert and they will all be the same.

title: ramaki
directions: Place chicken livers in boiling water for 1 minute; cut in chunks and marinate in 1 tablespoon soy sauce for 15 minutes. Chop chestnuts into thirds.
Wrap one slice of bacon around chestnut and chunk of liver; secure with toothpick.
Bake on rack in 325° oven for about 10 minutes.
These can be frozen after preparation and used at a later date.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add peanut butter and milk, beating until smooth and creamy.

title: spanish rice
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir about every 1/2 hour.

title: nobby apple cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and mix well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add creamed mixture.
Stir in diced apples, nuts and vanilla.
Pour in greased 8 x 8-inch pan and bake 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sweet sour pork
directions: Mix thoroughly. Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours, in glass bread pan coated with cooking spray.

title: oysterette snacks
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix.
Let stand overnight.
Before serving, mix again.
(If you don't like garlic you can omit.)

title: cinder cake
directions: Crush the package of Oreo cookies into crumbs.
Melt stick of butter and mix in crumbs.
Put aside 1 cup of this mixture.
Take rest and pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Take slightly melted ice cream and spread over crumbs.
Drizzle Hershey's syrup over ice cream. Take Cool Whip and spread over ice cream.
Drizzle more Hershey's syrup on Cool Whip.
Put the nuts on next, then remaining Oreo crumbs.
Put in freezer.

title: instant pizza
directions: Mix tomato sauce,
salami,
cheese and spices together. Spread on open-faced
muffins.
Sprinkle
with grated Parmesan cheese and bake 12 to
minutes at 400°.
After baking, put under broiler to brown the tops.
Serves 6.

title: maggie's special salad
directions: In small saucepan, mix sugar with cornstarch.
Blend in 1 cup water and the vinegar.
Cook, stirring until boiling and thickened.
Transfer to small bowl; cover.
Refrigerate until chilled.
In large bowl, toss remaining ingredients with prepared dressing.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pecan pie cupcake cookies
directions: In bowl, mix together flour, cream cheese and 1/4 pound butter. Roll into 24 small balls (quarter size).
Press into 2-inch cupcake tins.
Sprinkle nuts lightly on bottom of dough.
Mix together filling of light brown sugar, egg, vanilla and 1 tablespoon butter. Add 1 teaspoon of filling to cupcake tins.
Sprinkle nuts on top of cakes.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Turn oven down to 250° and bake 10 minutes more.
Cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar. Remove cakes from pan immediately and cool on wire rack.
Yield: 24 cookies.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a buttered 8 x 8-inch pan or 10-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until golden brown around the edges.

title: buttermilk chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Dip chicken into 1/2 cup buttermilk. Then roll chicken in mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan and place chicken in pan, breast down.
Bake 30 minutes, uncovered.
Turn chicken and bake 15 minutes more.
Turn chicken once more and pour mixture of mushroom soup and 1 cup buttermilk over chicken.
Bake 15 minutes more. Remove chicken to platter and garnish with parsley.
Serve with gravy left in pan.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: grandma's apple cake
directions: Mix together the margarine, sugar, salt, egg, cinnamon and apples.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients to the mixture.
Pour into an 8-inch square greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: frozen ice cream dessert
directions: Combine Oreo cookies and oleo; press in 9 x 13-inch pan. Freeze.
Soften ice cream.
Spread on cookie mixture and freeze. Combine evaporated milk, chocolate and sugar; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cook until mixture thickens.
Cool.
Spread on top of ice cream and freeze.
Top with Cool Whip.
Keep frozen.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over Bran Buds and let cool.
Cream shortening and sugar, then add eggs, one at a time.
Sift together the flour, soda and salt.
Add these dry ingredients alternately with the buttermilk.
Add cooled Bran Buds and fold in bran flakes and raisins.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Makes 6 dozen.
The batter keeps 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: sweet and sauerkraut(hot salad; microwave)
directions: Mix all ingredients in a pretty glass dish or large bowl. Microwave 6 to 7 minutes, stirring several times.
Serve hot or with cold, sliced roast, Polish sausage or barbecue.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Put popped popcorn aside in a large bowl.
In a mixing pan; melt margarine and marshmallows.
Remove from heat and add baking soda and salt.
Pour over popcorn.
Add peanuts and M&M's; mix carefully.
Grease (2) 9 X 13 pans, or 2 angel food cake pans. Pack into the pans and let cool completely.
Remove from pans and cut as you would cake.
Note:
Be careful when adding M&M's.
If mixture is to hot they will melt and break.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown
onion and beef together; drain.	Add sour cream, bouillon
cubes,
mushrooms,
mushroom
soup
and
ketchup and simmer for 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Cook egg noodles.
Drain and serve stroganoff over noodles.
Serves 6.

title: apricot bars
directions: Rinse apricots and cover with water in a saucepan.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Mix flour, sugar and margarine until crumbly.
Press into ungreased 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: palace trout
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon butter in nonstick skillet.
Add trout fillets side by side.
Add just enough milk and water to come halfway up trout.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add bay leaves. Cover and heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and cook for 15 minutes. Remove from heat.
Reserve liquid.
Discard bay leaves.
Place trout on bed of hot angel hair pasta.
In medium skillet, melt 1/2 cup butter and saut mushrooms and garlic for 5 minutes.
Add green onions and cook for additional 5 minutes.
Add shrimp and lobster; heat thoroughly, stirring constantly.
Sprinkle with flour and cook for 2 minutes.
Gradually add remaining milk, cream and reduced poaching liquid and simmer 10 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour sauce around edges of fish and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Serve hot.

title: robert and david's favorite chicken pot pie
directions: Layer chicken in bottom of casserole dish.
Pour mixed veggies over chicken.
Spread soup over veggies.
Mix Bisquick and milk until lumps are gone.
Pour over the soup and bake in a 400° oven until top is done.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Cook bacon until just about crisp; drain.
Combine bacon with beans, tomato sauce, onion, ketchup, brown sugar, mustard, salt, pepper and hot pepper sauce.
Bake beans, uncovered, in 2-quart casserole in slow oven (300°) for 3 to 5 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fluffy white frosting
directions: Combine the two ingredients for a quick frosting.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta; drain.
Steam vegetables until crunchy.
Saute slightly broccoli, cauliflower, carrots, green beans and mushrooms.
Mix zucchini, black olives and red onion with creamy Italian dressing.
Salt to taste.
Let set overnight.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Put skim milk and diet margarine in pan until melted.
Add cocoa supplement and cook over low heat, approximately 1 minute, until thick.
Then remove from heat and add chocolate pudding food product.
Stir in cinnamon, vanilla extract and oatmeal food products.

title: basic dough(for making decorations for special occasions)
directions: Stir together ingredients.
Knead together until it forms a medium-stiff, smooth dough.

title: buckeye candy
directions: Mix peanut butter, sugar, pecans and butter or margarine together.
Boil into small balls.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in double boiler.
Dip balls into the mixture, leaving tops exposed to look like buckeyes.
Place on wax paper to cool.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Mix all ingredients except cabbage.
Cook cabbage whole, cutting off leaves as they turn color.
Place handful of meat mixture in cabbage leaf and roll; place in steamer and cook on stove about 1 1/2 hours or until it is done.

title: tuna jalapeno croquettes
directions: Cover fish fillets with a mixture of mustard and fat-free Miracle Whip.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over fish.
Bake at 350° until fish flakes.
Season to taste.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg yolks and sour cream (in which baking soda has been dissolved).
Add enough flour to make the dough just stiff enough to roll out.
Roll dough out thin on lightly floured board.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Decorate if you wish.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat in a skillet.
Heat 3 cans of soup in another pan.
In another pan, boil egg noodles until tender.

title: favorite meat loaf
directions: Tear bread in small pieces and put in large bowl.
Add milk and egg.
Add meat and seasonings; mix thoroughly.
Form lightly into loaf and place in shallow baking pan or loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: salmon ball
directions: Combine all but nuts and parsley.
Shape into ball and roll in nuts and parsley.
Chill again.

title: baked apples
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, nutmeg, cinnamon, allspice and apples. Place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle 2 teaspoons of melted butter on top.
Bake in a 350° oven.
Cover for 1/2 hour; remove cover and brown.

title: mert's freezer slaw
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar and salt. Bring to a boil.
Set aside to cool.
Chop onions, peppers and cabbage.
Pour mixture over cabbage and stir well.
Put in meal size containers and freeze. Set out 30 minutes before serving.

title: barbecue smokies
directions: Liquid smoke is the secret ingredient.

title: cheese spread
directions: Beat cream cheese at medium speed with an electric mixer until smooth; add butter and remaining ingredients, mixing until blended.
Spoon into airtight containers.
Store in refrigerator up to 1 week before using.
Yield:
3 1/2 cups.

title: calamai fritto(fried squid)
directions: Clean squid thoroughly and cut into small pieces.
Mix oregano, basil and flour.
Roll squid in mixture.
Heat olive oil and add garlic. Brown garlic and add the squid.
Saute for 10 minutes.
Serve hot.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cold broccoli salad
directions: Drain broccoli real good (don't cook).
Mix all ingredients together.
Add eggs last.
Serve cold.

title: blueberry cream pie
directions: Cover bottom of pie crusts with nuts and bake until done.
Mix sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Add vanilla and pour into pie crusts.
Cover with pie filling.

title: darla's chili
directions: Cook onions, peppers, garlic and hamburger together, drain. Add whole tomatoes (cut with spoon) and liquid.
Add stewed tomatoes, cumin, sugar and bouillon cubes.
Let simmer so it gets thick, almost 1 hour.
Add chili powder and beans (do not drain). Heat thoroughly.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together the night before and refrigerate. Cook in oblong pan.
(Can use ham instead of sausage.
Also can substitute 1/2 cup sour cream instead of 1/2 cup milk.)
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: carob fudge squares(diabetic)
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl and mix until mixture sticks together.
Press into a flat, buttered pan.
Cut into squares.
Wrap in plastic wrap or wax paper for storing.

title: golden pheasant
directions: Blend in mixer.
Serve 1 shot of mixture with cream soda with ice.

title: delicious banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake about 40 - 45 min. in 350°F oven.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: jake's banana bread
directions: Cream cooking oil and sugar.
Blend in bananas, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, salt, and baking soda alternating with buttermilk--stirring in each addition.
Lightly flour nuts and add to mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan. Bake 325 for 1 hours.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti for 7 minutes.
Drain and rinse.
In skillet, melt butter and saute onions.
Add liquid from mushrooms and stir in chicken soup, evaporated milk, mushrooms, marjoram, pimento, meat and cheese.
Put spaghetti in greased oblong casserole dish and pour sauce over top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix together the red food coloring and cocoa powder; set aside.

title: electric skillet dinner
directions: Brown noodles in oil.
Add hamburger and cook until gray. Drain. Add the remaining ingredients and cook 20 minutes at 350 degrees.
Cut up cheese and melt on top.

title: tamale pie
directions: Brown beef
and onion in pan.
Drain. Add tomato sauce, chili and corn. Stir until mixed. Pour into casserole dish and top with cornbread batter. Cover with Cheddar cheese. Bake in a 350° oven until cornbread is brown and done.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix jello with hot water until dissolved.
Add pineapple, blueberries and 1/4 cup nuts.
Mix well.
Chill until set.
Mix cream cheese with sour cream and sugar.
Spread on top of chilled jello mixture.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup nuts on top.

title: ruby's buttermilk pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl, except buttermilk.
Mix well. Add buttermilk and beat 15 minutes.
Do not underbeat.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: texas pecan pie
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in a small bowl; mix well. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add evaporated milk; mix well.
Stir in pecan halves and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into an unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake additional 35 to 40 minutes, or until filling is puffed in center or is well browned.
Cool before serving.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix the butter, peanut butter, xxx sugar and vanilla.
In a pan, melt over hot water the chocolate chips and paraffin.
Roll the peanut butter mixture into walnut size balls.
Stick toothpick into each.
Dip into chocolate mixture.
Allow to harden.
Remove pick.

title: fast baked beans
directions: Mix beans, sugar, mustard and ketchup together.
Put in crock-pot.
Cook hamburger and onion together.
Mix with bean mixture and cook about 1 hour.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Beat eggs; add oil and strawberries.
Mix with sifted dry ingredients.
This makes 2 regular loaves.
Grease and flour loaf pans and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
You can make 1 loaf by dividing ingredients and mixing as instructed.

title: tuna and egg salad
directions: Shell hard-boiled eggs.
Dice, throwing away yolks.
Drain tuna.
Add all ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
Serve on bed of lettuce, crackers or bread.

title: pasta house salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Stir together the oil, vinegar and Parmesan cheese.
Pour over salad and let stand 1 hour before serving.
"Pasta House" is a popular restaurant in the St. Louis area.

title: superman hamburger
directions: Fry bacon alone; drain.
Fry hamburger patty.
Place lettuce, tomato, onion, catsup, mustard, bacon, ham, cheese and burger on very large bun.
Enjoy.

title: chicken soup
directions: Cook the chicken wings in water with the chopped onion and celery salt until done.
Remove chicken from pot.
Bone and skin wings and put meat back in pot.
Add rice, oregano and cream of chicken soup.
Mix well and heat until rice is done.

title: deviled clams
directions: Grind or chop very fine first 5 ingredients.
Simmer them in clam juice and butter until tender, about 5 minutes.
Mix well with thyme, pepper, mustard, bread crumbs.
Grease clam shells and fill with mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 25 - 30 minutes.

title: dump cake (easy!)
directions: Spoon cherry pie filling into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread pineapple over top.
Sprinkle cake mix over fruit.
Pour melted butter over all.
Sprinkle with coconut and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: carnation 5-minute fudge
directions: Combine butter, evaporated milk, sugar and salt in pan over medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Bring to a full boil.
Cook 4 or 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in marshmallows, chocolate, vanilla and nuts.
Stir non-stop for 1 minute (until marshmallows melt and blend).
Pour into 8-inch square buttered pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Place in saucepan sugar, margarine and syrup.
Mix well and boil for 1 minute.	Pour over 2 gallons plain popped corn. Toss and mix well.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Add
desired
amount
of peanuts if you want, during last 30 minutes of baking.

title: lastado dip
directions: Layer ingredients in the order given in pie plate or quiche dish.
Add remaining 1/2 can picante sauce or salsa.
Cover all with grated sharp Cheddar cheese.
Spread each layer gently and evenly.
Make at least 4 hours before serving.
Serve with plain round Doritos.

title: sausage potato soup
directions: Brown sausage over medium heat, stirring until it crumbles and is no longer pink. Drain and put in a large Dutch oven. Add potatoes and next 3 ingredients to sausage; bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes. Stir in soups and milk. Cook, stirring often, until thoroughly heated. Garnish, if desired.

title: skillet chicken tetrazzini
directions: Melt butter in electric skillet.
Add onion and celery; cook until clear.
Arrange chicken in layer over onion and celery.
Add uncooked spaghetti.
Mix salt, pepper, cream of chicken soup and chicken broth; pour over spaghetti, being careful to moisten all of spaghetti.
Add water, if needed, to cover spaghetti.
Place mushrooms on top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover and cook at 325° until steam escapes.
Turn immediately to simmer; stir occasionally.
Cook for 30 minutes.

title: vegetarian vegetable soup
directions: Place all diced vegetables, onion and garlic, in a 8-quart pot. Cover with water and tomato sauce.
Bring to a slow boil and while simmering, cook Ramen noodles by package directions, and add to the pot, along with beef bouillon cubes.
Season with Mrs. Dash and pepper.
Slow boil for 1 hour.

title: spinach dip
directions: Squeeze out excess water from thawed spinach.
Mix with other ingredients.
Hollow out bread to make a serving bowl.
Cut bread that has been hollowed out into squares.
Place spinach mixture into bread bowl.
Use bread squares as dippers along with raw broccoli and cauliflower.

title: pickles in a blanket(this recipe uses good old chipped beef.)
directions: With a knife, spread softened cream cheese over pickles, covering well, then wrap a piece of chipped beef around pickles and cut into slices.
Stick a toothpick in each slice for an easy appetizer dish.

title: butterscotch pudding cake
directions: Prepare pudding as directed on package.
Let cool.
Put cake mix in bowl (and eggs and oil if needed).
Add pudding.
Mix until well blended.
Bake in greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle cake with morsels and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: homemade dog bones number 2
directions: *If using bouillon, omit.
If low salt diet, omit.

title: simple spaghetti
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add onion and beef and saute until beef browns.
Add tomato sauce, water, salt, parsley, basil and pepper; blend well and bring to boiling.
Break spaghetti in half and sprinkle into boiling sauce a little at a time, stirring to keep it separated.
Cover tightly.
Simmer 20 to 25 minutes or until just tender, stirring occasionally.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar and vegetable oil; beat at high speed. Add eggs, one at a time, beating for 1 minute after each addition.

Sift together dry ingredients. Add vanilla flavoring and dry ingredients; mix. Dredge nuts and dates in a small amount of flour. Add to batter. Add apples. Do not add any liquids. This is a very stiff batter. Pour in Bundt pan that has been lined with wax paper. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: vinaigrette dressing
directions: Blend the first 7 ingredients in a blender until smooth.
Add 2 1/2 cups more sugar, vinegar and oil; blend again.

title: chocolate caramel cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box.
Punch holes in cake and pour syrup and milk into holes.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: pineapple cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs, butter and powdered sugar until well blended. Press into bottom of spring-form pan.
Chill for 30 minutes. Combine cream cheese, eggs, sugar, crushed pineapple and cinnamon. Beat until smooth.
Pour into prepared crust.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Cool for 1 hour.
Mix sour cream, sugar and vanilla. Spread over cheesecake.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes.
Chill several hours.

title: nana's banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F. Spray bottom only of 9 x 5 x 3 inch loaf pan with nonstick cooking spray.

title: potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour in unbaked pie shell. Makes 2 thin pie shells or 1 deep dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: You will also need a candy thermometer.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix together and store in refrigerator, covered.

title: scones
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar; with a pastry blender, thoroughly cut in shortening.
Add eggs, milk and mandarin peel, mix to make a soft dough.
Turn out on floured surface and divide in half.
Pat half into bottom of greased 8-inch cake pan.
Press dough about 1/2-inch up sides of pan.
Spread dough with marmalade.
Cover with remaining half of dough.
With a floured knife, cut through dough, dividing into 6 wedges.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes in a 425° oven.
Serves 6.

title: easy garden bake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease a square baking dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inch or pie plate, 9 x 1 1/4-inch.
Sprinkle zucchini, tomato, onion and cheese evenly in pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients together with mixer until smooth.
Pour evenly in dish.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Makes 6 servings.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Use 1 cup flour to dredge the dates, orange slices, coconut and pecans. Set aside. Cream oleo and sugar until fluffy. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add soda to buttermilk and add alternately with dry ingredients until well blended. When well mixed, add the dredged fruits and nuts and fold in gently. Pour into a tube pan that has been greased and floured. Bake at 250° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours. A very rich cake.

title: garbage stew
directions: If you don't have as much leftover meat as you would like, brown ground meat and onions, drain and return to pan.
Add all ingredients with cooked macaroni.
Add spices and salt and pepper to taste.

title: pizza in a tunnel
directions: Grease and lightly dust a 10-inch fluted tube pan or an 11-cup ring mold with cornmeal.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir in all ingredients in a Dutch oven baking dish.
Cook for 40 minutes or until top browns.

title: halayang ube
directions: Stir ube powder into milk in a saucepan.
Mix until smooth. Add condensed milk and cook, stirring, over low-moderate heat, until mixture thickens (about 15 minutes).
Gradually stir 1/4 cup of hot ube mixture into beaten egg yolks, then gradually return to simmering pot with the rest of mixture.
Add butter and continuing cooking, stirring constantly, for about 10 minutes more.
Place on well oiled or buttered 3-cup mold.
Chill until ready to serve. Unmold on a platter just before serving.

title: easy chocolate cherry cake
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients except powdered sugar. Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan (greased and floured).
Bake at 350° until done (40 minutes).
Let cool and sprinkle top with powdered sugar.

title: rolled sugar cookies
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat butter and shortening for 30 seconds; add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add egg, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add dry ingredients to beaten mixture, beating until well combined.
Cover and chill at least 3 hours (overnight is best).

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes in half and place in a shallow baking pan.
Melt margarine and add onion, parsley, salt, pepper, cheese and bread crumbs.
Spread mixture on top of tomato halves and bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: cheese tarts
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and eggs until smooth.
Place 1 vanilla wafer in bottom of cupcake cup.
Place heaping tablespoonfuls of cheese mixture into each cup.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.
Top with pie filling (cherry or blueberry).
Graham cracker pie crust may be substituted for vanilla wafer cupcakes.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook ground meat and mushrooms; drain on paper towel.
Return to skillet and add tomato sauce.
In a bowl, combine cottage cheese, egg, Parmesan cheese, parsley, oregano, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Lightly oil a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Arrange ingredients in layers as follows: noodles, meat sauce, cheese mixture and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.
One-thousand calorie recipe.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well.
Add next 3 ingredients and cook until thick.
Cool completely.
Stir in whipped cream.

title: meatballs in mushroom soup
directions: Combine all the ingredients, except the mushroom soup.
Shape the mixture into balls the size of large walnut.
Brown well in skillet.
Pour off any excess grease and add the soup.
Simmer for 45 minutes (the soup may be diluted with milk if a thinner gravy is desired).
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: cookie pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Grease a 12-inch pizza pan. In medium bowl, beat butter, brown sugar, egg and vanilla until light and fluffy. Add flour, salt, baking powder, baking soda and oats. Beat until blended. Stir in plain coconut and chocolate chips (reserve some chips for topping).
Spread dough evenly into greased pizza pan. Top with yellow tinted coconut.
Garnish with reserved chocolate chips, M&M's and walnuts. Bake 13 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream oleo with brown and white sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla. Mix together with flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Add chocolate morsels and pecans.

title: layered taco salad
directions: Mix refried beans and seasoning mix for first layer.
Spread evenly in serving dish.
Layer all other ingredients in order given.

title: seafood primavera
directions: Cook vegetables and pasta according to package directions. Set aside.
Rinse shrimp and scallops, drain and then use VERY LOW heat to get remaining water out.
Drain again then brown shrimp and scallops in a separate pan using 1/3 cup olive oil.
Remove seafood and place off to the side.
In a separate container blend flour, sugar, spices and milk until uniform. In the pan the seafood was browned in add the remaining olive oil and heat on low.
Add milk and blend and stir thoroughly.
Increase heat and bring to a boil, stirring constantly until mixture thickens.
Add extra milk to consistency you want.
Add pasta, vegetables and seafood on plate.
Pour sauce over to suit taste.

title: pomodori parmesan
directions: Place tomatoes in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix 14 saltines, Italian seasonings and pepper.
Melt oleo with onion, salt and 16 crackers.
Spread buttered cracker mixture over tomatoes. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: reuben dip
directions: Combine well. Transfer to casserole dish and bake, covered, for 30 minutes or until bubbles form at edges. Remove cover and bake 5 minutes until edges are golden. Serve warm with crackers or cocktail rye bread.

title: english muffin bread
directions: Combine 3 cups flour and yeast, sugar, salt and baking soda. Heat liquids until lukewarm.
Add to dry mixture and beat well. Stir in more flour until batter is stiff.
Put into 2 greased bread pans.
Cover and let rise until it reaches the top of the pans, about 45 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: crispy fried onion rings
directions: Peel off outer layer of onion until all onion is cut into many rings.
Combine mix and milk to form a smooth batter.
Dip onion rings into batter and fry until golden brown.

title: snowball cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 4 tablespoons cold water.
Add 1 cup boiling water.
Let cool.
Add juice of lemon, pineapple, sugar and salt.
Mix thoroughly and put in refrigerator to cool.
While this is partially setting, break cake into bite size pieces.
Also prepare 2 packages of Dream Whip as directed.
When gelatin mixture is partially set, mix with whipped topping.
Line a 4-quart bowl with wax paper.
Mix gelatin mixture and cake pieces thoroughly and pour into lined bowl.
Refrigerate overnight.
Turn cake onto cake plate.
Frost with the third box of whipped topping, prepared as directed.
Cover generously with coconut.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Melt butter and mix with flour and pecans. Pat firm in the bottom of 13 x 9 pan (ungreased) and bake at 350° for 18 minutes; let cool.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Pound chicken breasts with mallet.
Shake breasts in seasoned, floured bag.
Saute in oil in skillet until lightly browned.
Add garlic and rosemary; continue sauteing until golden brown.
Stir wine and wine vinegar into tomato sauce and add to chicken. Spread tomato paste over breasts and simmer, covered, for 20 minutes.
Add green pepper and simmer for another 20 minutes.
Add black olives and almonds; cook, uncovered, for 5 minutes. Sprinkle with parsley before serving.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: orange jello dessert
directions: Put vanilla pudding, tapioca pudding and orange Jell-O in a bowl.
Add 1/4 to 1/2 of the boiling water to dry ingredients and mix until smooth; then add rest of the water.
Cool.
Refrigerate until thickened.
Drain pineapple and oranges.
Add this to the ingredients along with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: okeechobee crappie(or other fish)
directions: Cut crappie in small pieces.
Soak in salt water for 2 hours or longer.
Drain.
Roll in corn meal mix and drop into hot (not burning) oil.
Fish will float when a golden brown.
Drain on a paper towel and eat up.

title: date bars
directions: To prepare filling, mix the first 3 ingredients in saucepan and add the extracts.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thick, about 10 minutes. Set aside to cool.

title: basic yeast dough
directions: Stir yeast
into
milk.
Blend	in
1/2 cup flour.
Set aside in warm place about an hour until bubbly.
Cream together butter, sugar
and salt.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well
after each addition.
Add yeast mixture alternating with the flour
to egg
mixture.
Knead
dough
until	smooth	and elastic.
Cover and
let
rise
in warm place until double in bulk, then
roll out
for dinner rolls, cinnamon, etc.
Makes good an pan!!

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Combine ingredients in large bowl, folding together until blended.
Spoon into decorative serving bowl.
Chill.
Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: corn-butterbean salad
directions: You may also add 1 tablespoon Durkee to add a little tartness to flavor.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: Cook and drain pepperoni; put back into pan.
Beat the egg and milk and mix through spaghetti.
Pour into buttered baking dish. Top with jar of spaghetti sauce.
Cover with Mozzarella cheese. Place rows of pepperoni slices on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes to set.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: tapioca dessert
directions: Boil water and salt together.
Add tapioca and cook for 15 minutes.
Add sugar and jello.
Cool and let set overnight, then add pineapple and Cool Whip.
Just before serving, add sliced bananas.
Marshmallows may be added too.

title: caramel corn
directions: In a large saucepan, combine brown sugar, syrup, margarine, salt and cream of tartar.
Bring to a boil and cook 5 minutes. Remove from heat and add soda.
Mix well and pour over popcorn. Mix the sauce real well with the popcorn.
Place on 2 greased cookie sheets; put in a preheated oven.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour.

title: herbed roast leg of lamb
directions: Wipe lamb with damp paper towel.
Rub surfaces of meat with lemon juice.
Make several slits in meat and insert halved cloves of garlic.
Spread mustard over all surfaces and sprinkle herbs over top with rosemary needles predominating, also salt.
Cut onions into halves or quarters and place over meat.
May use toothpicks to anchor.
Preheat oven to 450° and roast 15 minutes before turning heat to 350°.
Roast 25 minutes per pound.
Remove meat to oven platter to keep warm while preparing gravy.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Cook milk, flour, sugar and salt for 10 minutes.
Gradually add egg yolks; mix with water and cook about 20 minutes.
Cool and add vanilla.
Add 1 pint of whipped cream and put in refrigerator. Stir a few times during freezing.

title: nut roll
directions: Combine Marshmallow Creme and vanilla and gradually knead in sugar.
Shape into rolls about 1-inch in diameter.
Wrap individually in plastic wrap and freeze for 6 hours.
Melt caramels over hot water.
Remove from heat, but keep warm.
Dip rolls into caramels, then roll in nuts until well coated.
Store cooled candy in a covered container.
Yield:
20 pieces.

title: coconut pie
directions: Melt butter and add all the ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake 60 minutes at 300°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Blend eggs with pumpkin. Add water and flour to eggs and pumpkin.
Add this mixture to shortening and sugar.
Add spices and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in 2 large loaf pans or 1 hour and 10 minutes in a tube pan.

title: green chili casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion in large skillet.
Add soup, milk, chilies and Cheez Whiz.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, layer 1/2 of tortillas, then 1/2 of meat mixture, then repeat.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: brown rice
directions: Brown rice in butter until grains are brown.
Pour into covered dish and add soups.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cowboy stew
directions: Brown sausage.
Saute onion and bell pepper.
Mix together all ingredients and cook in crock-pot.

title: crazy cake
directions: Do not grease pan.
Sift flour, sugar, cocoa, sugar and salt in to a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make 3 holes.
Place some of the vegetable oil, vanilla and vinegar in each hole.
Pour 2 cups cold water over this and stir with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cheesecake
directions: First make the graham cracker crust by mixing the crumbs with the melted stick of butter.
Press the crumbs into a 10-inch spring-form pan.

title: salmon linguine
directions: Boil pasta with 1 tablespoon oil to desired doneness.
Melt butter in large saucepan and simmer with garlic, onions, parsley and dill.
Toss pasta in butter mixture and mix thoroughly.
Top pasta mixture with fish; garnish with chopped green onion.
Serves 1.

title: spicy meat loaf
directions: Combine meat, salt, pepper, onion, flour and eggs, then add 4 tablespoons brown sugar and 2 tablespoons catsup. Mix well and shape into a loaf.

title: fantastic fudge(child's recipe)
directions: Put chocolate chips in 1 1/2-quart microwavable bowl. Microwave on Medium (50%) for 5 to 7 minutes.
Stir milk, vanilla and salt into melted chips.
Pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Crush crackers and mix with melted margarine; set aside. Combine all other ingredients and place in a baking dish.
Top with crackers and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, syrup, salt and vanilla; mix well. Stir in melted butter and broken pecans.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch deep pie shell.
Bake for 45 to 55 minutes at 350°.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Mix buttermilk and soda in measuring cup; set aside.
Beat the 5 egg whites until stiff.
Cream shortenings and sugar.
Beat in egg yolks.
Add buttermilk alternately with flour.
Fold in egg whites, vanilla, nuts and coconut.
Spoon into well-greased and floured 9-inch round pans.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: pecan pie(without syrup)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325° until done in middle (approximately 50 minutes). Makes one 8-inch pie.

title: waffles
directions: Mix thoroughly flour, milk, oil and egg yolks. Add beaten egg whites; stir in with a spoon (do not beat). Mixture will look lumpy. Pour 1/2 cup of batter onto hot waffle iron; remove when a nice golden brown. Makes 8 waffles.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Prepare rice as directions on package direct.
Saute pepper, onions and mushrooms in 1/2 cup margarine. Drain rice.
Layer rice, sauteed mixture and grated cheese in 2-quart casserole in that order, ending with cheese.
Pour half and half on entire mixture.
Place in preheated oven and bake 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: grandma norma's chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar, oleo and milk.
Boil to soft ball stage (approximately 7 to 8 minutes), stirring constantly at full boil. Remove from heat and add chocolate chips, Marshmallow Creme, vanilla and salt.
Beat until creamy (about 3 to 4 minutes).
Add pecans and quickly pour into "Pam" sprayed (or greased) pan.
Cool and cut into bite-sized pieces.
Use a heavy pan.
I use my heavy Presto cooker (no lid)!

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done; cool and pull off bone.
While taking chicken from bone, boil noodles in the chicken juice.
When noodles are done and chicken is ready, combine chicken, noodles, cream of chicken soup, chopped onion and chopped eggs.
Put in large casserole dish and crumble potato chips on top.
Cover and cook at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Makes a delicious meal.

title: orange cookies
directions: Mix shortening and sugars until creamy.
Mix in egg.
Combine flour, soda and salt and mix into sugar mixture.
Add orange juice and rind, vanilla and almond flavoring.
Stir in nuts.
Make cookie rolls in wax paper.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cream butter, sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Add dry ingredients and beat. Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until done.

title: sesame slaw
directions: To make cabbage mixture, combine cabbage and green onions.

title: clam chowder
directions: Cut salt pork into 1/2-inch cubes and fry until golden brown. Chop onions into 1/4 sections and stir into salt pork; do not remove pan drippings. Cook until onions are transparent. Stir flour into onion and salt pork mixture to make a roux. Add water and stir until smooth. Cook until mixture thickens. Decrease heat slowly and add clam broth and clams. Chop potatoes into 1-inch cubes and add to chowder. Cook for approximately 1/2 hour, until potatoes are fork-tender. Add 1 stick of butter, salt, pepper and parsley. Cook another 15 minutes. Add cream. Keep on low heat until served.

title: popovers from jordon pond house, bar harbor, maine
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Beat eggs at high speed until lemon colored.
On slow speed, add 1/2 cup milk; beat until well mixed. Sift flour, salt and soda.
Add slowly on slow speed to eggs. Scrape sides of bowl and beaters.
Turn to high speed; add rest of milk.
Beat for 5 to 7 minutes, until batter is smooth and about as thick as heavy cream.
Pour into well-greased muffin tins or custard cups.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Without opening oven, reduce heat to 350° and bake 15 to 20 minutes longer.
Serve at once.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix the broccoli, raisins, pecans and bacon slices together. Mix the mayonnaise, sugar and apple cider vinegar, then pour over the first mixture.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs over butter.
Press to firm the crust.
Pour condensed milk over crust evenly.
Add remaining ingredients.
Press down gently. Bake 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven (325° for Pyrex pan).
Cool before cutting into squares.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Put all in a skillet and slightly brown.
Heat boiling water and mix with bouillon in chicken base mix and enough to prepare the rice (2 to 1 water to rice), then add a little water for the pot.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until water is absorbed.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Prepare German chocolate cake mix as directed.

title: breakfast sausage and grits
directions: Cook sausage
until
done;
drain
and	put in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking
dish.
Combine
hot
grits, cheese and butter. Stir until
cheese melts and is well mixed.
Combine eggs and milk; stir into grits.
Pour into casserole; bake at 350° for 1 hour. Garnish with pimiento strips.
Makes approximately 15 servings. Can be made the day before and baked the next day.

title: easy microwave lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and mix with sauce.
Place layer of ground beef on bottom of pan, then noodles, then cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese and repeat layers.
Last layer needs to be meat/sauce mixture.
Cook on High 20 to 25 minutes.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Brown chops on both sides and put into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix celery soup with water and bouillon cube.
Mix well and pour over chops.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Mix Stove Top stuffing mix as directed on box.
Take pork chops from oven and put as much stuffing as you want on each pork chop. Cover and return to oven.
Bake at 350° for 30 more minutes.
(I took off foil and baked about 10 minutes to dry the stuffing a little.)

title: flaky cream cheese horns
directions: Blend ground walnuts with orange marmalade and sugar.
Blend margarine and cream cheese until fluffy.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add gradually to creamed mixture.
Form into 4 parts in wax paper.
Chill for 7 hours.
Roll, one at a time, like for pie.
Spread nut mixture over dough.
Cut into 6 or 8 triangles.
Roll up and bake at 350°.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: easy shrimp sauce
directions: May add more or less horseradish and Tabasco.
Mix together and serve.

title: coin carrots
directions: Pare and slice carrots.
Cook carrots in salted, boiling water until crisp-tender.
Drain and cool.
Combine carrots, onions and pepper in large bowl and set aside.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients.
Use a small amount of milk to make dough workable, if necessary.
Measure by spoonful and shape into balls. Bake 12 to l5 minutes at 350° or place balls on cookie sheet and freeze.
Drop into plastic bag and freeze to have ready to bake for unexpected company.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bake 9-inch pie shell at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cook ingredients together until clear or thick.
Cool and put over fresh strawberries in baked pie shell.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine butter, sugar, cocoa and milk; boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Add other ingredients, mixing well.
You may wish to substitute coconut for cocoa.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: banana fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients except nutmeats in large saucepan and bring to rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for three minutes, still stirring constantly.
Remove
from heat and let stand for 15 minutes without stirring.
Beat until thick and creamy light in color; add nutmeats if desired and turn onto buttered platter.

title: don't peek stew
directions: Put all ingredients in a covered casserole.
Mix well.
Bake at 250° for 4 1/2 hours or place in a crock-pot for 6 to 8 hours on low setting.

title: forever ambers
directions: Combine orange slices, condensed milk, coconut, pecans and orange extract in baking dish; mix well.
Bake at 300° until bubbly.
Stir in confectioners sugar.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let stand until firm.
Yield: 2 dozen.

title: vodka slush
directions: Mix
ingredients
together and freeze.	Fill tall glass 1/3 to 1/2 full with slush.
Add 7-Up and serve.

title: oatmeal squares
directions: Mix together the butter, flour and 1/2 cup brown sugar. Flatten mixture into cake pan bottom.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.
Mix together the eggs, 1 cup brown sugar, soda, salt and oatmeal; spread on top.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Cut into bars. Eat.

title: chocolate-peanut butter pudding
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, cocoa and cornstarch. Stir together in separate dish the milk, peanut butter and vanilla. Add to sugar mix. Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and bubbly. Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat.
Pour in bowl and cover with wax paper.
Chill for up to 24 hours. Serve layered with sliced banana and whipped cream.

title: scotch casserole with biscuits
directions: Saute
onion slowly in margarine
for
minutes.
Add ground beef and cook over low
heat
until
brown, breaking up meat with fork as it cooks.
Blend
in flour, salt and pepper. Stir in milk, pimientos and green peas.
Keep mixture hot.

title: christine's pie crust
directions: Pour water into shortening and beat until creamy.
Add flour and mix well.

title: goulash
directions: Brown in a saucepan the hamburger, onion and garlic.
Drain off fat; set aside.
Cook the macaroni in a large pot with plenty of water until done.
Drain off water, then add hamburger, onion, garlic and butter; mix well.
Then add Prego sauce and salt.
Mix well again.
Serve.

title: preacher pickles
directions: Put the cucumbers in stone jar.
Pour boiling water over for 3 days (change).
Put alum over cukes on the fourth day and cover with boiling water.
Wash on fifth day and cut up in 1/2 inch or thicker slices and put back in jar.
Bring the vinegar, sugar, cinnamon, mixed spices and salt to a boil and pour over the cukes in the jar.
Makes 4 gallon jars - 1/2 bushel.

title: garden salad
directions: Drain beans and corn.
Mix with celery, onions, green pepper and drained chopped pimento.
Bring vinegar, sugar, salad oil, pepper and salt to a boil.
Pour over mixture.
Chill overnight. Yields 12 to 15 servings.

title: chopped beef spread
directions: Mix together and serve with bagels, crackers, etc.

title: tuna surprise
directions: Mix together tuna, soup, corn and peas in pan; heat.
In separate pan, cook desired amount of rice.
When both are done, put desired amount of rice on plate and top with desired amount of tuna mixture and serve.

title: cherry salad
directions: Combine ingredients; sprinkle top with chopped pecans.
Chill 2 hours.

title: fruit crunch
directions: Put mixture of the first four ingredients into 2 separate bowls.
In the bowl that will be the mixture for the top, put 1 extra teaspoon of shortening for the top of the cake.
Mix second bowl until crumbly.
Press mixture into 13 x 9-inch greased pan.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add egg.
Sift and measure dry ingredients.
Add alternately with buttermilk or sour cream. Spread some rhubarb in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add remaining rhubarb to batter and spread over pan.
Top with 2/3 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon (well mixed).
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for angel food cake pan 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: crab and spinach quiche
directions: In a large bowl, lightly beat eggs.
Add milk, salt, pepper and nutmeg; set aside.
Combine cheese and flour.
Add to egg mixture with crab and spinach; mix well.
Pour into 2 pastry-lined 9-inch pie plates or quiche pans.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Cut into narrow pieces.
Serve warm.

title: oriental shrimp squares
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Trim bread and cut into 4 squares per slice.
Place spoonful of shrimp mixture on bread. Add another square of bread and pinch sides together.
Deep fat fry until toasted golden brown.
Serve at once.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Mix wet ingredients and dry ingredients, separately.
Add dry mixture to wet.
Mix nuts, 3 tablespoons sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon together.
In ungreased tube pan, place 1/2 of dough mixture, sprinkle nut mixture and then rest of dough.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain and crumble and reserve with 1/4 cup drippings.
Cook onion in reserved drippings until tender. Blend in flour, sugar, salt, celery seed and pepper.
Add water and vinegar.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Add bacon and potatoes, tossing lightly; heat thoroughly about 10 minutes. Garnish with parsley, if desired.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Stir chicken, green peppers, cream cheese and 1/2 cup salsa in medium saucepan on low heat until cream cheese is melted. Spoon 1/2

cup of chicken mixture down center of each tortilla; roll up. Place in lightly greased 12 x 8-inch baking dish. Stir cheese and milk in small pan over low heat until smooth. Pour sauce over tortillas. Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until heated. Top with remaining salsa.

title: rice broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients and pour into a 3-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: plum good cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Then put oil and beat eggs in one at a time.
Add the baby food and raisins or nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool about 50 minutes in pan.

title: little ears
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy. Add sugar and cream. Add enough flour to make a dough which can be rolled very thin.

title: chicken and dumplinsa choralier favorite!
directions: Add enough water to broth, soup and milk to make about 4-5 quarts.

title: donnie duke clark's homemade rolls or bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and undissolved yeast.
Combine water and Crisco and heat over low heat until liquids are warm. Gradually add to dry ingredients.
Let rise in warm place until double.
Work it down until stiff.
Make out as rolls in a muffin pan or as a loaf in loaf pan.
Let rise again until double in size, then bake at 375° to 400° until brown.

title: potato hamburger casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook beef and onion until meat is no longer pink; drain.
Stir in 1/2 teaspoon salt, pepper, green beans and soup.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole; set aside.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and put in greased baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Can be reheated in microwave.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Mix well the margarine and cream cheese with the sugar. Add eggs
one
at
a time; beat well.
Sift flour; add vanilla and butter.
Mix
all
this
and pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Layer chicken, onion rings and sliced cheese.
Mix soups, broth and tomatoes and pour over chicken.
Place chips on top (crushed).
Bake until bubbly.

title: creamed cucumbers
directions: Combine ingredients and gently mix with cucumber and onion slices.
Chill.

title: turnip stew
directions: Brown pork in oil; remove.
Add flour to oil for roux.
Add water, seasonings and pork.
Cook on low fire for one hour.
Add turnips and cook for one-half hour.
Add onion tops and parsley. Serve over rice.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Put the hash browns, 1/2 cup melted butter, sour cream, soup, onion flakes and salt and pepper in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan or casserole. Crush the cornflakes and mix with the 1/4 cup melted butter.
Sprinkle over the potatoes.
Grate the cheese and sprinkle over top. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: calzone
directions: Soften together yeast, honey and water.
Add salt and flour. Knead for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cover and set in a warm place to rise until doubled in bulk, 1 hour.
(I usually set it on the dryer outside.)
Punch down.
Divide into 6 sections and roll out in rounds 1/4-inch thick.
Fill with 1/2 to 3/4 cup filling on half of the circle, leaving a 1/2-inch rim.
Moisten the rim with water, fold the empty side over and crimp with a fork.
Prick it here and there.
Bake on an oiled tray in a preheated 450° oven for 15 to 20 minutes, or until crisp and lightly browned.
Brush each pastry with a little butter as it emerges from the oven. While the dough is rising, make the filling or if you want to make a pizza, chop up the ingredients.

title: garden pea salad
directions: Put drained peas in a
bowl. Add eggs, relish, onion flakes, celery salt and pepper.
Gently stir in mayonnaise until completely mixed. Sprinkle paprika on top.
(Can save some egg pieces to garnish top, if desired.)

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Mix the milk, peanut butter, egg and vanilla until smooth. Add Bisquick.
Mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on an ungreased baking sheet and bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Press the candy in the center of each cookie immediately after baking. Makes 5 dozen.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Mix ingredients together until zucchini is evenly coated. Pour mixture into a greased pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: cheese log
directions: Grate Cheddar cheese.
Allow both cheeses to soften to room temperature.
Mix both cheeses together.
Add in pressed garlic. Roll mixture into shape of a log so that it will fit on cracker. Sprinkle cheese with paprika and roll up in tinfoil.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Serve thin slices on crackers.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir water, 1/2 cup salsa, margarine and contents of vegetable seasoning packet in a saucepan.
Stir in stuffing crumbs until moistened.
Divide stuffing mixture into 6 servings in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover each serving with a chicken breast.
Pour 1/2 cup salsa over the chicken.
Loosely cover pan with foil.
Bake for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake until the cheese is melted.
Serves 6.

title: sour cream potato salad
directions: Mix potatoes with celery, onions, sour cream, French dressing and vinegar.
Add seasonings to taste.
Makes 4 servings.

title: prairie dogs
directions: Slit hot dogs lengthwise, leaving one side hinged.
Insert a thin strip of processed American cheese in slits and wrap each hot dog in a slice of bacon.
Grill hot dogs over medium heat, turning several times, until bacon is done as desired.
Serve in toasted buns with your favorite barbecue sauce.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Combine flour and salt in bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients, except soda, in large mixing bowl.
Beat at medium speed until light and fluffy, scraping sides occasionally, for 5 minutes.
Reduce to low speed; add dry ingredients and soda, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Bake 1 1/2 hours or until toothpick comes out clean, using 12-cup Bundt pan.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Invert onto wire rack; remove pan and cool completely.
Serves 16.

title: agnes' rice hot dish
directions: Fry hamburger and onion and drain off fat.
Put hamburger, onion and rice into baking dish.
Pour the green beans over the top.
Lay slices of Velveeta cheese all over top.
Add a little water to the soups and mix.
Pour soup mixture over the other ingredients.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: bacon-wrapped chicken-mushroom kabobs
directions: Cut each chicken breast half into 5 chunks.
Cut each mushroom in half.
In a large bowl, mix mushroom halves, chicken pieces, soy sauce, vinegar, honey, salad oil, green onions and juice from pineapple.
Let this marinate while preparing remaining ingredients.
Prepare outdoor grill for barbecuing.
Cut each bacon slice crosswise in half.
On 4 long skewers, thread bacon-wrapped chicken and pineapple pieces.
Reserve soy sauce mixture to brush on chicken kabobs.
Cook about 15 to 20 minutes on grill or until chicken is fork-tender and bacon crisp.
Yields 4 servings.

title: pretzel dessert
directions: In medium bowl, cream together margarine and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Add pretzels.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 10 minutes in preheated oven at 350°.
Cool.
In medium mixing bowl, beat together 1 cup sugar and cream cheese.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spread over cooled pretzel crust.
Chill.
Pour boiling water over strawberry gelatin.
Stir to dissolve.
Add frozen strawberries and stir until thawed.
Chill until gelatin is slightly thickened.
Spoon gelatin over cream cheese layer.
Chill until set.
Cut into squares and serve.
Garnish with additional whip cream, if desired.

title: heavenly chocolate
directions: Prepare Brownie mix according to directions and bake.
When done poke holes in top of brownies.
Pour Kahlua over them. Crumble brownies.
Prepare mousse as directed.

title: pie crust
directions: Combine sifted flour and salt in mixing bowl.
Cut in Crisco; mixture should be coarse.
Sprinkle with water a little at a time. Toss with fork.
Work dough into a ball.
Divide into two parts. Roll out.
Makes two pie crusts.

title: sausage and mushroom spirals
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brown sausage; drain well.
Stir in onion, parsley, cream cheese and mushrooms.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Separate dough into 8 rectangles.
Press together perforations. Spread about 1/4 cup meat mixture over each rectangle. Starting at largest end, roll up jelly roll fashion.
Pinch edges and ends. Cut each roll into 4 pieces.
Place, cut side down, on ungreased cookie sheet.
Brush with egg. Bake 16 to 21 minutes until a deep golden brown.
Serve warm with sauces (Dijon mustard, horseradish sauce, etc.) to dip in.

title: mary grilc's cheese strudel
directions: Mix cheese, sour cream, egg yolks, rind of lemon and tapioca. Beat egg whites until stiff, adding sugar gradually.
Fold into cheese mixture.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan generously.
Begin layering phyllo dough until bottom is covered.
Brush each with melted butter; use about 4 sheets, buttering each.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Brown onion with margarine. Brown ground beef and combine with rest of ingredients. Simmer for 20 minutes. Pour into greased casserole dish.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix together soups and rice.
Put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Top with chicken.
Brush chicken with melted butter and salt and pepper to taste.
(I melt 1 stick of butter and pour it over the chicken.)
Bake at 350° for a little over an hour.
Serves 6.

title: cream tarts
directions: Mix together ingredients, then pour into unbaked pie shells. Bake at 350° until done.

title: chicken paprikash
directions: Put chicken breasts into 13 x 9-inch baking dish (sprayed with Pam).
Sprinkle chicken with flour.
Simmer together onion, pepper, paprika and red pepper.
Pour tomato sauce, wine and simmered onion and pepper mixture over chicken.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours until chicken is done at 350°.

title: soft jumbles
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar, vanilla, and egg. Beat until smooth. Add flour, soda, and milk alternately, beating until well mixed. Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased baking sheet.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° until golden brown.

title: hot cabbage slaw
directions: Mix cabbage, onion, salt and pepper and let sit at least 4 hours before fixing dressing.
Take Crisco and place in large frying pan; melt and add a handful of cabbage and onion and saute until it starts to turn brown.
Add apple cider vinegar and cook 1 minute.
Pour over rest of cabbage to what has been added 1 tablespoon sugar.
Mix thoroughly and place on low heat and heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.

title: mushroom medley
directions: Use large skillet.
Place chopped onion, green pepper and fat; cook until light brown.
Brush to side of skillet and add beef and brown.
Mix all together.
Then add mushrooms, tomatoes and noodles.
Add seasonings, cover and simmer for one hour.
Sprinkle the grated cheese over the top a few minutes before it is time to serve.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Blend in an electric blender just long enough to make it chunky.
Chill and serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and pick off the bones.
Put chicken in casserole dish.
Mix sour cream and soup, then pour over chicken.
Crumble 1 pack of Ritz crackers and sprinkle over the top.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: homemade lemonade
directions: Mix together and refrigerate this syrup.
To make glass, mix 3 tablespoons syrup and add water and ice.
For pitcher, all syrup and 4 1/2 cups water.
Add lemon and/or orange slices to garnish.

title: caramel frosting
directions: In saucepan, melt butter.
Add milk and brown sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 2 minutes.
Cool 30 minutes, then add confectioners sugar and stir until smooth.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with milk and sugar. Slowly beat in Cool Whip and vanilla until mixed.
In a large clear bowl, make 3 layers.
Layer 1, cream cheese mixture.
Layer 2, cake.
Layer 3, cherries (spoon in with juice near edges to see cherries). Continue layers until bowl is full.
Last layer should be cream cheese mixture. Garnish with some cherries. Refrigerate overnight.

title: cheesy chicken fajitas
directions: Pour combined lime juice and jalapeno peppers over chicken and cover; marinate in refrigerator 30 minutes.
Drain.
Saute onion and pepper in oil until tender.
Add chicken; cook 5 to 7 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Add remaining ingredients except tortillas, stirring until process cheese product begins to melt.
Serve in warm tortillas.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Bring oil and vinegar to a boil.
Cool.
Pour over remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.

title: fruit slush
directions: Use juice from pineapple and peaches.
Add enough water to make 3 cups.
Add the sugar.
Freeze, then serve, partly thawed.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Cook cocoa, oleo, Crisco and water in rolling boil.
Mix together good and add flour and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake in cookie sheet 20 to 30 minutes.

title: breakfast egg casserole
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk, cheese, sausage and spices.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add bread (may refrigerate overnight). Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cuban chicken
directions: Add all ingredients.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Simmer for 1 hour, turning the chicken occasionally.
Serve the sauce over rice.

title: sparkling punch
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Then garnish with remaining 3 ingredients (float slices or wedges in punch).

title: fannie may fudge
directions: In saucepan, heat butter, sugars and milk; stir until dissolved.
Stir a few times until it comes to a boil.
Cover and let boil 5 minutes without stirring.
Remove from heat; add marshmallows and stir until dissolved.
Add chocolate in order given, one at a time, until melted.
Add vanilla and nuts.

title: ham and bean soup
directions: Rinse beans; place in Dutch oven with water.
Bring to boil over high heat.
Boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; let stand 1 hour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer, covered.

title: blueberry pound cake
directions: Mix cake. Fold in drained blueberries. Bake in greased and floured pan for 1 hour at 325°.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add alternately with buttermilk.
Add flavor and coconut.
Bake in a greased stem pan at 350° for 50 minutes or 1 hour.

title: velveeta cheese fudge
directions: Melt cheese, oleo and cocoa.
Add powdered sugar; mix well. Stir in vanilla.
Add nuts, if desired.
Spread into buttered 9 x 9-inch pan.
Chill for 1 hour.
Cut into squares.
Store in refrigerator.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and celery.
Mix jello with 3 cups of water. Mix with remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Mix the sugar, vinegar, salt and celery seed.
Add thinly sliced cucumbers and onions, one onion for each 3 cucumbers.
Let set in refrigerator at least 3 days, then eat!

title: goof balls or s'mores
directions: Melt caramels, oleo and milk together in double boiler.
Take marshmallows and dip in caramel mixture.
Then roll in Rice Krispies.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: clam pie
directions: Mix clam sauce, bread crumbs, butter and cheese in a medium bowl.
Pour into ungreased pie plate.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375° or until bubbly.
Serve as an hors d'oeuvre with crackers.

title: stuffed yellow squash
directions: Cut squash in half and take seed out.
Mix the hamburger and green pepper.
Stuff into squash and bake in 350° oven until meat is done.
Take out and put cheese on top.
Heat until melted.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place chicken (single layer) in baking dish.
Spread French dressing over chicken with pastry brush. Sprinkle 2 packages of Lipton onion soup over French dressing. Spread berried cranberry over Lipton onion soup.
Place in oven (not covered) for 1 hour.
Tastes great served over rice.

title: date-orange bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.

With electric mixer, cream the sugar and butter until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Stir in orange juice and orange peel. Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt.

Add to creamed mixture and blend well. Fold in dates and nuts. Spoon batter into pan. Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until pick inserted in center comes out clean. Remove from pan. Cool on rack. Makes 1 loaf.

title: lina's savory-frosted meat loaf
directions: Combine meat, French dressing, crumbs, onion, 2 beaten eggs, salt and pepper.
Shape into oval loaf in shallow baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Place on baking sheet or heat-proof platter.
Combine potatoes, one beaten egg and Miracle Whip. Frost loaf with mixture.
Broil until lightly browned.
Garnish with mushrooms and pimento strips.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: velma's bread
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Stir well to dissolve.
Add 2 1/2 cups flour and stir well.
Add shortening and salt.
Place 1/2 to 1 cup of flour on board and knead 100 times, working flour in. Let rise until double in size (about 2 hours).
Make into 2 large loaves or three medium loaves or rolls or alligators (cinnamon, nuts, etc.).

title: easy fudge
directions: Heat sugar, butter, cocoa, milk, vanilla and salt over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Spread quickly in buttered pan.
Cool; cut into squares.

title: dr. bird cake
directions: Put all dry ingredients together.
Then add all other liquids and put in well greased tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool before removing from pan.
Needs no icing.

title: dilled green beans
directions: Empty green beans into 1-quart saucepan.
Add water and salt. Bring to a boil.
Cook for 7 to 8 minutes or until green beans are just tender.
Add green onions, vinegar, oil, dill weed and sugar. Stir to blend.
Reheat.
Serve hot or chill and serve cold.

title: bread pudding
directions: Toast bread; break into baking dish.
Add 1/2 of milk; let soak.
Beat all ingredients together.
After milk is warm, add to bread and milk in baking dish.
Stir together and bake 30 minutes at 400°.
Be sure and put baking dish in pan of water.
This is like a custard.
Good served with lemon sauce.

title: caramel cookies
directions: Cream the shortening.
Gradually add sugars and cream thoroughly. Add eggs and vanilla extract. Stir flour, salt and soda. Gradually add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Press from a cookie press or drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: dill pickles
directions: *One piece of garlic at top of jar and one at bottom.

title: celery casserole
directions: Cook celery in boiling water to just cover for 8 minutes.

title: no-cholesterol hot fudge sauce
directions: Stir together sugar, cocoa, flour and salt.
Whisk in milk. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Remove from heat.
Let cool a few minutes.
Whisk in margarine; add vanilla.
Keep refrigerated in jar with tight lid.
Keeps up to 6 months.
Serve warm or cold.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: graham cracker dream bars
directions: Cover bottom of 9 x 13 pan with whole graham crackers. Combine in a saucepan margarine, sugar, milk and beaten egg.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, to full rolling boil.
Cool until warm.
Beat in cream cheese.	Add coconut, nuts and graham cracker crumbs.
Spread over layer of whole graham crackers, then top with another layer of whole graham crackers.

title: jumbo raisin cookies
directions: Add one cup water to two cups seedless raisins, boil five minutes.
Cool.
Cream one cup shortening adding little by little two cups sugar.
Add three eggs, beat well.
Add one teaspoon vanilla and cooled raisins.

Sift together four cups sifted flour, 1 teaspoon baking powder, one teaspoon soda, 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon, 1/4 teaspoon nutmeg, 1/4 teaspoon allspice, pinch of salt, mix well then add one cup chopped nuts.
Chill dough, drop by teaspoonful on a greased baking sheet.
Bake in hot oven (400 degrees) for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: frozen fruit cup
directions: Combine all fruits and juices.
Fill 9 x 13 inch pan or individual molds full.
Freeze.
Thaw for 30 to 60 minutes before serving.
Serves 25.

title: coffee cake
directions: Melt butter.
Mix with frosting mix.
Set aside.
Beat for 2 minutes:
cake mix, sour cream, eggs and 1 mashed banana.
Add 1 chopped banana.
Pour 1/2 the batter in 9 X 13 greased pan. Sprinkle 1/2 crumbled frosting mixture over batter.
Add rest of batter.
Top with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in a greased casserole dish.
You can mix 2 cups of crushed corn flakes and 1/4 cup melted margarine to put on top or you can use a can of Dundu onions on top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken or turkey divan
directions: Precook broccoli or other vegetables a few minutes.
Drain. Mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry.
Butter a 2-quart casserole dish and place broccoli in bottom.
Add chicken and cover with soup mixture.
Top with grated cheese and crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Drain artichoke hearts and green chilies.
Chop hearts coarsely and dice chilies.
Drain pimientos but reserve 2 teaspoons for garnish.
In medium bowl, mix first 6 ingredients. Spoon into 1 1/2-quart baking dish and sprinkle with additional Parmesan and reserved pimiento.
You can make ahead to this point and cover into refrigerator.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 30 minutes until bubbly.
Serve with chips.
Makes 5 cups.

title: idaho lentil soup
directions: Combine bacon drippings, onions, carrots and celery in 4 gallon kettle.
Cook, covered, 20 minutes.
Stir in flour, then other ingredients, except the sliced frankfurters.
Simmer, uncovered, 3 hours.
After 1 hour, cut meat from bones; chop. Return
meat and bones to kettle.
Just before serving, remove the bones; add sliced frankfurters to heat and salt to taste. Makes 50 servings.

title: party chicken salad
directions: Combine oil, marmalade, vinegar, mayonnaise, curry powder, salt and red pepper seasoning in 2-cup glass measure.
Stir until smooth.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate until ready to use.

title: chocolate chip butterscotch bars
directions: Combine flour and soda in a medium bowl.
Mix well. Set aside. In a large bowl, use an electric mixer to blend the sugar and butter. Add egg and vanilla. Beat at medium speed until light and smooth.
Scrape down the sides of the bowl, then add the flour mixture, pecans and chips.
Blend at low speed until just combined.
Do not overmix.
Transfer batter into a greased 8 x 8-inch baking pan and level top with a rubber spatula.
Bake at 300° for 35 to 45 minutes. Cool on rack.

title: johnnie mo-zetti
directions: Brown together hamburger and onion.
Combine remaining ingredients except cheese in a baking dish.
Place stripped cheese across top.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts and is well browned, about 30 minutes.

title: hot potato and broccoli vinaigrette
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into 1-inch cubes.
Cook potatoes covered in 1-inch boiling water until just tender.
Drain thoroughly and keep hot.
In another saucepan, cook broccoli (that has been washed and broken into small branches) in 1-inch boiling water until crisp-tender.
Drain thoroughly and keep hot.
In small saucepan combine remaining ingredients, except tomatoes.
Bring to just boiling over medium heat, stirring.
Arrange potatoes and broccoli in serving dish.
Pour hot vinegar mixture over, tossing gently. Garnish with tomatoes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add pineapple.
Set aside until syrupy.
Grind raw cranberries and measure equal amount of sugar. Mix berries, sugar, chopped apple and nuts.
Add to Jell-O mixture.
Let set 3 to 4 hours in refrigerator.
Will keep up to 2 weeks.

title: a loaf bread or hot rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350° before baking.
Dissolve yeast in one cup warm water.
Mix all other ingredients.
Let rise double in size. Punch down and half dough.
Put in greased loaf pans and bake about 1 hour.

title: apple crumble
directions: Place apples in buttered 9-inch pie pan; sprinkle with sugar and lemon juice.
Combine flour, brown sugar and nutmeg in small bowl.
Cut in butter with pastry blender until mixture is crumbly; sprinkle over apples.
