Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until juices bubble up and topping is golden.
Serve with ice cream.
Serves 6.

title: soup
directions: Chop vegetables into a large pan.
Add water to top of vegetables.
Cook until it comes to a boil.
Add onion soup mix. Boil for 10 minutes.
Cut down heat and cook until vegetables are tender.
Good alone or with brown rice.

title: tabbouli
directions: In ceramic or glass bowl, make layer of bulgur.
Add olive oil and lemon juice.
Layer with vegetables in this order:
all ingredients as listed beginning with scallions and ending with cucumbers.
Sprinkle vegetable salt and fresh mint over top.
Cover loosely for at least 24 hours and up to 2 weeks.
Serve on Romaine lettuce or in pita bread.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: stuffed mushrooms with sausage
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms and chop.
Cook sausage and onion. Drain.
Combine all ingredients and stuff mushrooms.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese if desired.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: yummy chicken
directions: Melt 1/2 stick of margarine.
Dip chicken pieces in melted margarine, then roll in mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour 10 minutes or until crispy.

title: bacon squares
directions: Mix mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce, salad seasoning and paprika.
Stir in cheese, bacon and onion.
Spread about 3 tablespoons of the mixture over each slice of bread (less if using party bread).
Bake on ungreased baking sheet at 400° for 10 minutes.
Cut each slice into quarters.
Serve hot.
Makes 56 appetizers.
This is a family favorite.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Let stand at least 3 hours, then rinse.

title: raspberry sherbet salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add sherbet immediately; stir until dissolved.
When slightly congealed, add crushed pineapple and nuts.
Pour into a mold and chill.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cut butter into dry ingredients.
Blend in egg, milk and vanilla. Roll out on
floured surface and cut out.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 8 minutes until lightly browned. Decorate with frosting and sprinkles.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Place ingredients in pie shell. Refrigerate/freeze, then serve.

title: chocolate scotcharoos
directions: In large saucepan, combine corn syrup and sugar.
Bring to a boil on medium heat.
Stir in peanut butter.
Mix well.
Stir in Rice Krispies.
Mix well and put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles with salt and drain.
Put egg in cottage cheese and mix well.
Brown hamburger meat; drain and add spaghetti sauce.
Let simmer 15 minutes.

title: warm sausage potato salad
directions: Place potatoes in a saucepan and cover with water; bring to a boil, Reduce heat; cover and cook for 4 minutes. Add beans; cook 3 to 4 minutes longer or until vegetables are tender. Drain and place in a bowl. Add sausage and onion. In a saucepan, melt butter. Stir in the flour, mustard, salt and pepper until smooth; gradually add the milk. Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 1 to 2 minutes or until thickened. Remove from heat. Stir in the mayonnaise; pour over vegetable mixture and toss to coat. Transfer to a 3 quart baking dish coated with non-stick cooking spray. Cover and bake at 350 degrees for 45 to 50 minutes or until heated through.

title: chocolate delight dessert
directions: Mix pecans, margarine and flour together.
Press into an 8 x 10-inch oblong dish.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes. Cool completely.
Mix Cool Whip, powdered sugar and cream cheese together. Spread 1/2 of mixture over crust after it has cooled.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Boil sauerkraut in water for 15 minutes; drain and cool.
Heat sugar in vinegar until dissolved.
Cool; add Wesson oil.
Mix all together.
Store in refrigerator.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into a ball; roll in parsley flakes.
Refrigerate.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Broil onions, mix all ingredients in buttered casserole dish. Top with cheese Ritz crackers.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Combine the ingredients.
Put oyster crackers in covered container (Tupperware).
Pour liquid over the crackers.
Seal and store overnight.
Toss occasionally so liquid goes through all crackers.
(You can make in the morning as long as you toss, so liquid goes over all crackers.)

title: meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Roll in small balls and bake 20 minutes at 350°. Makes 3 or 4 dozen.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Pour pie filling and pineapple in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend slightly.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over fruit mixture.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 12.

title: mush
directions: Give her a face, eyeballs and a nose. And a whole body and put icing clothes on it. Spray pans so the cake won't stick. Put red looking cake mix in it. Put it in the oven at 200° cause I don't like my cake to hot and you gotta cook cakes. You let it cool and put flowers on Barbie's clothes. Eat with lots of cold milk.

title: veg-all chicken pie
directions: Mix together and pour into 9-inch pie crust.
Top with second crust.
Put several 1-inch slits in top crust.
May brush with egg, if desired.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before slicing.

title: chocolate brickle
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to boil until caramel color; pour this on large cookie sheet and spread thin.
Pour in chocolate chips and pecans.

title: casserole cabbage rolls
directions: Chop cabbage and spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown meat; stir in rice, salt and pepper.
Spoon over cabbage.
Heat tomato soup and water to boiling.
Pour over all ingredients. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350° (Note:
Reduce oven to 300° after first hour). Fluff with fork before serving.

title: fruit salad or dessert
directions: Combine fruit, marshmallows and sour cream. Fold in whipped topping.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mary's meat balls
directions: Mix and make meat balls and add 1 small jar of grape jelly and 2 bottles of chili sauce.
Cook for 1 hour or maybe a little longer in 375° oven.

title: crab meat mousse
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except the whipping cream.
Whip the whipping cream (in a separate bowl) until peaks form.
Fold the cream gently into the mixture of crab meat.
Spoon mixture into mold.
Refrigerate until firm, (usually about 8 hours).
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Mix in corn, green beans, cream soup and 3/4 package of cheese.
Put into a lightly greased 9 x 13 pan; cover with single layer of Tater Tots and bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Remove and add the remaining cheese to top of Tater Tots.
Bake until cheese is melted and Tots are brown.

title: country fair blue ribbon chocolate cake
directions: Combine melted butter, cocoa and salt.
Add milk and vanilla. Mix into sugar in 3 parts.
Mix until smooth and glossy.

title: fall dessert
directions: Mix 2 cups cookie crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and margarine; press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate.

title: chocolate dream dessert
directions: Mix flour, nuts and margarine and spread in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Press mixture down with fork.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cool.

title: lime jello cottage cheese mold
directions: Sprinkle jello powder on cottage cheese and mix until jello is dissolved.
Add drained pineapple and mix.
Then add Cool Whip and stir until all ingredients are blended thoroughly.
Pour into jello mold and chill until firm.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Place Veg-All in casserole dish.
Melt Cheez Whiz with 1/2 stick of margarine.
Pour over Veg-All.
Crumble crackers in a bowl with 1/2 stick of margarine.
Crumble on top of Veg-All mixture.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: 9-day pickle
directions: Pour boiling water over cucumbers for 4 days.
Drain well each time.
On fifth day, make syrup and pour over for 4 days, drain and bring to boil each day.
Can pickles ninth day.

title: no bake strawberry pie
directions: Cook together sugar, water, jello and flour in a heavy saucepan until thick.
Put strawberries in crust and pour jello mixture on top.
Chill and top with whipped cream.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and pour into an 8 1/2-inch square casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 450° for 10 minutes. Serves 6.

title: quick mexican cornbread
directions: Mix and pour in greased pan.
Bake at 450° for 20-25 minutes.

title: spice ornaments
directions: Mix in bowl.
Put in Ziploc bag; knead.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Pour out.
Cut with cookie cutter and punch hole for ribbon.
Let dry on newspaper for 24 hours or bake 2 hours in 200° to 250° oven.
Makes approximately 24.

title: prize fudge frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients except vanilla in saucepan. Cover and cook slowly until mixture boils. Remove cover and cook without stirring until a little dropped into cold water forms a soft ball. Remove from heat, let stand until cool. Add vanilla. Beat until thick enough to spread.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Grind peppers in food chopper (using gloves or in blender without gloves).
If too hot for taste, decrease amount.
Bring sugar and vinegar to boil.
Add ground peppers.
Bring to rolling boil.
Remove from heat for 5 minutes; add Certo and pour in sterilized jars.
Cover with melted paraffin.

title: beef burgundy and rice
directions: Saute beef, carrots and onion in oil over high heat until beef is browned, 3 to 5 minutes.
Add bouillon cube, water, wine and seasonings. Bring to a full boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover.
Remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Stir or place in serving dish and sprinkle with parsley. Makes 4 servings, each less than 350 calories.

title: buca di beppo garlic mashed potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and place in large pot.
Cover with water and bring to a boil over medium to high heat.
Reduce heat to low and cook until the potatoes are tender.
About 15 minutes.
Drain potatoes and transfer to large serving bowl. Immediately add garlic, oregano, salt, cheese and butter.
Blend thoroughly with the whip attachment of an electric mixer.
Serves 4.

title: jellied fruit salad
directions: Heat fruit cocktail to boiling.
Stir in jello and boil for 2 minutes.
Pour into bowl and chill until set, but not real firm.

title: homemade chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken until done.
When cooled off, debone.
In medium size bowl, add soup, milk and chicken; mix well.
Gently stir in mixed vegetables.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add to pie crust lined pan.
Top with other pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until brown.
This is wonderful!

title: banana bread
directions: In bowl 1, mix flour, soda and salt.
In bowl 2, mix margarine and sugar.
In (large) bowl 3, mix bananas, eggs and sour cream. Mix flour and sugar mixture, 1 cup at a time, to banana mixture. Divide into 3 loaf pans and bake at 350° about 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: swedish sugar cookies
directions: Boil raisins in water until almost dry.
Beat sugar, shortening, vanilla, eggs and salt well.
Add raisins.
Add flour and soda.
Mix well.
(Add more flour if necessary; sometimes it will take more if raisins are wetter.)
Make small balls of dough. Roll in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together with electric mixer until smooth.

title: crazy crunch
directions: Bring sugar, oleo and corn syrup to boil, stirring constantly. Boil 10 to 15 minutes, or until mixture turns light caramel color (290° on a candy thermometer).
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla. Pour over popcorn and peanuts on lightly greased baking sheet. Toss with 2 large spoons until all are coated.
Cool.
Break into pieces and store in plastic bags.

title: sloppy joes(from leftover meat loaf)
directions: Soak country ham in water overnight.
Remove from water; pat dry with paper towel.
Place in roasting pan, skin side up.
Add 4 cups water, pineapple juice or any liquid.
Place in cold oven. Heat to 400°.
After temperature reaches 400° for 20 minutes, turn oven off and leave for 3 hours (never open door).
Turn oven back on to 400° again and leave 20 minutes.
Cut oven off and leave for 8 hours or overnight.

title: chicken 'n dressing
directions: Cook chicken (preferably in pressure pan) in enough water to yield amount of broth.
Strain broth.
Mix 1/2 chicken soup and 1/2 of broth with mushroom soup (1/2 of broth goes in chicken soup).
Set aside.
Combine stuffing mix with butter; reserve 1/2 cup for garnish.
Add celery and onion to chicken soup.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Spoon half the stuffing mix into dish.
Add 1/2 chicken; cover with 1/2 chicken soup mixture. Repeat stuffing, chicken and chicken soup layers, then pour mushroom soup over all.
Sprinkle with reserved stuffing mixture. Refrigerate overnight.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Soak apples in lemon juice several minutes.
Combine apples with all other ingredients and lightly toss.
Refrigerate overnight and serve chilled.

title: dr. pepper chili
directions: Brown meat and onion; add garlic, salt, tomato paste, Dr. Pepper and water.
Simmer until thick.
Add remaining ingredients. Put lid on pan and cook 10 more minutes.
Serves 8.

title: raisin nut bars
directions: Mix flour, sugar and butter until it looks like corn meal. Put in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: traditional mississippi mud cake
directions: Beat eggs until thick.
Add sugar.
Combine margarine, flour, cocoa, vanilla and nuts.
Mix well and add to sugar mixture.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove and spread marshmallow cream (thin layer) over top while warm. Let stand a few minutes before adding frosting.

title: southern style potato salad
directions: Boil the potatoes and dice into cubes.
Dice boiled eggs, well. Dice sliced pimientos.
Dice green pepper and onions, very fine. Add all other ingredients.
(Miracle Whip and sandwich spread should aid in bringing about the overall desired consistency.) Salt and pepper can be added, season to taste.
Serves 16 to 20.

title: grandma stauffer's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the margarine, sugars, eggs and vanilla in a large bowl. Add dry ingredients and mix well. Fold in chocolate chips. Drop by spoonful on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes. Cool on rack.

title: chicken-rice bake
directions: Mix 1/2 package soup mix with the other ingredients except chicken.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and place chicken on top. Sprinkle rest of soup mix over chicken.
Bake covered at 400° for 1 hour.

title: nonfat sour creammexican sour cream
directions: Mix together and it's done, refrigerate!

title: cucumber and onion
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers and onion.
Soak in salt water for 2 hours.
Add vinegar and sugar.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: blackened scallops
directions: Mix spices and herbs, except salt, with oil in a small bowl. Set aside.
Heat cast-iron pan over high heat. When hot, add spice mixture to pan and cook 1 minute. Stir constantly!
Add pepper and shallot. Mix and cook 2 minutes over high heat. Add scallops.
Mix well.
Cook 3 minutes over high heat. Stir once and season with salt.
Serve over hot pasta.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.

title: zelene placky
directions: Combine the sauerkraut and eggs and enough flour to make a soft dough.
Turn the dough onto a floured board.
Roll out to 1-inch thickness.
Cut into squares and place on a greased pan. Brush with melted margarine and bake at 400° until done, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sweet and sour marinated vegetables
directions: Wash broccoli thoroughly; cut flowerets and stems into bite-size pieces.
Combine broccoli, cauliflower, mushrooms and green onions in shallow dish.
Combine remaining ingredients in a jar.
Cover tightly; shake vigorously.
Pour over vegetables. Cover and chill at least 3 hours.
Drain vegetables just before serving.

title: nora jean's mexican casserole
directions: In largest skillet brown hamburger and chopped onion with salt, pepper, garlic salt and lemon pepper.
Drain excess grease. Add remainder of ingredients to meat mixture and simmer until hot.

title: mamaw's oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugars.
Add eggs, water and vanilla.
In a separate bowl, sift together dry ingredients, except oatmeal.
Stir dry ingredients into creamed mixture.
Stir oatmeal into mixture 1 cup at a time.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, until lightly browned.
Cool 2 minutes and remove.

title: chocolate caramel bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°; beat eggs, sugars, dressing and vanilla together.
Then add flour and soda.
Set aside 1 cup batter; spread remaining batter in a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Melt caramels with milk over low heat.
Top crust with melted caramels.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and pecans.
Spoon remaining batter by teaspoons over pecans.
Continue baking 10 to 15 minutes, until light brown.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt butter.
Add onion, rice, beef broth and mushrooms (do not drain).
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour. Serve 8 to 10.

title: fat-free pumpkin drop biscuits
directions: Combine the flours, sugar and baking powder.
Stir to mix well.

In a separate bowl, combine the pumpkin and buttermilk; stir until blended. Add the pumpkin mixture to the flour mixture and stir just until the dry ingredients are moistened. Coat a baking sheet with nonstick cooking spray. Drop heaping tablespoonfuls of dough onto the sheet, placing the biscuits 1/2-inch apart for soft biscuits or 1 1/2-inches for crusty biscuits.
Bake at 375° for about 18 minutes or until lightly browned.
Transfer to a serving plate and serve hot.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: 1. Layer drained broccoli on bottom of 9 x 13 inch dish.
2. Mix other ingredients except Parmesan cheese, butter,
and chicken. Second layer chopped chicken, sprinkle
cheese between layers and spread sauce on top.
3. Dot with butter. Bake 30-40 minutes at 350°.
4. Sprinkle with toasted almonds.

title: marjorie whitfield's devil cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs, beating until creamy.
Add chocolate mixture.
Beat on low the flour and buttermilk mixture alternately.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook in two 10-inch greased pans for about 30 minutes.

title: cottage cheese cool whip dessert
directions: Mix dry jello, cottage cheese and add drained fruit and nuts or marshmallows.
Fold in Cool Whip and chill until jello is set. Garnish with fresh fruit.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients except tomato sauce.
Roll into miniature balls.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.
When ready to serve, mix and heat tomato sauce with meat balls.

title: shepherd's bread
directions: Scald milk and stir in sugar, salt and oleo or butter.
Cool to lukewarm into large warm bowl.
Sprinkle in yeast.
Stir until dissolved. Stir in lukewarm milk mixture and half the flour. Beat until smooth.
Stir in enough additional flour to make a soft dough.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat, onions and pepper. Add other ingredients. Cook slowly about 3 hours. Serve on hamburger buns. Freezes well.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into strips.
Salt each piece, dip in flour and fry in pan with oil.
Add meat, soup, water and chopped onion to crock-pot. Add salt and pepper and bouillon to taste.
Cook on high for 4 to 6 hours or until meat is tender.
Serve with white rice and corn.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine, blend in flour.
Cook over low heat until smooth and bubbly.
Gradually add milk.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Boil for 1 minute.
Add salt, soup and 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Stir until cheese melts.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Stir in sour cream.
Add chicken and broccoli; mix well.
Turn into greased 9 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: black cherry salad
directions: Heat cherry juice and water.
Add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Chill until it begins to thicken.
Add remaining ingredients except lettuce.
Pour into mold and chill until firm. Unmold and serve in lettuce cups with salad dressing.
Serves 8.

title: crabmeat thermidor
directions: Thaw crabmeat and retain liquid (may substitute imitation crabmeat).
Melt butter over medium heat.
Stir in flour, salt and paprika until blended.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook, stirring, until mixture is thickened.
Remove from heat.
Stir in crab, liquid, parsley, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, Tabasco and 1/4 cup cheese.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix ingredients and roll into balls.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 400°.
Add 1 bottle hot catsup and bake a few minutes more.

title: lemon custard cloud(tart and tangy; rich, yet light)
directions: Place egg yolks, lemon juice and fruit sweetener in small saucepan.
In small dish, dissolve cornstarch in water.
Add this to lemon mixture.
Blend in potato flakes.
Stir over medium heat until mixture thickens.
Cool thoroughly.
Beat egg white and cream of tartar until stiff peaks form.
Fold in cooled lemon mixture.
Tear cake into walnut-size pieces and fold into lemon mixture.
Spoon into dessert glasses or glass square pan.
Chill. One serving = 1 bread and 1 fat exchange, 130 calories, 18 grams carb., 3 grams protein, 5 grams fat, 88 mg sodium and 51 mg cholesterol.

title: seven layer salad(serves 15)
directions: Layer in order given and let stand 2 hours or overnight.
Mix just before serving.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and "topping". Press mix into casserole dish (9 x 13-inch). Mix cheese/topping and sprinkle on top. Bake in a 450° oven for 12 to 15 minutes. May be made ahead the day before except for cheese and topping. Serves 4.

title: vanilla wafer dessert
directions: Roll 1/2 wafers. Spread in bottom of pan. Beat eggs and sugar until thick and creamy. Spread over wafers. Mix nuts and pineapple with whipped cream and spread over top of butter mixture. Roll rest of wafers and spread over top.

title: instant hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in airtight container. Use 2 teaspoons in a cup of hot water.

title: popcorn cake
directions: In a large pan put popped popcorn, nuts and candied fruit. Melt together oleo and marshmallows.
Pour over popcorn mixture. In well buttered angel food cake pan, press into pan.
Set for a couple of hours in refrigerator.
Turn out and slice.

title: calico corn custard(makes 8 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 1/2-quart baking dish.
Dice peppers.
Place in large bowl. Strain corn and reserve liquid. Add corn to peppers.
Add milk to reserved liquid to measure 1 cup.
Beat eggs thoroughly.
Beat in sugar, nutmeg, salt, pepper, half and half and milk.
Pour in prepared dish and bake in boiling hot water bath in oven for 40 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Blend room temperature butter, sugar and salt together.
Add syrup and milk; blend thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat 1 minute.
Add flavoring and pecans.
Pour into unbaked deep-dish pie crust.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: tofu enchiladas
directions: In a medium bowl, combine tofu, cheese, cilantro, onion, corn and chili powder.
Heat enchilada sauce.
Dip each tortilla quickly into the heated sauce and place it on a flat surface; top with 1/2 cup tofu mixture and roll tightly.
Place seam side down in an 8-inch square shallow baking dish.
Pour remaining sauce over enchiladas.

title: brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl combine dry ingredients.
Combine remaining ingredients in another bowl; add to dry ingredients and stir to blend.
Place batter in an 8 x 8-inch nonstick pan sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake 15 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: working girls pie
directions: Mix ingredients well in large bowl. Pour mixture into pie shell. Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours. Serves 6 to 8.

title: brown sugar muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add beaten egg.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk and vanilla.
Add nuts.
Pour into muffin cups and bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: peach pie alaska
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add ice cream by spoonfuls.
Stir until melted and smooth.
Blend in whipped topping and fruit.
Chill, if necessary, until mixture will mound. Spoon into crust.
Chill about 3 hours or freeze until firm. Makes 8 servings.
Garnish.
If you're counting calories, try making this recipe with sugar-free Jell-O.

title: chocolate-chip cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Coat 10-inch Bundt pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Mix together cinnamon, sugars and cocoa in small bowl; set aside.
In a mixing bowl, combine cake mix, vanilla pudding, eggs, sour cream, milk and oil; beat for 10 minutes. Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour into prepared pan, alternating cake batter and sugar mixture.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 70 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Yield: 12 servings.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Combine meat, tomatoes, soup and beans and heat.
Line pan with Doritos.
Pour mixture on top.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Prepare the cake mix as directed, adding the oil.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes in a sheet cake pan.
Beat the cream cheese until soft.
Mix the pudding with the milk and blend in the cream cheese.
Spread on a cooled cake.
Mix the pineapple with the Cool Whip and spread over the cream cheese.
Sprinkle with coconut and nuts.

title: nut cake
directions: Cream butters and sugar in one bowl.
Mix rest of ingredients together in another bowl (except vanilla and nuts).
Slowly add ingredients to butter and sugar.
Add vanilla when all mixed.
Add nuts to mix slowly.
Put in cold oven.
Cook 1 hour at 325° in 2 tube pans.

title: peach kuchen
directions: Sift first 3 ingredients.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Press into glass baking dish, 9 x 11-inch.
Cut up fruit (cut plums in half and take out pit or slice peaches).
Mix together sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over fruit.

title: rocky road candy(great for gift giving)
directions: Melt morsels with margarine and condensed milk on low heat until melted.
Mix in marshmallows and nuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool in refrigerator.
Cut into squares.

title: walnut bread
directions: Sift flour into mixing bowl.
Add sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Add egg, milk and vanilla; mix until blended.
Add 1 1/4 cups walnuts.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Sprinkle remaining 1/4 cup walnuts over top. Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Let stand in pan 10 minutes. Turn out onto wire rack to cool.
Makes one loaf.

title: apple date dream
directions: Sift sugar, flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and allspice.
Combine eggs, pie filling, oil and vanilla.
Stir into flour mixture and mix well.
Stir in dates and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool and cut in squares and serve with whipped cream or Dream Whip.

title: next best thing to robert redford
directions: Blend the flour, butter and pecan pieces.

Press in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake for 15 minutes in a 250° oven. Beat the cream cheese, sugar and half of the Cool Whip and pour on the crust. Mix the chocolate, vanilla and milk all together and pour over cheese layer.
Add the remaining Cool Whip and sprinkle with crushed pecans on top.

title: taco salad
directions: Prepare ground beef according to directions on seasoning mix package.
In a large salad bowl, layer lettuce, meat, olives, cheese, tomato, onion and broken tortilla chips.
To serve, toss well and top with taco sauce and/or your favorite dressing.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water, set in refrigerator to cool, but not jell.
Empty cake mix in a bowl, add oil and eggs, alternately.
Add a little lemon peel, if desired.
Add jello mixture last.
Mix well.
Bake in 9 x 12-inch sheet pan or tube pan at 350° or until golden brown, don't overbake.
Keeps well.

title: tapper dough
directions: Put flour in a very large bowl (that has a sealed cover). Make a well in the center.
Add milk, water, sugar, salt and eggs. Then sprinkle with yeast.
Do not mix.
Seal lid; let set one hour.
Remove seal; add 1 cup melted margarine.
Mix together and knead dough.
(May need more flour.)
Reseal.
When the lid pops off, the dough is ready to shape into rolls, etc.

title: applesauce spice muffins
directions: Cream butter; gradually add 2 cups sugar, beating well at medium speed with an electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add applesauce, mixing well.

title: crunchy parmesan chicken
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients.
Dip chicken in mixture of egg and milk.
Roll chicken in dry mixture.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Pour melted butter over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: cornish hens with wild rice dressing
directions: Wash hens; glaze with diet margarine and orange marmalade. Place stuffed hens with rice in oven at 350°.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: The day before or early in the morning you can begin.
In a large kettle or bowl, combine gelatin with boiling water, stirring until dissolved.
Then fold in all at once, strawberries with juice, drained pineapple, bananas and nuts.
Turn half of strawberry mixture in 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish as a first layer and refrigerate until firm, about 1 1/2 hours.
Then evenly spread sour cream.
Gently spoon on rest of strawberry mixture and refrigerate.
Just before serving, cut in squares and serve on lettuce leaves.
Serves 12.

title: chicken paprikash
directions: Brown chicken in shortening in skillet.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook over low heat for 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Serve over flat noodles.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Fill pie plate with sliced apples.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
In a small bowl mix butter, flour, sugar and egg.
Add salt and walnuts, if desired.
Pour all over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: clam chowder
directions: Dice and cook potatoes in 6 qt.
Dutch oven, set aside.
Do not drain.
Cook, drain and crumble bacon.
Cook celery and onions in skillet with a small amount of fat left over from the bacon.
Put bacon in skillet with onions and celery on very low heat.
Drain clams and tuna and add to skillet, allow to simmer for a few minutes.
Pour contents of skillet in pan with potatoes and add milk.
Cook on low heat until almost boiling.
Add corn starch to cold water and stir into soup.
Cook until solids stay suspended when soup is stirred, thicken more if needed.

title: chocolate yogurt melts
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in large bowl; beat until blended. Stir in walnuts and chocolate pieces.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoons 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Garnish with walnuts if you wish.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until cookies are set.
Cool on wire racks.
This is a chewy, brownie-like cookie with a chocolatey flavor.

title: chili rellenos bake
directions: Brown beef and onions; drain.
Sprinkle meat with salt and pepper.
Halve chilies crossways and remove seeds.
Place half the chilies in 10 x 6 x 1/2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese; top with meat mixture, arranging remaining chilies over meat.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Pour over chilies.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes until knife comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes before serving.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Mix and roll into small biscuits.
Bake until light brown. Can be made ahead and frozen.

title: raisin pumpernickel bread
directions: In large bowl, combine yeast and warm water.
Let stand about 5 minutes.
Add rye and whole wheat flours, molasses, cocoa, coffee and salt.
Beat dough by hand or with dough hooks until flour is moistened.
Stir in all-purpose flour.
Scrape dough onto floured surface.
Knead, adding as little flour as possible, about 5 minutes.
Put raisins and sunflower seeds into dough and knead to distribute.
Place dough in oiled bowl; cover with plastic wrap and let rise until double, about 1 hour.

title: waldorf cranberry mold
directions: Heat 1 cup cranberry juice cocktail just to boiling.
Dissolve gelatin in hot juice.
Add remaining juice and salt.
Chill until partially set.
Stir in apples, celery and nuts.
Pour into 6 individual molds.
Chill until firm.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add vinegar and food coloring; beat well.
Sift dry ingredients; add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla; beat well.
Pour into tube cake pan and bake at 350° until done.
(Knife inserted into cake will come out clean.)

title: creamed dried beef
directions: Melt butter in heavy frying pan. Add dried beef and cook a few minutes. Blend in flour. Stir thoroughly. Take from heat. Add milk and blend well. Heat until boiling, stirring constantly.

title: melon mint cocktail
directions: Boil for 5 minutes the sugar and water to make a simple syrup. Pour simple syrup over 3 tablespoons chopped mint leaves.
Let syrup cool, strain it and add to it the juice of lemon and orange. Chill.

title: crab delight
directions: Bone and flake the crabmeat.
Combine with green pepper and pimento.
Blend together the 1/4 cup salad dressing, egg yolks, onion juice, onion and seasonings.
Add to the crabmeat mixture; toss until well mixed.
Pack into 6 custard cups and unmold into casserole.
Top each with 1 tablespoon of salad dressing; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in a 400° oven for 25 minutes, or until bubbly. Makes 6 servings.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Warm in crock-pot at least 2 hours.

title: fruit cake macaroons
directions: Chop cherries and dates; mix all ingredients.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Debone and chop.
Put in bottom of large casserole dish.
Add 1/2 of stuffing mix; place chicken on top.
Pour stock over, then place remaining half of stuffing mix on top.
Slightly dilute cream soup and pour on top using a fork to force some of the soup down.
Bake at 325° about 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: finger paint
directions: In a large bowl, mix starch and cold water.
Stir in boiling water.
Microwave on High for 3 to 6 minutes.
Mix in soap and coloring.
Paint away.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix buttermilk with pudding, then add cool whip.
It will seem rather lumpy at first, but it will smooth right out.

title: jambalaya
directions: Brown sausage; add all ingredients except green pepper. Heat to	boiling, stirring occasionally.
Reduce to simmer 10 minutes. Cook
uncovered.
Stir
in green pepper.
Heat until pepper is warm.

title: rosemary pifer's imperial holiday cut-outs
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg and water, beat well.
Combine with flour, baking powder and salt. Chill at least one hour or overnight.
Roll dough to 1/8 inch thickness.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes.
Frost and decorate.

title: blueberry sauce
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in water.
Add berries.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer until clear and thickened, 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove from heat; add lemon juice and rind.
Chill. Good on pancakes and waffles.

title: cook while you sleep cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350° while mixing mixture, then turn oven off. Beat egg whites.
Add cream of tartar and salt.
Beat until stiff. Add sugar, two tablespoons at a time, beating after each addition. Stir in vanilla, nuts and chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheets lined with aluminum foil.
Put in oven (make sure heat is off!).
Do not open oven door for at least 8 hours.
Carefully remove cookies from foil.
Makes 40 to 50 cookies.

title: cherry filled coffee cake
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients in order given.
Reserve 1 cup of batter; pour rest into greased jelly roll pan.
Spread cherry pie filling over batter.
Drop reserved batter by the teaspoonful over the pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until done. Cool.

title: hobo casserole
directions: Crumble ground beef into a baking dish.
Layer potatoes, cheese, onion and green pepper over beef.
Spread with soup. Bake, covered with oiled foil, at 300° for 1 hour or until ground beef is cooked through and potatoes are tender.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Add enchilada sauce, soups and chili peppers.
Cook 15 minutes at low heat.
Place layer of sauce in casserole; add layer of tortillas and layer of cheese.
Repeat and end with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: creamy scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 2-quart casserole.
Cut potatoes into slices, about 4 cups.
Heat 3 tablespoons margarine in a saucepan until melted.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Stir until mixture is smooth; add milk and cook until bubbly.
Arrange potatoes, onions and sauce in layers alternately.
Cover and bake for 30 minutes, then uncover and bake for awhile longer, until potatoes are tender.

title: chocolate creme de menthe bundt cake
directions: Mix first five ingredients well.
Reserve 1 cup of this mixture and to it add creme de menthe.
To the remaining batter, add chocolate syrup.

Pour chocolate batter into your Bundt pan or an angel food pan which has been sprayed with Pam, then pour your green batter in (you may want to add a couple drops of green food coloring on top of the chocolate).
Don't stir!
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Mix all together except half of cheese.
Put in casserole. Top with rest of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or more, until heated through.

title: corn bread casserole
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Pour into a greased 11 x 7 x 2 in. baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 400 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes or until the top and edges are golden brown.
Yields: 4 to 6 servings.

title: butternut squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Pour into lightly greased 1-quart dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until set. Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: spicy new york strip roast
directions: Trim excess fat from steak. Combine thyme and next 5 ingredients in a small bowl; crush with back of spoon. Pat mixture evenly on both sides of steak. Heat olive oil in a cast-iron or ovenproof heavy skillet over medium-high heat.
Add steak and cook 3 minutes on each side. Bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes or until desired degree of doneness.
Remove from oven; cover with aluminum foil and let stand 10 minutes. Cut into thin slices and serve with buttered rice.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Prepare brownie mix and bake according to directions in a 9 x 13 pan. Prick top of warm brownies with fork at 1-inch intervals and drizzle with Kahlua or coffee. Let cool and crumble.

title: chicken-in-a-pot
directions: In Dutch oven, brown chicken in oil until golden.
Add onion, garlic and seasonings.
Cover and slow cook 30 minutes.
Add tomatoes and wine and simmer 30 minutes or until tender.

title: lemon squares
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients; mix well and pat into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: venison steak
directions: Season steaks with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Layer steaks and vegetables in a crock-pot.
Mix together the soup and water.
Pour over steaks and vegetables.
Cook on low for 8 to 10 hours.

title: saturday morning breakfast bake
directions: Brown sausage.
Cut bread slices in half.
Place bread lengthwise on ends and place in 2 rows in 9 x 9-inch baking dish. Sprinkle sausage on top and in between slices of bread.
Beat with fork remaining ingredients.
Pour over top, making sure it gets between bread slices.
(Make sure you grease the pan; Pam will do.) Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes, covered.
Remove cover and cook for about 5 to 10 minutes longer.
Top with cinnamon or pancake syrup.

title: cheddar-scalloped potatoes
directions: Over medium heat, melt margarine in 10-inch skillet.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Stir in soup, milk, pepper and potatoes.
Heat until boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; cook 5 minutes or until hot and bubbling, stirring occasionally.

title: lyna's best grilled chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken.
Cook in large saucepan until boiling.
Turn to low; add chicken; simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove chicken and grill slowly over charcoal or gas grill approximately 20 minutes. Outside will be crispy and inside delicious.

title: yia yia's greek easter bread
directions: Proof yeast in water.
Mix together milk and sugar, then butter and eggs.
Add yeast mixture.
Slowly add flour.
Knead for 10 minutes.
Let rise until doubled in oiled bowl.
Cover.
Knead again for 10 minutes; let rise.
Knead again.
Roll into 3 strands and braid dough.
Circle braid in a Bundt pan which has been oiled.
Cover and rise once more.
Brush on an egg wash and sprinkle sesame seed.
Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cinnamon friendship tea mix
directions: Combine ingredients as listed.
Package for gift giving.
For 1 serving, combine 1 tablespoon of mix and 1 cup hot water in a mug.
Add sweetener, if desired.
Makes 2 1/2 cups mix.

title: cherry salad
directions: Drain pineapple and mix all ingredients together. Refrigerate.
Keeps several days.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling water.
Arrange stalks and florets in greased baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
Cook chicken until done.
Cut up breasts and place chicken on top of broccoli.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour three 8-inch pans. Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add eggs.
Mix flour and spices. Mix with sugar mixture. Add berries and mix well.
Pour into greased pans and bake 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
Cake should be moist. Don't overbake.

title: seven week muffins
directions: Pour 2 c. boiling water over 2 c. 100% all bran.
Cool. Cream crisco and sugar, add eggs, then add all remaining ingredients to the cooled water and bran mixture.
Blend well. Bake at 350° for 12-15 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen muffins.
Batter will keep in refrigerator 7 weeks.

title: the next best thing to robert redford
directions: Combine flour, margarine and nuts and press into bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Cool.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and half of Cool Whip.
Blend until smooth.
Spread over cooled crust.
Combine puddings with milk and whip until well blended.
Pour over cream cheese mixture. Spread remaining Cool Whip over pudding.
Refrigerate overnight or 6 to 8 hours.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Stir all ingredients together with wooden spoon.
Do not grease pan.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: In blender, combine dry milk powder and sugar.
Pour in melted butter and with machine running, add boiling water.
Blend until mixture is smooth and thick.
Store in covered container in refrigerator until used.
Makes 14 ounces or equivalent to 1 can of Eagle Brand milk.

title: orange blossom slush(powder mix)
directions: Stir together dry ingredients.
Put in blender.
Add vanilla. Mix in blender.
Store in airtight container.

title: ricotta cheese cookies
directions: Cream all ingredients together.
Then add 4 cups flour.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Ice cookies with Cream Cheese Icing dipped into coconut.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions and sugar in 3 tablespoons butter until golden brown. Stir in flour & pepper. Gradually stir in broth. Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes. Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 30 minutes. Stir in parmesan cheese. Meanwhile, in a skillet, melt remaining butter; add bread. Cook until brown. Ladle soup into 2 ovenproof bowls. Place a slice of provolone cheese in each bowl; top with bread and remaining cheese. Bake at 375 degrees for 10 minutes.

title: hamburger pinwheels
directions: Mix Bisquick and milk.
Roll out about like pie crust, not too thin.
Mix oleo, catsup, mustard and onion.
Spread over dough. Crumble raw ground meat on top.
Roll up dough like a jelly roll. Cut about 1/4-inch slices; lay on cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 400°.
Serve on plate with soup or gravy on top.

title: portuguese soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in large pot.
Bring to boil, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat; simmer until thick, 2 hours. Stir once or twice.
Season with pepper.

title: date-nut balls
directions: Cook
dates,
sugar and margarine, stirring constantly, until margarine
is
absorbed.
Add nuts and pour hot mixture over rice cereal in a large bowl.
Mix well.	Form into small balls
and dust with powdered sugar.
Put several small balls in a
paper bag with powdered sugar and shake until balls are coated.
Yield: 4 dozen.

title: potato casserole
directions: Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, lightly greased with butter.
Top with 1/4 cup melted butter and 2 cups corn flakes. Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Combine corn bread mix, eggs, butter, broccoli, onion, cheese and salt in bowl.
Mix well.
Spoon into baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: quick guacamole
directions: Mix avocados, salsa and lemon juice in bowl.
Make sure avocados are mashed.
Refrigerate.
Serve with tortilla chips. Makes about 2 cups.

title: corn pudding
directions: Add milk to corn, melted butter, seasoning and eggs.
Mix well.
Add baking powder and pour into greased casserole.
Bake about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: old-fashioned apple pie
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Mix all dry ingredients together. Fold in apples.
Add water.
Pour into pie crust; add butter on top of apples, then put crust on top.
Cut 3 holes in top so air can escape.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix eggs, milk, sugar, flour, water, salt and pepper.
Beat well.
Butter baking dish and add some butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Stir about 1/2 cooking time.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix and cook on low heat until sugar is dissolved.
This makes about 4 cups.
Slice apples and dip in sauce.

title: noodle pepperoni pizza
directions: Discard seasoning packets from noodles or save for another use.
Cook noodles according to package directions, drain.
Heat oil in ovenproof casserole dish.
Press noodles into dish, evenly covering the bottom of the dish.
Cook until bottom of the crust is lightly browned, about 5 minutes.
Pour sauce over the crust. Sprinkle with cheese and add pepperoni.
Broil 4 to 6 inches from the heat for 3 to 4 minutes or until heated through and cheese is melted.

title: yummy potato casserole
directions: Mix together hash browns, 1/2 c. butter, salt, pepper, dried onion, soup, sour cream and cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 - 60 minutes in a 9 X 13 baking dish.
Halfway through baking add cornflakes, 1/4 c. butter and grated cheese.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Store in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Prepare Mexican cornbread as directed on package.
Saute onions and zucchini with a little water.
After cooking until tender drain off excess water.
Add zucchini, onion, soup and seasoning to cooked cornbread.
Mix well.
Spray pan with Pam.
Pour mixture into pan and add cheese on top.
Let cook in oven at 350° for 25 minutes or until cheese melts and browns.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix together pudding and Cool Whip.
Mix in all other ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put sugar, syrup and water in a pan and bring to a boil over high heat.
Turn to medium-high heat and continue cooking until it reaches 264° on a soft crackle.
Add peanuts and cook 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat, then add the butter and soda.
Stir up well and pour out immediately in ungreased pans. You could use two people to do this; one to pour and one to spread it out.
It hardens very fast.

title: chocolate icing
directions: Place margarine, cocoa and milk in a saucepan. Bring to a boil, being careful not to let it scorch. Add powdered sugar, vanilla, and pecans. Spread on warm cake.

title: maida pakoda or fritters
directions: Chop onions, green chilies, ginger and coriander leaves.
Mix the flour with salt and baking soda.
Add buttermilk, water and chopped ingredients.
Heat oil.
Take small portions of dough and drop in the oil.
Fry until golden brown.
Prepare in the same manner until all the mixture is used up.
Serve hot.

title: apple muffins
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix applesauce, egg and melted butter.
Pour all at once into flour mixture.
Stir just until moistened.
Pour batter into greased muffin cups.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: beef noodle bake
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Boil your noodles. Put in baking dish. Pour tomato juice on top of meat mixture.
Put 1/2 cheese on top. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Take out.
Stir the mixture.
Put rest of cheese on top, bake 15 minutes.
Ready to eat.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump all ingredients into a 9 x 13-inch ungreased cake pan. Never mix ingredients.
Put ingredients in pan in order given for best results.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until nicely browned.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: sour cream scalloped potatoes
directions: Put thawed hash browns in large casserole dish.
Combine soup concentrate, sour cream, cheese, 1/2 cup butter and onions. Gently blend into potatoes.
Combine corn flakes and 2 tablespoons butter.
Sprinkle on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 16 servings.

title: crescent cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Open 1 can rolls and lay flat on bottom of pan.
Mix egg yolk, sugar, 2 packages cream cheese and vanilla.
Spread on flat rolls.
Open 2nd can of rolls and lay flat on top of cheese mixture.
Brush with egg white.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into four pieces.
Place white sugar and cinnamon in a plastic bag.
Add biscuit pieces, a few at a time, and shake to coat.
Place pieces in a greased tube pan until all are used.
Bring brown sugar and margarine to a boil in saucepan. Pour over top of biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Turn topside up to serve.
Pieces are picked off when eaten.
Great fun for all!

title: choco-mint snappers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt chocolate over hot (not boiling) water.
Remove from heat.
Combine shortening, sugar and egg in bowl and beat until creamy.
Blend in chocolate and corn syrup. Sift together flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt and stir in gradually.
Shape dough into balls using 1 level tablespoon for each.
Roll balls in sugar (about 1/4 cup).
Place 3 inches apart on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let stand a few minutes before removing from pan.
Makes 3 dozen 3-inch cookies.

title: chocolate no-bake cookies
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients over medium heat until margarine is melted, then boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and quick oats.
Stir and use spoon to drop cookies onto waxed paper or greased pan.
Let cool and enjoy.

title: lemon bars
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients.
Press into 8 x 8-inch pan and microwave for 3 minutes on High.
Beat eggs until fluffy.
Stir in flour, baking powder, sugar, juice and lemon rind.
Pour over layer, which has been heated already.
Cook on High for 6 minutes. Cool and cut into squares.

title: onion rings
directions: Slice onions and soak in milk (enough to cover onion rings) overnight or at least 2 hours.
Beat the egg with the milk that the onions stood in.
Dip onion rings in milk mixture, then in flour, then back in milk, then in cracker crumbs.
Let dry a little, then deep fry in deep fryer.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Note:
If using whole chicken, chop into bite size.

title: poor man's cake
directions: Bring sugar, cinnamon, water, shortening and raisins to a boil over medium heat for 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool to lukewarm at least, or until cold.
Mix remaining ingredients in large bowl.
Add cooled mixture and stir well.
Bake in loaf pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: company cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix cracker crumbs, 2 tablespoons sugar and margarine.
Press in bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake 10 minutes; cool.
Heat oven to 300°.
Beat cream cheese in large mixer bowl.
Add 1 cup sugar gradually, beating until fluffy.
Add lemon peel and vanilla.
Beat in 1 egg at a time.
Pour over crumb mixture.
Bake until center is firm, about 1 hour.
Cool to room temperature.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours, but no longer than 10 days.
Top with sour cream or glaze.
Makes 12 servings.

title: pineapple-yogurt pops
directions: Combine all ingredients; pour mixture into frozen pop molds or 12 (3 ounce) paper cups, inserting wooden sticks.
Freeze until firm.
Yields 12 servings; 0.3 grams fat; 59 calories; 1 mg. cholesterol.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add slightly beaten eggs.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add alternately with sour cream.
Add vanilla and cinnamon.
Pour into oiled pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.
(Makes 1 large loaf or 2 small loaves.)

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Pour into baking casserole dish.
Do not cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Should be brown on top.

title: red tomato relish
directions: Combine vegetables; drain.
Add sugar, vinegar and spices. Let set 10 minutes.
Bring to a boil, then simmer for 30 minutes. Heat lids.
Put relish into jars and seal.
Makes approximately 7 pints.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Place pie filling in cake pan, well-buttered.
Arrange rolls on top.
Bake at 375°
for 30 minutes.
Spread powdered sugar glaze on top while warm.

title: chocolate filled cupcakes
directions: Cream the first 5 ingredients and add chocolate chips. Mix remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Batter will be thin.
Fill cupcakes 1/2 full.
Fill with a teaspoon of cream cheese mixture. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease bottoms only of 2 loaf pans.
Blend all ingredients on low speed for 1 minute, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat on medium speed 1 minute.
Pour into pans.
Bake 50 minutes to 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes in pans; remove to rack.

title: pound cake fruit cake
directions: Beat butter and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs one at a time. Add flour, vanilla and baking powder; mix well.
Stir in nuts and candied fruits.
Mix well.
Pour in a greased and floured Bundt pan and bake at 350° for first 30 minutes; finish baking at 300° for one hour.

title: mint-fudge cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheets.
In small mixer bowl, beat cake mix and sour cream with electric mixer on medium speed about 2 minutes, or until smooth and creamy.
The batter will be stiff, so an electric mixer combines it best.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded spoonful 2 inches apart on prepared cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven 10 to 12 minutes. Makes about 6 dozen.

title: gena's yellow cake
directions: Grease and lightly flour two 8 x 1 1/2-inch or two 9 x 1 1/2-inch round cake pans.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
Beat butter about 30 seconds.
Add sugar and vanilla; beat until well combined.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 1 minute after each.
Add dry ingredients and milk alternately to beaten mixture, beating after each addition.
Turn into pans.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until done.
Cool 10 minutes on wire racks.
Remove from pans.
Cool.
Serves 12.
Also can be used for cupcakes.

title: chilli-cheese appetizer
directions: Place 1 pie crust on a pizza pan. Spread on cheeses. Evenly distribute green chillies on top of cheeses. Top with remaining pie crust. Seal edges of pie crusts with a fork and prick top pie crust generously. Sprinkle chili powder on top crust. Bake in preheated 450° oven 10 to 15 minutes. Serve with salsa and sour cream.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocados in medium bowl with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
In another bowl, combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning.
To assemble, spread bean dip on a large shallow platter.
Top with seasoned avocado mix.
Layer with sour cream mixture.
Sprinkle with onion, tomatoes and olives.
Cover with cheese.
Serve chilled or at room temperature with chips.

title: mimi's frozen cranberry salad
directions: Butter 9 x 13-inch dish with 2 tablespoons butter.
Mix with a fork softened cream cheese, mayonnaise and sugar.
Add crushed pineapple, whole cranberry sauce, Cool Whip and pecans.
Pour into dish.
Cover and freeze.
Cut into squares when ready to serve. (Allow a few minutes out of the freezer before cutting.)
Good with turkey or ham or for dessert.

title: amazing mongolian shrimp
directions: Butterfly shrimp, leaving tail on.
Place ham piece in center with 2-inch piece of green part of green onion.
Wrap with one piece of bacon and hold with toothpick.
Deep fry until bacon is brown.

title: parmesan cheese chicken
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Dip chicken breasts in melted butter or margarine, then in crumb mixture.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put 1 pie shell in a large pie pan.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Put other pie shell on top and crimp.
Do not prick top!
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until golden brown.
Let sit before serving.

title: soul steaks
directions: Trim excess fat from steak.
Combine beer and hot sauce to marinate steak in .
Marinate
steak in refrigerator for 12 to 24 hours, turning several times.
Remove from refrigerator, allowing steak to warm to room temperature before cooking.

title: cake batter
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar (beat).
Add Crisco oil and beat until fluffy; add milk (beat).
Add 2 cups flour, beating as you add them.
Add flavoring.
Oil and flour your pans.
Put in oven and heat them.
Spoon batter into pans.
Cook at 350° until light brown and springs back at touch in middle.

title: "buckeyes" peanut butter balls
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and roll into balls.
Set in refrigerator for 1/2 hour or longer to firm up.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips.
Dip the balls into hot chocolate mixture.
Put on wax paper to cool.
Can be frozen indefinitely.

title: chicken spaghetti(feeds the masses; freezes well)
directions: Saute celery and onion in butter until onion is clear.
Add olives, peas and soups; mix well.
Cut up Velveeta and add to mixture.
Add tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Mix spaghetti with all ingredients, except Mozzarella, in large pan.
Cover with grated Mozzarella. Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 45 minutes.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except ginger ale.
When ready to serve, add chilled ginger ale.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, beaten well.
Sift together all dry ingredients and add alternately with applesauce to shortening mixture.
Mix lightly.
Pour into a greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with 1/3 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake at 335° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: corn and ham soup
directions: Combine all ingredients except half and half in a saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in half and half.
Heat thoroughly.

title: chop suey
directions: Brown meat lightly in skillet.
Add 2 cups of water and salt. Simmer until tender (1/2 hour).
Combine flour and 1/4 cup of water; substitute cornstarch for flour for shiny, thick chop suey. Stir into hot meat.
Add green pepper, onion and celery.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes.
Add bean sprouts and soy sauce.
Heat 10 minutes or more to blend.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: vegetable burger soup
directions: Brown ground beef, then drain.
Stir in the rest of the ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 1/2 hour.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and peanut butter; add milk.
Fold in Cool Whip and pour in pie crust and freeze.

title: cherry delight
directions: In a saucepan, melt margarine.
Add crushed graham crackers and mix well.
Press mixture into 8 x 8-inch glass dish.
Combine softened cream cheese and confectioners sugar together and pour over layer of graham cracker crust.
Sprinkle pecans over cream cheese mixture.
Next, gently spoon cherry pie filling over nuts. Whip Dream Whip according to package directions and spread over pie filling.
Garnish with crushed graham crackers.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: walnut bourbon balls
directions: Thoroughly mix the vanilla wafer crumbs, confectioners sugar, cocoa and walnuts.
Add corn syrup and bourbon and mix well. With hands, roll mixture into 1-inch balls, then roll each in granulated sugar.
If desired, wrap each ball in plastic wrap or colored foil.
Store in tightly covered container.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: frozen fruit cup
directions: Boil sugar and water.
Cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in a container and freeze.
Keeps well.
Defrost and serve. Serves 6.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix in a saucepan and bring to a boil the margarine, sugar, cocoa and milk.
Boil for 1 minute. Add the peanut butter, vanilla and oats. Stir and drop by the teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: diabetic dessert
directions: Mix vanilla pie filling with milk as directed on box.
In large bowl (punch), slice cake.
Place a layer of cake in bottom of bowl. Place a layer of pie filling over cake, layer of pineapple, layer of bananas, layer of pudding, layer of Cool Whip and sprinkle with a few chopped nuts.
Repeat with another layer of all of the layers, ending with Cool Whip and nuts.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in ungreased glass Corning Ware at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Yields about 6 servings.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Bring sugar, salt, cocoa and 1/4 cup milk to a boil. Boil for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes. Remove from heat and add margarine and vanilla; let cool. Mix pudding and 3 cups milk. Stir in Cool Whip. Layer crackers, 1/2 pudding mixture, crackers, pudding mixture and top with crackers. Beat the cooled cocoa mixture and spread over the top layer of crackers.

title: heavenly lemon cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in a large bowl. Add
egg
yolks,
water,
vegetable oil, lemon rind and lemon juice.
Stir until smooth.	Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until
stiff
peaks
forms.
Fold egg whites into flour mixture, blending
well.
Pour
batter into ungreased 10-inch tube pan. Bake
at
for 1 hour and 10 minutes, or until done.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk together.
Add sour cream and whipped topping.
Layer bananas, wafers and pudding, ending with pudding. Add wafers for decoration.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix and bake for 35 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add milk.
Sift flour with baking powder; add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Add eggs and grated coconut.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Mash avocados with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and seasoning mix.
On large tray, layer one on top of the other: bean dip, avocado, seasoning mix, onions, tomatoes and cheese.
Serve as dip with Doritos.

title: tarter sauce
directions: Mix all together and chill before serving.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well and spread on a platter.
Layer the remaining ingredients keeping the Cheddar cheese last.
Serve with corn chips.
Serves 10 to 15.

title: creamed cabbage
directions: Boil ingredients until tender.
Make a medium white sauce and layer with cabbage mixture in a buttered casserole.
Top with cracker crumbs and bake until bubbly.
Even children like this.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Drain pineapple and use juice to mix pistachio pudding mix. Drain fruit cocktail and add fruit to the mixture.
Mix marshmallows and Cool Whip together and add to the mixture.
Add pecans and mix well.
Chill overnight.

title: harvest fruit mold
directions: Combine fruit and enough water to cover in saucepan; simmer, gently covered, for 30 minutes.
Add sugar for last 5 minutes of cooking.
Drain fruit, reserving syrup.
Add water to syrup to make 2 cups.
Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups boiling water.
Stir in syrup mixture.
Chill to partially set.
Pit prunes; cut up all fruit.
Fold into gelatin.
Pour into 6-cup ring mold.
Chill until firm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: nut hershey pie
directions: Put in double boiler and heat to melting.
Remove and cool. Whip 1/2 pint heavy cream.
Add to Hershey mixture, folding in. Put in baked pie shell and refrigerate.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: luscious bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan. In large bowl, combine cake mix, margarine, sour cream and eggs at low speed until moistened.
Beat for 2 minutes at highest speed. Stir in nuts and spread in preheated pan.
Bake for 18 to 20 minutes.
Center will not be firm to touch.
In medium bowl, combine coconut and Eagle Brand milk.
Gently spoon and spread over partially baked base.
Return to oven and bake 15 to 20 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool completely and spread frosting over bars.

title: cheesecake date bars
directions: Combine cookies and butter with 1/2 cup sugar in bowl, mixing well.
Set aside 1/2 cup for top.
Press remaining mixture onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.
Mix dates with flour; set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients with 1 cup sugar; mix until smooth.
Add to date mixture, blending well.
Pour over crust; spread to cover.
Sprinkle reserved crumbs over top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes and cool.
Cut into bars.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: brides delight
directions: Drain
pineapple juice into saucepan with 2 tablespoons cherry juice.
Heat
and	add
marshmallows to dissolve.	Add fruit and nuts
and
cool.
Add
whipped
cream and fold into mixture.
Pour into
individual
molds, regular mold, spring-form
pan
or
flat dish.
Chill at least 8 to 12 hours.
Very good.
Can
be used as a salad or a dessert with Cool Whip and cherry on top.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Mix meat, onion and celery.
Place into cooked cabbage leaves; roll up.
Place the rolled end down in pan.
Put in 1 quart tomatoes.
Just before serving, pour 1 can tomato soup over cabbage.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: tropical fruit dip
directions: Thaw Cool Whip.
Mix all ingredients.
Great with green grapes, mandarin oranges, watermelon or any of your favorite fruits.

title: raisin sour cream pie
directions: In top of double boiler, blend together sugar, cornstarch and salt. In small bowl, combine beaten eggs, 1 1/2 cups of the sour cream, the raisins and the lemon juice. Stir in sugar mixture. Set over hot, not boiling, water and cook until thick, stirring frequently. Pour into baked pie crust.
When cool, top with remaining 1/2 cup sour cream. Chill several hours. Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: parisian rice
directions: Combine and bake until thick in covered casserole at 350°. Serves 4 to 6.

title: buttermilk doughnuts
directions: Mix all ingredients together; add flour last.
Stir until shininess leaves the dough.
Roll on floured surface and cut. Deep fry in vegetable oil or shortening until golden brown.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: artichoke appetizers
directions: Cook onion in water until tender; drain.
In bowl, combine eggs, crumbs, salt, pepper, oregano and hot pepper sauce.
Stir in onion, cheese and artichokes.
Spread in greased 11 x 7-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 25 minutes or until set.
Cut into squares.
Serve hot, garnished with pimento strips.

title: dessert fruit squares
directions: Mix sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Add lemon juice.
Slowly beat in flour.
Spoon mixture onto well-greased 15 x 10-inch cookie sheet and then spread evenly.
Visualize 20 squares and dab your choice of pie filling (about a tablespoon) in the center of each square.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Let cool partially, then sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Cut into 20 squares.
Great for taking to potlucks.
Spoon on Cool Whip if desired when serving.

title: rising to the occasion
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl blend cream cheese, sugar and vanilla with 1 egg until smooth.
Pour into pie shell. Sprinkle with nuts.
In another bowl, blend 3 eggs, corn syrup, 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1/2 cup sugar until smooth.
Gently pour over nuts.
Bake on center of oven rack for 50 to 60 minutes, until center is just set and pastry is golden.
Cool on a wire rack. Serves 8.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Let rise until double.
Punch down and roll out.
Spread with butter and cinnamon.
Roll together like jelly roll; cut in pieces.
Let rise until double.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 400°.

title: apple pie
directions: Peel apples, slice in pastry shell.
Mix with fork and spread remaining ingredients over apples.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
This makes a delicious pie!

title: coconut cake and icing
directions: Beat 5 ingredients and fold into rest of ingredients.
Pour into two 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° until done when tested.

title: crab-shrimp salad
directions: Butter one side of bread and cube.
Place in a bowl.
Add all the other ingredients except crab and shrimp.
Refrigerate overnight or several hours.
Before serving, add crab and shrimp.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Blend at medium speed flour, sugar, oil, baking powder and orange juice.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Fold in 1 pint frozen blueberries which should be slightly floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes in a greased tube pan.
Top with sugar and cinnamon.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken and cut up.
Place in a large baking dish and add soup and peas.

title: squash puffs
directions: Cook squash, onion and green pepper until tender; drain well. Mix other ingredients.
Combine all ingredients and mix well. Drop into fryer by teaspoons and brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place ingredients in casserole.
Mix, cover.
Bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: scotcharoos
directions: Melt first 4 ingredients in top of double boiler.
Pour over Rice Krispies and nuts, if desired.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan which has been sprayed with Pam.

title: microwave chili dip
directions: Crumble beef into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Add onions.
Cover and microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes or until beef is browned, stirring once.
Drain off fat.
Stir in tomato paste, chili seasoning and garlic.
Cover and microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes or until hot.
Serve with corn chips.
Makes 2 cups.

title: baked vegetable cutlets
directions: Saute the peppers in the olive oil until soft, about 15 or 20 minutes.
Add all of the remaining ingredients except the vegetable oil and let the mixture stand for 30 minutes or overnight, refrigerated.
Bring to room temperature before continuing.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Blend well. Sift flour into bowl, scoop out center as for biscuits and pour mixture in center. Mix by hand until just firm enough to roll.
Pinch off small ball.
Roll and pat flat onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: my chicken recipe
directions: Place chicken in casserole dish.
Mix preserves and dressing. To this, add 1/2 of onion soup mix.
Pour mixture over chicken. Sprinkle the rest of the soup mix over the top.
Cover and cook in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash 15 minutes; drain well.
Put in casserole dish. Add onions, soup, sour cream, pepper and salt.
Put oleo over top. Cover with crushed crackers.
Cover with foil.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove foil and bake one minute.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in bread pan for 1 hour at 350°. Cool in pan 20 minutes, but upside down and tap bottom to remove. Cool on rack.
Good eaten with butter or cream cheese.

title: grandma parker's grasshopper salad
directions: Put all in a dish and stir all together.
Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Soften cheese, mayonnaise and sugar.
Mix well until creamy. Add cranberry sauce, pineapple and nuts and mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in a 9 x 12-inch dish.
Freeze overnight.
Can be stored in freezer for several weeks.
Serve frozen.

title: lime-nut congealed salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple.
Add water to make 2 cups.
Place on stove.
Add marshmallows, continuing to heat until marshmallows are melted.
Place jello in bowl.
Pour hot liquid over jello, stirring until dissolved.
Place in refrigerator; leave until it begins to congeal.
Mix well the remaining ingredients, pecans, cream cheese and drained pineapple.
Add to congealed mixture, mixing well.
Return to refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: cool whip fruit salad
directions: Mix thoroughly and refrigerate 4 to 8 hours before serving. Will keep in refrigerator about one week and will freeze wonderfully. Can be eaten frozen. Thaws quickly.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Boil the sugar, salt, margarine, syrup and vanilla 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add soda.
Stir quickly. Pour over popcorn; mix well.
Spoon onto a large flat pan.
Bake in 250° oven 1 hour.
Stir in oven and as it cools so it won't stick.

title: brownie pudding
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Add milk, salad oil and vanilla; mix until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Mix together brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa; sprinkle over batter.
Pour hot water over entire batter.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: baked apples
directions: Spread applesauce in baking pan.
Core apples and peel down an inch from top.
Place on applesauce.
Stuff each apple with 1/2 of a pitted date and 1/2 teaspoon margarine.
Sprinkle apples lightly with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until tender, basting with sauce 2 or 3 times.

title: almond layers
directions: Blend together sugar, margarine and almonds.
Pat in bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake about 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Blend 4x sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Spread.
Mix chocolate and vanilla puddings and 2 cups milk only.
Let set a few minutes. Layer on top of cheese mixture.
Add remaining Cool Whip; sprinkle with almonds.
Cover.

title: florida sunshine salad
directions: Wash and thoroughly dry the romaine lettuce.
Tear into pieces and put into a large bowl.
Slice the avocado onto the lettuce. Peel and separate the grapefruit into sections, removing all membranes.
Put on top of the avocado.
Crumble the Blue cheese on top of the grapefruit.
Just before serving, add the fruit salad dressing and mix lightly.

title: coffee cake
directions: Combine pudding mix with cake mix.
Add oil, water, eggs and flavorings.
Beat well.

title: salmon tetrazzini
directions: Cook together olive oil and onions.
Add flour, salt and thyme; mix.
Stir in half and half or milk; cook until thickened. Stir in sherry, pepper, salmon, olives and green pepper.
Turn into greased shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish (I use 9-inch square Pyrex dish).
Sprinkle with 1/3 cup grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Garnish with paprika and parsley.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Sift flour and pepper.
Put cheese and shortening through food chopper.
Add a little flour occasionally to keep chopper from clogging.
Gradually work flour into cheese and shortening until smooth and pliable.

title: sesame soy halibut
directions: With whisk, mix together soy sauce, tahini, brown sugar, peanut oil, vinegar, red pepper and sesame oil until well combined. Gently warm in small saucepan.
Cook fettuccine according to package directions.
Drain.
Toss with green onion and 1/2 cup sesame soy sauce.
Keep warm.
Bring 3 cups water and lemon juice to boil in large skillet.
Add halibut.
Lower heat.
Simmer, covered, until halibut flakes when tested with a fork.
Gently remove halibut and drain.
Divide halibut and pasta onto 4 dinner plates.
Drizzle with remaining sesame soy sauce.
Sprinkle with cilantro and sesame seed.

title: lime jello mold
directions: Combine Jell-O, sugar and hot water; dissolve.
Add marshmallows.
Stir until more completely dissolved.
Cool at room temperature.
Add pineapple, cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Add walnuts.
Set 4 hours in refrigerator.

title: irish bread
directions: Sour milk by adding 2 tablespoons vinegar to 2 cups milk.
Let sit for 5 minutes.
Mix dry ingredients into bowl; add butter, caraway seed and raisins.
Mix together lightly.
Beat egg and add dry ingredients.
Pour sour milk in and stir with a fork until well blended.
Don't overbeat.
Put in a well buttered black frying pan. Melt 2 tablespoons butter and pour over top.
Sprinkle with sugar. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 50 additional minutes.

title: six layer lettuce salad
directions: Layer in 8 x 10 pan: 1. Lettuce broken into bite size pieces. 2. Onions (diced). 3. Frozen peas. 4. Spread on mayonnaise mixed with 2 tablespoons sugar. 5. Sprinkle on cheese and Farmland bacon which has been crumbled. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Put persimmon pulp, 2 cups sugar, 1/4 cup melted butter, eggs, sour milk and baking soda in large bowl.
Mix and pour into cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
When done, take out of oven and poke holes in cake.
Bring water, 1 tablespoon butter and 1 1/2 cups of sugar to a boil in pan.
Pour over cake.
Put back in oven for about 10 minutes.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Mix dry goods.
Melt butter and seasonings; pour over cereal. Mix well.
Bake 15 minutes at 325° then at 300° for 45 minutes.
Or microwave 6 to 7 minutes (stir every 2 minutes).

title: melt-in-your-mouth almond cake
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream the butter and sugar.
Add almond extract.
Add eggs one at a time. Beat well after each addition.
Stir soda into yogurt.
Add yogurt alternately to butter mixture with flour, mixing well.
Bake in greased 9 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cranberry crunch
directions: Mix together oats, flour and brown sugar.
Cut butter into mixture.
Place 1/2 mixture into 8 x 8-inch greased baking dish. Press in.
Cover with whole berry cranberry sauce.
Place other 1/2 of mixture on the cranberry sauce.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: diabetic strawberry pie
directions: Cook until slightly thickened. Add 2 boxes sugar-free strawberry Jell-O. Let completely cool. Fold in 1 quart sliced fresh strawberries. Put into a graham cracker crust. Refrigerate.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip together Cool Whip and cream cheese.
Add sugar, milk and vanilla.
Stir in the peanut butter.
Place in freezer for at least 2 hours.
Thaw before serving.

title: creamy lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend first 3 ingredients for crust and press into bottom and up sides of a 9-inch pie plate (use a fork). Bake 10 minutes and cool.

title: mexican dip
