directions: Mix in small bowl the sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning mix.
Begin layering in a large casserole, starting with bean dip, then avocado dip, then sour cream mixture, then remaining ingredients in order given.

title: popular pesto pizza
directions: Put the crust on a cookie sheet and spread the sauce onto it. Spread the pesto over the tomato sauce. Pile on the cheese! If you want to make the crust crunchy, spread the butter around the edges and sprinkle on the salt. Cook at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until crust is golden brown. Cooking times may vary according to crust types.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt chips.
Add nuts.
Spoon onto cookie sheet lined with waxed paper.
Let set.

title: deer jerky
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Pour 2 cups over meat in mixing bowl and mix thoroughly.
Divide meat into 2 doubled food storage Baggies with previously unused liquid.
Put on tray in refrigerator for 24 hours, turning and mixing occasionally.
Drain off liquid. Lay on paper towels and pat off excess liquid.
Dry in dehydrator at 145° for 6 hours, longer for thicker slices.
Can also be dried in oven.

title: fruit juice spritzers
directions: Combine equal portions of chilled fruit juice and club soda or mineral water or for a sweeter taste ginger ale.
Pour over crushed ice.

title: rosemary's cinnamon tea rolls
directions: In medium bowl, blend cottage cheese and butter.
Add in flour and mix until dough forms a ball (dough is better if refrigerated overnight).

title: watergate salad
directions: Fold all ingredients together and chill.

title: hearty cheese chowder
directions: Cook vegetables in water about 10 minutes, until just done. Add creamed corn; season to taste and set aside.
Melt butter in separate pan and mix with flour.
Gradually add milk, stirring over medium heat until thickened.
Add cheese and heat until cheese is melted.
Do not boil.
When ready to serve, combine cheese sauce with vegetables and ham.
Heat thoroughly.

title: german chocolate brownies
directions: Melt 2/3 cup margarine and chocolate over low heat.
Set aside to cool.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Set aside. Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla until well blended.
Mix in chocolate until blended.
Add dry ingredients.
Beat until smooth. Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool.

title: ham appetizers
directions: Spread cream cheese on ham slice.
Roll and cut in small sections. Makes good appetizers.
Slice rolls.

title: never fail dumplings
directions: Mix ingredients.
After it is mixed all together, divide into 3 parts.
Roll each part out very thin and let dry for about 20 minutes.
Cut into small strips and drop into broth of boiled chicken.
Chicken may be picked off the bone and added to broth and dumplings.

title: escalloped pineapple
directions: Beat together eggs and sugar.
Add pineapple and butter, cut in pieces.
Mix together.
Pour over bread cubes.
Mix well.
Pour into rather shallow, slightly greased pan (9 x 13-inch).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve as hot vegetable.
Great with ham.

title: savory lamb kebobs
directions: In a large bowl, add all of the ingredients.
Cover all pieces of meat well.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours or until next day, stirring several times.
On metal skewers, thread meat and vegetables.
Cook on medium coals 4 to 6 inches above fire.
Cook about 15 minutes, rotating often.
Makes 6 to 8 kebobs.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Mix butter and cream cheese. Add sugar.
Add one egg at a time and continue beating.
Fold in flour, a little at a time. Add coconut and vanilla.
Bake in a tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: peanut butter nut clusters(microwave)
directions: Place chips in a 2-quart casserole and microwave 2 minutes. Stir well and microwave 2 more minutes.
Stir in nuts and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper until set.
Store in airtight container.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: positive power salad
directions: Dice first 4 ingredients.
Combine all ingredients and toss with lo-cal dressing.

title: cheesy spinach bread
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1 cup Mozzarella cheese. Spread onto bread slices, 1 tablespoon per slice.
Sprinkle with remaining 1 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet; broil 4 to 6 inches from heat for 2 minutes.

title: ginger chicken balls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Pour broth and egg over crumbs.
Let stand until moistened.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Form into small balls; place on a greased baking sheet.
Bake 20 minutes.
Serve with picks and sauce for dipping.

title: ginger snaps
directions: Cream shortening, brown sugar, egg and molasses.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill one hour.
Shape into balls and roll in sugar.
Bake at 375 degrees for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: generic ice cream(makes 2 gallons)
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla together.
Add Milnot and beat well.
Pour into ice cream container.
Add milk and plug in freezer.

title: vegetable rice
directions: Slice onion and saute in butter.
Add mixed vegetables and stir a while.
Then add water, rice and salt.
Cook until rice is cooked.

title: party pizzas
directions: Fry meat separately. Drain and combine. Add cheese and spices. Spread on bread.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze.
After frozen, put in freezer containers. Bake frozen pizzas at 400° for 10 minutes.
Yields 60 pizzas.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Combine ingredients in a frypan.
Stir until boiling.
Can frost while cake is still hot.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Top with crushed cornflakes or crackers.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° or until golden brown on top.

title: old fashioned meat loaf
directions: Lightly mix the first 7
ingredients and form into a loaf.
Place in shallow pan and place in oven at 350°.
While it is starting to cook, mix
the remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil; pour over meat loaf and continue baking 1 1/2 hours.

title: green tomato casserole
directions: Place layer of tomatoes in lightly greased casserole dish. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Dot with butter. Add 1/3 of the cheese. Repeat layer 2 times. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes. Sprinkle cracker crumbs over top. Dot with additional butter. Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: fudgy bonbons
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a medium saucepan, combine chocolate chips and butter.
Cook and stir over very low heat until chips are melted and smooth.
Add sweetened condensed milk and mix well. Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup and level off.
In medium bowl, combine flour, nuts, chocolate mixture and vanilla.
Mix well.
Shape 1 tablespoon (use measuring spoon) of dough around each kiss, covering completely.

title: caramel corn
directions: Cook syrup, sugar and salt over medium heat for 5 minutes. Remove from heat; add baking soda, butter and vanilla.
Pour over popped corn; stir until all corn is well coated.
Preheat oven to 250° and bake for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: mom's banana pudding
directions: In double boiler, combine condensed milk with 1/2 to 3/4 can more water.
Mix 3 tablespoons of flour and sugar together.
Add water to make paste.
Add vanilla and egg yolks; mix well.
Cook on low until thick.
Put graham crackers in bottom of dish.
Slice bananas and add sauce.
Cover with crackers.

title: divine potato casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and pat into a 9x13-inch pan. Mix 4 tablespoons melted butter with corn flakes and spread over the top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 to 1-1/2 hours until potatoes are tender.

title: linguine with clams and broccoli
directions: Cook linguine according to package directions.
Add broccoli 3 minutes before linguine is done.
Drain, but reserve a little cooking water.
Drain clams; reserve liquid.
Saute garlic in oil until brown.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper until smooth.
Add clam liquid; cook, stirring until thick and bubbly.
Add clams; heat to serving temperature.
Place linguine in serving bowl. Pour on sauce and Parmesan cheese.
If mixture is too thick, add a little pasta water.

title: jello cake
directions: Bake cake by directions on box.
Take meat fork and make holes in the cake.
Mix Jell-O in hot water until dissolved.
Pour Jell-O over warm cake.
Put crushed pineapple on top of this.
Ice with Cool Whip.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: hot pepper butter
directions: Mix hot peppers in blender.
Put mustard, vinegar and sugar in pan.
Bring to boil.
Add peppers, water and flour to make thickening.
Boil until thick.
Fill pint jars and seal.
Makes 7 pints.

title: fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients except vanilla.
Bring to a boil; cook until, when dropped in cold water, it forms a ball.
Add vanilla. Remove from heat and beat until stiff.
Pour into glass pan.

title: chicken and crescent almondine
directions: Combine chicken, cream of chicken soup, water chestnuts, mushrooms, Miracle Whip, celery, onion and sour cream.
Cook over medium heat until bubbly.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Place crescent roll triangles over hot chicken mixture.
Combine cheese, almonds and melted butter and spread over dough.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until crust is golden brown.

title: lite fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender.
Blend until smooth. Chill and serve.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all together.
Use 3 teaspoons of mix for 1 cup.

title: veggie rice dish
directions: In a skillet, heat oil and brown the Rice-A-Roni. Add frozen veggies and 3 cups of water. Bring to boil, then simmer while covered. Stir frequently. When rice is fully cooked, add cheese and let melt. This is good with only meat.

title: chicken sopa
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove from bones, reserve broth. Melt oleo, add chilies and onion and cook until tender.
Add chicken, soups, chestnuts and one soup can of chicken broth.
Tear tortillas into eighths.
Layer in greased casserole tortillas, chicken mixture and cheese.
Repeat at least 3 layers.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Chop apples with peel on and mix with chopped onion, celery and seasonings.
Stuff chops and place in baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and sage.
Cover tightly and bake 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Remove cover and brown.

title: corn bread
directions: Stir to combine thoroughly first 5 ingredients.
Add eggs, milk and oil.
Beat just until smooth.
Bake in greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Slice eggplant, peel and place in ice water for 30 minutes (optional).
Beat egg and milk together.
Dip eggplant in mixture and then flour.
Brown eggplant slices in hot vegetable oil on both sides and place in baking dish one layer deep; spread pasta sauce over eggplant.
Repeat with second layer of eggplant, pasta sauce and sprinkle with cheese.
Place in hot oven just long enough to melt cheese.
Serves 4.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, flour, butter, vanilla and salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Blend in buttermilk.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Pie should be very browned.
This recipe makes enough for 2 pie shells (deep ones).

title: easy creamed vegetables
directions: In saucepan, cook vegetables in unsalted water until tender, drain.
Stir in soup.
Heat; stir often.
Thin to desired consistency with milk.
Makes about 3 1/2 cups.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all the vegetables and add spices to taste.
Mix in cheese cubes and macaroni.	Add mayonnaise.
Mix well with hands, so that all vegetables and cheese are well coated.	Chill and serve.
May garnish with bell pepper rings and sprinkle with paprika.

title: latkes(potato pancakes)
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl. Heat oil in covered pan. Place mixture in pan by spoonfuls; form a flat pancake.
Brown on each side and drain.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix chicken soup and vegetables together.
Pour in one pie shell and top with other.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening with two knives or pastry blender.
Mix in just enough milk to make soft dough, not too wet.
Turn out on lightly floured board.
Pat out to 1/2 to 3/4-inch thickness.
Cut with floured cutter.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet 15 to 20 minutes at 375° to 400°.
Serve hot with butter.
Yield:
12 to 16 biscuits.

title: herb chicken
directions: Duck:
Night before, wash ducks thoroughly and place in a glass dish.
Stuff each cavity with a celery stalk, 1/4 apple, 1/4 onion, a dash of poultry seasoning and a dash of thyme.
Rub outside with salt and seasoned pepper.
Pour (at least) a cup of your favorite wine over them, tightly cover, and let marinate overnight in the refrigerator.
Next morning, empty birds (save celery, etc.).
Stuff with sausage dressing and place in baking pan.
Pour all the marinade, including celery, apple, etc., over ducks and cook as you would a small baked hen (basting as you go) at 350°.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown meat in bacon drippings; add all other ingredients. Place in casserole dish, 9 x 13-inch.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: broccoli rice hot dish
directions: Prepare Minute rice according to package directions. Cook broccoli.
Mix rice and broccoli; put in a greased 9 x 12-inch casserole.
Saute onion and celery in butter.
Add milk and cheese to onion and celery; mix well.
Add chicken soup and water chestnuts.
Pour over broccoli.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: mom's ice cream mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Add enough milk to fill freezer container to 2/3 full. Refrigerate overnight. Add fruit right before freezing.

title: baked hush puppies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a medium bowl; make a well in center of mixture.
Combine onion and next 4 ingredients; add to dry ingredients, stirring until just moistened.
Spoon 1 tablespoon batter per hush puppy into miniature muffin pans or madeleine pans coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from pans immediately.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: potato pie
directions: Line bottom of baking dish with potatoes.
Add onions to top of potatoes, then add hamburger.
Next, add soup.
Do not dilute. Add cheese.
Cover and bake at 400° until potatoes are done and cheese is golden.
(Hamburger should be browned and drained.)

title: kristin's favorite oreo pie
directions: Crumble cookies (reserve 3 tablespoons for topping).
Mix Cool Whip and cream cheese until smooth.
Make pudding as directed from box.
Mix all together.
Pour into prepared pie crusts or dessert dish.

title: post-gazette brownies
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt chocolate squares, chocolate chips and butter together.
Allow to cool.
Cream together eggs and sugar; add vanilla.
Gradually add cooled chocolate mixture to creamed mixture.
Fold in flour, marshmallows and walnuts.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool.
Refrigerate several hours before cutting into squares.

title: bread sticks
directions: Melt butter and stir in all ingredients except cheese.
Blend well.
Dip cut side of buns in butter mixture.
Slice with electric knife into 3 sticks.
Place buttered side up on cookie sheets and sprinkle heavily with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 200° for 1 1/2 hours (will freeze).

title: sugar-free pineapple pie
directions: Stir mix into milk in medium saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
When mixture is hot, add the well drained pineapple.
Cook until it comes to full boil.
Cool.
Stir the cooling mixture two or three times.
Pour into baked pie shell or graham cracker crust.
Put in refrigerator.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: rice dressing supreme
directions: Heat chicken broth to the boiling point.
Season with 1 teaspoon of salt if not seasoned.
Add the rice and stir until it boils up once.
Lower flame, cover and steam 15 minutes.
Saute the onion and celery in margarine until clear; add mushroom and seasonings and combine the 2 mixtures.
Turn rice into casserole to be served hot.
Serves 8.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain and rinse.
Combine with remaining ingredients and mix well. Refrigerate.

title: cucumber and tomato salad
directions: Cut cucumbers and tomatoes into bite size pieces.
Put on a bed of leaf lettuce; top with the Italian dressing (prepared as on packet).
Last, put on a big handful of seasoned croutons.

title: sweet trash
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in a large container.
Break up the almond bark and melt at 15 second intervals in microwave. Stir each time.
Pour over other ingredients.
Stir gently.
Pour onto waxed paper covered cookie sheet.
When cool, break up (approximately 2 hours).

title: broccoli, cheese and rice side dish
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a casserole or oblong glass dish.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 45 minutes, then uncovered for 15 minutes.

title: chopped beef sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients except rolls.
Spread on rolls.

title: strawberry angel cake
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 1/4 cups boiling water.
Stir in thawed strawberries, sugar and salt.
Cool until it begins to thicken; fold in whipped cream.
Cover bottom of 9-inch pan with half of the torn angel food cake.
Pour half of mixture over cake.
Make another layer of cake and pour remaining mixture on it.
Put in refrigerator 4 to 5 hours.

title: bar-b-qued spareribs
directions: Mix ingredients together and coat ribs.
Bake at 375° for about 2 1/2 hours.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Slice zucchini thin and simmer in butter for 6 minutes.
Melt sour cream and Swiss cheese.
Add zucchini, butter and chives. Stir to coat.
Season well with salt and pepper.
Top with bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Heat 30 minutes in 375° oven.
Serve.

title: spritz cookies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Work flour in with hands.
Use a cookie press to form cookies.
Food coloring may be used to color cookie dough.
Bake at 400° for 7 to 10 minutes.
Do not brown.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: mama's pecan balls
directions: Finely chop 1/2 cup pecans and coarsely chop remaining 1/2 cup of pecans; set aside.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured pan(s). Bake in a preheated oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash; add onion and saute in margarine until tender. Add milk, cheese and Ro-Tel.
Stir.
Pour into greased casserole. Crumble Ritz crackers over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: spinach torte(vegetarian dish)
directions: Cook spinach and drain.
Combine remaining ingredients in a large bowl.
Spoon into a buttered tube pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: old-fashioned muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease twelve 2 1/2-inch muffin pan cups; set aside.
In medium bowl, combine dry ingredients; mix well.
Using pastry blender, cut in oleo and shortening until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Combine milk, vanilla and eggs. Add to dry ingredients all at once, stirring just until moistened. Do not overmix.
Spoon batter into prepared cups, filling each 3/4 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown. Immediately remove from pan to cooling rack.
Serve warm.
Makes one dozen.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix cake mix as instructed on box.
Mix 6 ounces cream cheese, 3 cups of the powdered sugar and 3/4 stick oleo (soften cream cheese and oleo in microwave).
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam. Layer pan with nuts, then coconut, then prepared cake mix.
Drop cream cheese mixture by spoonfuls in cake mixture, taking care not to touch sides.
Bake at 300° for 60 minutes.
When done, invert immediately, top down, to cool.
Nuts will now be topping.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Cook spinach.
Drain.
Combine eggs, cream cheese and Cheddar cheese.
Stir in spinach, almonds, green onions, parsley, salt and pepper.
Pour into shell.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Top with tomato and 1 tablespoon Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 4 minutes more.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: steamed beans
directions: Wash beans and cut in 1-inch lengths.
Bring water to a rolling boil, then turn fire off.
Put beans in water for 3 minutes.
Drain water and mix in bacon bits and your favorite dressing.

title: plum cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and oil and beat until creamy.
Blend in flour and spices.
Beat on medium speed 2 or 3 minutes.
Add plums and vanilla and mix thoroughly.
Bake in well-greased tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: crock-pot baked beans
directions: Drain beans.
Mix everything in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 6 to 7 hours.

title: low-fat potato bacon soup
directions: Cook onions and bacon until tender.
Stir in water and potatoes.
Boil.
Reduce heat.
Slightly mash a few potatoes. Stir in milk, seasoning and pepper to taste.

title: far east celery casserole
directions: Slice celery into 1-inch pieces.
Cook in small amount of boiling, salted water until crisp, about 8 minutes.
Drain.
Mix celery, water chestnuts (drained and thinly sliced), pimento and soup in 1-quart casserole.
Toss bread crumbs, almonds and butter. Sprinkle over celery mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: taglarinie(serves 12)
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and garlic in half of the oil. Saute meat in remaining oil (just until red is gone).
Combine onion and pepper, garlic, meat, chili powder and tomato sauce. Simmer 1 hour.
Cook noodles; wash and drain.
Add noodles, corn and mushrooms.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Push olives into mixture.
Top with grated cheese.
Heat in a 350° oven long enough to heat through and melt cheese.

title: brazil nut snowballs
directions: Cream butter, add sugar gradually and cream well.
Add
egg and vanilla and beat until fluffy.
Stir together flour and salt, cut into creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Shape into balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350 for 20 minutes.
Cool and roll in powdered sugar.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown hamburger and diced onion; add sauce with diced onion. Cook spaghetti 1/2 hour.
Put hamburger, sauce and onion mixture in a large bread pan.
Add layer of spaghetti, then sauce.
Top with cheese.
Repeat until pan is full.
Cook at 350° until done or cheese has melted.

title: quick and easy chocolate fudge
directions: Grease 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
In heavy saucepan, stir together corn syrup and milk.
Add chocolate pieces, stirring constantly.
Cook, over medium to low heat, until melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Add powdered sugar.
Beat until creamy smooth.
Stir in nuts, if wanted.
Turn into prepared pan.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes and cool.
Put in the refrigerator.
These will keep a week or longer.

title: amy's company casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain. Brown meat in 1 tablespoon butter. Stir in tomato sauce. Remove from heat. Combine cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream, onion and green pepper.

title: coconut pie(makes its own crust)
directions: Combine all ingredients in order and mix well. Pour into a well greased 10 inch pie pan and bake at 300° for 45-60 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pineapple garlic pork chops
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pork chops; mix well.
Place chops in shallow dish.
Pour in marinade.
Cover and refrigerate overnight, turning occasionally.
Remove chops from marinade and grill (or broil) over medium hot coals 5 to 6 minutes per side, turning and basting with marinade.
Discard marinade or boil for 2 to 3 minutes to use as sauce.

title: fruitcake(no sugar)
directions: Cook raisins in water until absorbed.
Cool.
Add applesauce, eggs, sweetener and oil.
Mix well.
Add dry ingredients and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: caramel icing
directions: Boil to 234°, then add 1 teaspoon vanilla and let cool. Beat to spreading consistency.

title: salmon with fresh basil sauce
directions: Rinse fillets under cold water; pat dry.
Cut fish into slices 1-inch thick.
Fry fillets in the oil in a skillet over high heat for 3 minutes.
Turn pieces over and sprinkle with the salt and pepper and lemon juice.
Cook on second side another 3 minutes. Remove pan from heat.

title: copper pennies pickled carrots
directions: Cut and boil carrots until tender, for about 5 minutes. Combine tomato soup, salad oil, sugar, vinegar, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper together.
Pour over carrots, pepper and onion.
Refrigerate.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice and parboil squash.
Drain.
Mix soup, sour cream, onion, carrot, salt and pepper with squash.
Mix dressing and melted butter. Place 3/4 of dressing in pan.
Put squash mixture on top.
Top with remaining dressing.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ono banana bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and mashed bananas. Combine flour, salt and baking soda and blend into banana mixture. Pour into two (1 pound) loaf pans and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: honey cheese pie
directions: Cream cheese; combine honey, eggs, lemon, salt and milk.
Add to cheese a little at a time; blend.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 325° and bake for 30 minutes.
Chill before serving. Makes 1 pie.

title: cocoa fudge candy
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Add milk and white corn syrup.
Cook to candy stage, then add oleo and nuts.
Pour onto a greased cookie sheet.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Pour into two loaf pans and bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until golden brown on top.
This is a very moist bread.

title: hamburger upside-down pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In a skillet, saute onion, pepper and beef in oil until brown.
Add tomato sauce and remaining ingredients; mix well.
Turn into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with cornbread topping (use box of Jiffy corn muffin mix, mixed as directed on box and use for topping).
Bake 25 minutes at 400°. Turn onto serving plate at once with topping side down.
Serves 6.

title: new england mussel chowder
directions: Rinse and debeard mussels.
Steam in large pot with 1 cup water until all shells are open (approximately 4 minutes).
Remove meats and chop in half.
Save 1 1/2 cups strained mussel broth. Saute salt pork in pot until partially rendered.
Add onions, saute until transparent.
Add flour and blend.
Add broth.
Stir and bring to boil.
Add potatoes.
Boil until done (10 minutes). Add mussel meats and cream.
Season to taste.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar. Beat in eggs. Add flour. Mix well. Add vanilla, apples and pecans. Bake in 2 (9-inch) pans or 13 x 9 pan in preheated 350° oven for approximately 40 minutes.

title: applesauce fruit cake(milk-free and egg-free)
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Beat the soda into the applesauce; add to shortening and sugar.
Add cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves, cocoa and salt.
Add flour slowly.
Add raisins.
If applesauce is thin, it takes more flour (4 cups); if thick, less. You can add other dried fruit if you like (prunes, apricots, cut in very small pieces).
If short on applesauce, a little water may be added and a little less soda (1 1/2 teaspoons).
Bake at about 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in oblong pan, or until done to touch.

title: roast honey chicken
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients in saucepan.
Heat until honey and chutney are warm.
Dip chicken in sauce until coated.
Place in shallow metal pan.
Bake in 400° oven for 1 hour.

title: coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour a square 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Mix sugar, shortening and egg thoroughly.
Stir in milk.
Blend dry ingredients and stir in.
Spread batter in pan. Sprinkle top with a mixture of 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Bake 25 to 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Makes 9 (3-inch) squares.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Wash zucchini; cut off stems.
Cut each in half lengthwise. Using the curved contour blade on the grapefruit knife, hollow out the zucchini halves, leaving 1/2-inch edge all around.
Cook zucchini in boiling, salted (1/2 teaspoon) water 5 minutes; drain. Saute garlic in hot butter.
Discard garlic; add onion and saute. Add tomato, rice, parsley, oregano, 1 teaspoon salt and the cayenne.
Toss with fork.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Salt inside of zucchini; fill with rice.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 15 minutes.
Brown under broiler.

title: breast of chicken with asparagus and carrots
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Cut chicken crosswise in 1/4 inch strips. Tear off 4 lengths of aluminum foil large enough to allow for heat circulation and expansion. Place chicken in center of lower half of each piece of foil; season with salt and pepper. Top with asparagus, carrot and onion. In a small bowl, combine margarine, lemon juice, tarragon, salt and cayenne pepper. Pour equally over each piece of chicken. Fold upper half of foil over ingredients, making a series of locked folds; repeat folds for ends, pressing tightly to seal. Place foil packets in a single layer on large cookie sheet. Cook 18-20 minutes, until chicken tests done. To serve, cut an "X" in top of packet. Fold back foil or remove to plate.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in long casserole dish. Bake at 350° until done.

title: saucy meatballs
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Shape into 20 meatballs.
Brown in shortening.
Drain.
Sprinkle flour over meatballs.
Stir gently to coat meatballs.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Combine cabbage and carrot.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Stir into cabbage mixture.
Chill.

title: hunter's chicken
directions: On waxed paper, combine flour, basil, garlic powder and pepper.
Coat chicken lightly in flour mixture.
Brown chicken, one-half at a time.
In same skillet, combine soup, tomatoes and carrots.
Heat to boiling; return chicken to skillet.
Reduce heat and cover.
Cook for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in zucchini.
Cover; cook for 10 minutes or until chicken is done.
To serve, arrange chicken over noodles.
Stir sauce and spoon over chicken.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: spring salad
directions: Dissolve jello (partially set).
Fold in rest of ingredients until mixed.
Fold in whipped cream.
Refrigerate.

title: rhubarb shortbread squares
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Set aside.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, butter, vanilla, eggs and milk.
Put half of the dough on bottom of 12 x 18-inch pan; spread sauce on.
Add remaining dough on top.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes until brown. Sprinkle powdered sugar on top.

title: honey dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients except oil.
While processing, slowly add oil.

title: red potatoes fried with onion and garlic
directions: Depending on how many you are cooking for, you can add or delete ingredients. (Serving size for 6.) Heat stovetop medium to medium-high. Pour oil into large frying pan. Place cut potatoes and onion into oil before it gets hot. Stir in pepper and garlic salt. Never leave cooking oil alone (EVER). Stirring and keeping a constant eye out, make sure to fry until golden brown or to taste.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: In a large skillet, cook and stir ground beef and onion in butter until onion is tender.
Stir in flour, salt, garlic salt and pepper; cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soup; simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
Stir in sour cream; heat through.
Serve over noodles.

title: onion crusted chicken
directions: Flatten the chicken breast pieces.
Season with salt and pepper.
Combine melted butter, dry mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Dip chicken pieces into mixture and then roll in crushed onion ring crumbs.
Place in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with remaining crumbs and drizzle on any leftover butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pancho's cheese dip
directions: Mix tomatoes, garlic, cumin and water; simmer 25 minutes. Divide grated cheese and mixture of liquid in half.
Mix 1/2 of liquid and 1/2 of grated cheese in blender, then second half. Reheat the entire mixture until well heated.

title: fruit tea
directions: Steep tea, then add remaining ingredients,
in order given, and add enough water to make 1 gallon.
Serve hot or cold.
Can be kept in refrigerator several days or up to 1 week.

title: great mammaw's ice pickle chips
directions: Bring vinegar solution to a full boil.
Pour over cucumber mixture.
Let pickles simmer only long enough to lose bright green color.
Place in hot jars and seal.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat together milk and eggs, toss with spaghetti and spread in a greased 11 x 18-inch pan.
Top with sauce, pepperoni and cheese.
Bake 40 minutes.
Let stand and cut into serving portions.

title: sirloin barbecue
directions: Cook 8 hours in crock-pot.
Pull apart.
Serve on buns.

title: gold rush brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease well on 8 x 8-inch baking pan. Put all ingredients in a mixing bowl and mix well.
Spread mixture in greased pan.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Cool and cut.

title: kim's baked beans
directions: Cook bacon strips; drain and crumble.
Brown ground beef; drain.
Add onion, molasses, ketchup, brown sugar and dry mustard. Stir ingredients together and heat through.
Add small portions to B & M baked beans.
Cover and bake 1 hour until piping hot at 325°. Larger portion, add entire mixture to 2 (3 pound) cans B & M baked beans.
Cover and bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until hot.
Stir occasionally.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add vanilla.
Beat eggs and add to mixture.
Sift flour, soda and baking powder together 2 or 3 times (or mix well together) and add to the creamed mixture in 2 to 3 additions.
If this mixture is too soft to form a roll with the hand, put on dough board, add flour and knead until you can form a roll.
Chill.
Cut in slices.
Place on baking sheet and bake at 350° for about 8 to 10 minutes.
Watch!

title: cheesy meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium mixing bowl; blend thoroughly.
Spread mixture evenly in glass loaf dish.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave at time cook (power level 7) Medium-high for 23 to 29 minutes or until center is no longer pink, rotating dish 1/2 turn after 12 minutes cooking time.
Let stand, covered 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: cocktail weiners
directions: Combine all
ingredients in heavy sauce pot, Simmer for 1 hour. Serve with crackers.

title: hot apple relish
directions: Put apples, onions and peppers in food processor and process until very finely chopped.
Add sugar and vinegar; boil until thickened.
Put in sterilized jars.
If you don't want it very hot, use less hot peppers.
Makes about 11 pints.

title: pico de gallo
directions: Chop tomatoes, onion, cilantro and jalapeno into small diced pieces.
Mix together in one bowl.
Add lemon, salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with fajitas!

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, sugar, salt, eggs, butter, milk and vanilla thoroughly and pour into a buttered casserole dish.

title: artichoke pie
directions: Thinly slice the artichoke hearts vertically and spread out on paper towels.
Pat dry when thawed and drizzle with lemon juice. Heat olive oil and butter in a 10-inch skillet with an ovenproof handle.
Coat artichoke heart slices with flour and brown on both sides in hot fat.
Beat eggs slightly.
Mix in salt, pepper and milk.
Pour over artichoke slices in skillet.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 10 minutes or until egg mixture is set.
Makes 4 servings.

title: turkey chip surprise
directions: Place the turkey with the chips on the bread and mash down hard.
Happy eating!

title: oven browned chicken(serves 100, 3 pieces each)
directions: Arrange half of the onion slices on bottoms of shallow baking pans.
Add chicken pieces.
(Do not pile on top of each other.) Top with remaining onions.
Combine flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
Sift over chicken and onions.
Pour on butter.
Bake in moderate oven at 375° for 1 hour or until brown and tender.
Serve with its onion and juice.

title: banana bran muffins
directions: Combine egg, brown sugar and oil. Add vanilla. Blend in dry ingredients. Mix in bananas and walnuts. Divide batter to make a dozen muffins. Spray muffin pan with Pam. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. Delicious - Can be frozen!

title: chicken cheese ball
directions: Mix together; form into ball.
Roll in chopped nuts.

title: reuben spread
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread in slow cooker. Mix well. Cover and cook on high 1-2 hours, stirring occasionally. Turn cooker on low to keep warm while serving. Spread on slices or bread.

title: party pound cake
directions: Cream butter, margarine, shortening, flavorings and 1/4 cup milk until well blended.
Add sugar and cream well; beat in one egg at a time.
Add dry ingredients alternately with remaining milk. Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: crescent roll coffee cake
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar, egg yolk, vanilla and lemon juice; set aside.
Spread 1 package of rolls in 9 x 13-inch pan. Lightly seal edges together.
Spread cream cheese mixture over this.
Lay second package of rolls on top.
Do not try to press edges together as you want mixture to bubble up while baking.

title: pasta with artichoke hearts
directions: Melt butter and oil.
Add flour and stir until smooth.
Blend in broth; stir until thickened.
Reduce heat to low and add garlic, parsley, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add artichokes, 2 tablespoons Parmesan and capers. Cover and simmer 8 to 10 minutes.
Toss with cooked pasta and garnish with an extra tablespoon of Parmesan.
Sauce freezes well! Serves 4.

title: scalloped oysters
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a 2-quart casserole or 6 to 8 individual casseroles.
Melt butter in a large skillet over medium heat.
Remove from heat; add flour and stir until smooth.
Return to heat and cook, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes or until light brown.
Add paprika, salt, pepper, cayenne, garlic, onion and green pepper.
Cook 3 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add oysters and their liquid, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce. Stir well.
Sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pinto beans
directions: Wash beans and place in pot with enough water to cover beans. Let them come to a boil. Turn off.
Let beans soak in pot for at least 6 hours. Add water to cover beans completely and let come to a boil.
Cook on low heat for 2 hours.
Add ham hock or salt pork, onion and garlic.
Let beans cook for 2 more hours.

title: sweet-sour green beans
directions: Cook beans according to package directions; drain.
Fry bacon; drain on paper towel.
Leaving about 3 tablespoons of grease in pan, saute onions until tender.
Add the dry mustard, vinegar and sugar, cooking until sugar dissolves.
Pour sauce over beans. Bake in a covered casserole dish for 30 minutes in a 350° preheated oven.
Makes 6 servings.

title: potato delight
directions: Defrost potatoes 30 minutes.
Mix together all other ingredients.
Put in casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: christmas candy
directions: Combine
sugar,
butter and milk.
Cook to 238° on candy thermometer
(soft	ball),	then stir in one jar of Marshmallow Creme and
beat until mixture is very thick and creamy (about 8 minutes).
Add
remaining ingredients and beat well.
Pour onto greased (Pam sprayed) platter and let sit until firm.
Cut with very
sharp, warm knife into bite size pieces.
Makes about 100 pieces.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cut up dates, candy and nuts with flour. Cream together butter, sugar and eggs. Add 1 cup buttermilk. Add soda to other 1/2 cup buttermilk, then add to creamed mixture. Add flour mixture and mix well. Bake in tube pan at 275° for 3 hours.

title: chocolate chip cheese cake
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, sugar and margarine. Press in bottom of pie pan to form a crust. Mix cream cheese and sugar. Mix well with mixer until well blended. Add eggs one at a time, mixing well after each. Blend in chocolate chips and vanilla. Pour into crust. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 250° and bake 35 minutes more. Chill well before serving.

title: cake-on-a-string
directions: Give each child a threaded needle.
The children then string such things as chunks of raw apple, prunes, raisins, pineapple chunks, walnut halves or anything else you can think of.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into balls and roll in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Beat all ingredients together except shrimp.
Add shrimp last and mix in by hand.
Refrigerate.

title: tangy meatballs(microwave)
directions: Combine crumbs, milk, salt, onion and curry.
Mix lightly. Add beef; blend thoroughly.
Shape mixture into 36 one-inch balls. Arrange half the balls into a double circle on a round micro-proof plate.
Cover with waxed paper.
Use Cook cycle and cook 6 to 8 minutes or until beef is no longer red, rotating dish once during cooking time.
Repeat with remaining meatballs.
Serve on toothpicks.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Combine and when ready to serve, add 1 pint of cream, whipped stiff.

title: white chocolate fudge
directions: Cook sugar, butter and 2/3 cup Carnation milk together. Bring to boil. Boil 5 minutes; take off heat. Stir in rest of ingredients. Pour into pans.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans.
Mix soup into beans in quart size casserole. Heat at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with onion rings until toasted. Makes 10 servings, approximately.

title: fruit kabobs and fruit dip
directions: Put fruit on wooden skewers.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Make jello; chill until almost firm.
Add the remaining ingredients; chill until firm.

title: savory pork soup
directions: Cut pork into 1-inch cubes.
Dredge cubes in flour and brown in oil in large skillet.
Add onion and cook for one minute, stirring constantly.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to boil and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: pink lady congealed fruit salad
directions: Make ahead and refrigerate. Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup hot liquid; cool. Add fruit, marshmallows and nuts. Add Cool Whip to mayonnaise. Fold into Jell-O mixture. Chill in ungreased container. Unmold on lettuce for decoration.
Serves 12.

title: cinnamon crisps
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg yolk.
Add dry ingredients.
Spread in a jelly roll pan (10 x 15-inch).
Brush slightly beaten egg white over dough.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Press into dough and bake at 350°.
Cut into triangles while still hot.

title: reese's peanut butter cups
directions: Melt Hershey's and add little peanut butter to taste.
Cut cupcake papers in half.
Drop 1 tablespoon chocolate; let set. Drop 1 tablespoon peanut butter; let set.
Drop 1 tablespoon chocolate; let set.

title: mother's good bread pudding
directions: Cut soft bread into slices and break into crumbs.
Pour over them scalded milk and the melted butter.
Let stand 5 minutes. Beat egg yolks; add 3 tablespoons sugar, vanilla and salt. Combine with bread mixture and turn into baking pan.
Set in pan of hot water in slow oven and bake 45 minutes or until custard is firm.
Cool.
Spread with a layer of jelly and cover with the stiffly beaten egg whites to which 2 tablespoons of sugar has been added.
Brown in oven and serve hot or cold.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Beat egg whites, salt and baking powder until stiff.
Add sugar.
Fold in pecans and cracker crumbs.
Bake in buttered pan at 325° for 30 minutes.
Fill with 1 quart strawberries.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat 3 eggs thoroughly with 2/3 cup sugar, dash of salt, 1 cup dark corn syrup and 1/3 cup butter or margarine, melted.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla flavor.
Add 1 cup pecan halves.
Pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain beans thoroughly.
Pour into large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill several hours or overnight.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: baked dip
directions: Blend cheese and milk.
Stir in beef, onion and green pepper; mix well.
Add sour cream.
Spoon into small baking dish. Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Serve with crackers.

title: ambrosia chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small mixing bowl, stir together flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and egg.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Add Ambrosia semi-sweet chocolate chips.
Mix well.
Roll a heaping tablespoon of dough into a ball.
Place each ball 2 inches apart on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in preheated oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove baking sheet from oven and place cookies on cooling rack.
Makes approximately 3 dozen cookies.

title: quickie jello salad
directions: Mix jello and applesauce; heat.
Let cool and add Sprite. Chill until congealed.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: low-fat cool-easy pie
directions: Stir into large bowl the boiling water and Jell-O for 2 minutes or until completely dissolved. Mix cold water and ice to measure 1 cup. Add to Jell-O, stirring until ice is melted. Stir in Cool Whip until smooth. Refrigerate 15 to 20 minutes or until thick. Spoon into crust. Refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.

title: veal scaloppini
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl and pour into 2 quart casserole dish. Bake covered at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until bubbly.

title: chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Place marshmallows in the bottom of a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine sugar, cocoa and hot water.
Pour over marshmallows. Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Pour over marshmallow mixture.
Top with nuts.
Bake in oven at 350° for 50 minutes. Cool in pan on a rack for 10 minutes.
Turn out onto tray.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together; chill.
Serve with fresh fruits.

title: cinnamon-chocolate strips
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat 1 1/3 cups sugar, margarine, vanilla and eggs in a large bowl.
Stir in flour and baking soda.
Stir in chocolate morsels.

title: fruit shimmer
directions: Combine, shake or blend all ingredients add crushed ice. Makes 1 serving.

title: grandma's german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water; cool.
Cream butter and sugar together; add egg yolks one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add vanilla and melted chocolate and mix until blended. Sift flour with soda and salt and add alternately with buttermilk.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and pour batter into 3 greased and floured 8-inch pans and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Mix Pet milk, sugar, egg yolks, margarine and vanilla; cook and stir over medium heat 12 minutes, until mixture thickens. Cool and add coconut and pecans and stir.
Cover top and sides of cooled cake.

title: easy potato soup
directions: In a large soup pot, combine the celery, onion, potatoes, water, butter, salt and black pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce the heat to medium-high and cook until the potatoes are fork tender, not mushy.
In a small bowl, combine the flour with 1/2 cup milk.
Whisk until smooth.
Add to the soup mixture and stir. Add the remaining milk.
Taste and adjust the seasonings, if needed. Keep warm until time to serve.
Makes about 2 qts.

title: easy fruit cake
directions: Grease loaf pan well.
Line with foil.
Grease inside of foil in pan.
Mix ingredients well.
Place in pan and press down firmly until packed. Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Cool completely in pan. Improves with age.

title: pan-fried scallops
directions: Mix bread crumbs, salt, pepper and paprika.
Roll scallops thoroughly in bread crumb mixture.

title: special k bars
directions: Melt together first 3 ingredients.
Do not boil.
Remove from heat and add cereal.
Stir until well mixed.
Spread on buttered cookie sheet to cool.

title: queso(mexican cheese dip)
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften at room temperature.
Mix together all ingredients to blend.
Serve this as a dip for corn chips or raw vegetables.

title: apple raisin muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin pan. In a large bowl, beat oil and sugar with electric mixer for 2 minutes. Add eggs and vanilla. Beat 1 minute.
In another bowl, stir together flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt. Add dry ingredients to oil mixture. Stir just to combine. Stir in apples, raisins and walnuts.
Spoon batter into prepared muffin cups.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until tester comes out clean. Remove muffin tin to wire rack.
Cool 5 minutes and remove from pan. Finish cooling on rack. Freezes well.

title: swiss ham and vegetables
directions: Melt butter; add flour, salt, pepper, sugar and onion. Gradually stir in sour cream.
Cook and drain beans; add sauce and ham.
Put in buttered casserole; top with cheese.
Melt butter and add cornflakes.
Mix well and pour over cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: spinach salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Will keep in refrigerator for a couple of weeks.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs with flour; add salt and flavorings.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 300° for 1 hour.

title: squash pickles
directions: Put squash and onion in bowl.
Sprinkle with salt and let stand for 1 hour.
Drain any liquid.
Mix vinegar, sugar, celery seed, mustard seed and bell pepper in saucepan and let it come to a boil.
Add squash and onion to vinegar mixture.
Place in hot jars and seal.

title: jiffy raisin relish
directions: Combine raisins, onion and chili powder.
Heat chili sauce and water to boiling; pour over raisin mixture and let stand an hour or longer.
Makes 3 cups.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Roast pecans in oven at 300° for about 15 minutes.
Mix all ingredients together and add chopped pecans.
Freeze in 4 or 5-quart freezer.

title: white jello
directions: Mix Knox gelatine in cold water; set aside.
Boil crushed pineapple with sugar.
Set aside.
Cream cream cheese with Marshmallow Creme.
Set aside.
Put gelatine and pineapple together; bring to a boil, then add to cheese and Marshmallow Creme mixture.
Beat at low speed.
Put in refrigerator until it sets, then add Cool Whip.
Beat until all mixed.
Put in a dish and refrigerate.
If you want, sprinkle with nuts and cherries. It looks nice.

title: chili-on-cornbread
directions: Pour
cornbread batter into skillet or on a griddle and make pancake or fritter like fried cornbread.
Place cornbread on plate.
Top
with chili, shredded cheese, lettuce, chopped onions and olives.

title: eggnog bread
directions: Mix together the flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and nutmeg. In separate bowl, beat together the eggs, half and half, oil, almond extract, brandy extract and vanilla.
Stir ingredients; mix well.
Fold in cherries and nuts.
Pour into 2 greased pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: minestrone
directions: Combine all ingredients in large pot.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes or until all vegetables are tender.
Add water to keep ingredients covered when necessary. Yields 12 cups.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all together. Pour into 9 x 13 baking pan. Bake 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mint drops
directions: Combine confectioners sugar, cream cheese and flavoring in a bowl.
Mix well. Roll on flat surface and cut into desired shapes. Chill in refrigerator.
Yields 24 servings.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix well and pour into unbaked 9-inch pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Turn oven to 350° and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: jello delight
directions: Combine and refrigerate 10 minutes.
Ready to eat.

title: beef with snow peas
directions: Mix together sugar, m.s.g., cornstarch, soy sauce and water. Set aside.

title: taco soup
directions: Mix all the ingredients and cook to a boil, then simmer for a few minutes.
Serve over Tostitos and grated cheese.

title: easy hors d'oeuvre
directions: Spread cream cheese thinly on tortilla.
Place single layer of meat on cream cheese.
Roll up tortilla and cut into bite-size pieces.
Arrange around a bowl of salsa for dipping.

title: meat turnovers
directions: Brown beef, onion and garlic over medium-high heat.
When meat is brown and onion is soft, drain and discard fat from skillet. Add remaining ingredients (except rolls) to skillet.
Simmer 7 to 10 minutes or until liquid has evaporated.
Remove from heat. Heat oven to 375°.
Unroll crescent rolls into 4 rectangular sections.
Pinch together the center diagonal perforations of each rectangle.
Roll out rectangles (between sheets of waxed paper) until they are very thin, about 6 x 10-inches.
Place two of the rectangles on lightly greased baking sheets; spread each with half the meat mixture and top with the remaining rectangles.
Seal turnovers by pressing all edges with a fork.
Make 3 slashes in top rust.
Bake 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: best ever cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan (or spray with Pam).
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into strips.
Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Coat meat strips with flour mixture.
In skillet, cook meat in hot oil until browned on all sides.
Drain tomatoes, reserving liquid.
Add tomato liquid, water, onion and garlic to meat in skillet.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour or until meat is tender. Uncover and stir in tomatoes and green peppers.
Simmer for 7 to 8 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: parmesan crescents
directions: Mix baking mix and water until soft dough forms; beat vigorously for 30 seconds. Turn onto surface well floured with baking mix. Gently roll in baking mix to coat; shape into ball. Knead 10 times. Roll or pat into 12-inch circle. Spread with margarine and sprinkle with cheese. Cut into 12 wedges. Roll up, beginning at rounded edge. Place rolls with points underneath on baking sheet; curve slightly. Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: to-die for chocolate-pecan pie
directions: Beat margarine, sugar, Pet milk, eggs, cocoa, vanilla and salt in mixing bowl at low speed. Stir in coconut and pecans. Divide the filling evenly among the 3 pie shells. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Fry bacon crisp, drain and crumble; set aside.
Wash and cut broccoli and cauliflower into bite-size pieces.
Chop onion. Layer vegetables and bacon in an airtight container.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar.
Spread mixture over salad.
Seal container. Refrigerate overnight.
Mix well before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: barbara's strawberry soup
directions: Put first 4 ingredients through the blender, then put in a saucepan.
Add the sugar.
Cook over low heat 10 minutes.
Do not boil.
Add cream.
Chill.
Garnish with fresh berries.
Sinful!

title: panakokken
directions: Mix eggs, flour and milk.
Melt butter in pan, then pour mix in it.
Do not stir after putting in pan.
Preheat oven to 425°. Bake for 20 minutes or until done.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a mixing bowl. Beat well until smooth and creamy.

title: sausage surprise
directions: Cut sausage and potatoes or apples into bite-sized pieces. Heat skillet on low-medium heat. Heat oil. Add sausage and onions, cooking and stirring until onions are clear. Remove.
Add potatoes or apples. May be necessary to add more oil. If you use potatoes, salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and cook until almost tender/done, stirring occasionally. Add sausage and onions, stirring until done.

title: dill dip
directions: Cream sour cream and mayonnaise and add flavorings.
Let stand as long as possible to allow flavors to set.
Serve with chips or raw vegetables.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt together oleo,
peanut butter and chocolate chips. Pour over
Crispix
cereal
and stir to coat each piece.
Put powdered sugar
in a bag.
Dump cereal in and shake until all pieces
are coated.
Pour
in a shallow pan and let set after separating.

title: potato pizza bake
directions: Brown beef.
Place potatoes and onion in a large buttered baking dish; add meat.
Mix cheese soup with milk until smooth. Add this to meat and potatoes, mixing together. Combine tomato sauce, salt, pepper, oregano and sugar.
Pour over top; dot with butter.
Cover and bake at 375° for at least 1 1/2 hours.
Remove cover and arrange sliced cheese on top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Return to oven, uncovered, for about 15 minutes until cheese is bubbly.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients, except wings; stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Pour over wings; marinate for 48 hours.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°, uncovered.
Use cookie sheet covered with aluminum foil to bake wings.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in greased baking dish. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: cheesy scalloped potatoes
directions: Blend soup, milk and pepper.
In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, arrange potatoes, onion, sauce and cheese in layers.
Dot top with butter; sprinkle with paprika.
Cover.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour. Uncover; bake 15 minutes more, or until done.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together all but cheese and spread in 10 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Top with cheese.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Add all of this to the cooked and drained spaghetti.
Add Salad Supreme seasoning mix to taste.
Add 1 (16 ounce) Italian dressing. Refrigerate overnight.

title: apple cinnamon muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients in large bowl.
Mix milk, apple juice concentrate, egg whites and oil in a bowl or blender.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
Add the chopped apples.
Line muffin pans with paper baking cups and fill with batter.
Bake in a 425° oven for 17 minutes.
Cool and freeze.
Remove muffins from freezer and heat in microwave as needed.
Makes about 30 muffins.

title: french toast
directions: Remove bread from package and let dry for a few minutes so that it won't be too soft.
Blend remaining ingredients for a few seconds in a blender.
Dip bread into egg mixture and brown on a hot griddle (which has been greased with margarine).

title: colossal cheeseburger
directions: Slice off top of bread and hollow out, leaving about 1 inch all around.
Combine all ingredients except cheese; fill bread shell.
Wrap in foil; bake at 375 degrees for one and half hours. Remove foil and top with cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems and chop up.
Preheat to 350°.
Melt margarine and saute onions, add chopped stems and continue sauteing.
Then add bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese. Mix well, remove from heat and put mixture into mushroom caps.
Add water to cover bottom of cookie sheet.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in 350° oven on jelly roll pan for 25 minutes or in 9 x 13-inch pan for 35 minutes.

title: shrimp and sausage jambalaya
directions: In a 4-quart heavy pot, saute sausage until firm and remove with slotted spoon.
Add olive oil to drippings and saute green pepper, garlic, parsley and celery for 5 minutes.
Chop tomatoes and reserve the liquid.
Add tomatoes, tomato liquid, chicken broth and green onions to the pot.
Stir in all spices.
Add the rice which has been washed and rinsed three times.
Add sausage and cook 30 minutes, covered over low heat.
Stir occasionally so rice does not stick.
After mot of the liquid has cooked out, add shrimp and cook until they are pink.
Transfer mixture to casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: drop doughnuts
directions: Fill crust with ground raisins, apple, green tomatoes and top with 1 cup sugar, cinnamon and butter.
Cover with lattice crust.

title: harmony punch
directions: Dissolve sugar and jello in water.
Do not boil.
Add all other ingredients except 7-Up.
Freeze in plastic ice cream bucket until ready for use.
Partially thaw, place in punch bowl and add 7-Up.

title: lemon delight
directions: Mix Eagle Brand and lemonade together.
Stir in whipping cream (do not whip) and then Cool Whip.
Fold in pineapple and mix all together.
Add cake that has been broken into bite size pieces. Pour into a large dish and refrigerate for several hours.
Cut into squares.

title: pan layered salad
directions: Line pan with bite size pieces of lettuce.
Add onions.
Add celery.
Add green pepper.
Add frozen peas.
Place in 3 spots the mayonnaise and spread carefully to seal.
Add cheese.
Add crumbled bacon.
Make early in day, or the night before serving. Refrigerate.
Stays crisp for several days.

title: couscous salad
directions: Chop cucumber and tomato. Slice carrot. In a medium bowl, combine cucumber, tomato, carrot, uncooked couscous, onion and olives. Pour salad dressing over the vegetables. Cover and chill for 1 - 1 1/2 hours. To serve, spoon vegetable mixture into lettuce lined bowls. Serves 6.

title: grandma's dishpan cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Mix cake mixes together in a large bowl.
Add spices.
Stir in raisins, nuts and chocolate chips; blend in well.
Fully line a dishpan with wax paper.
Pour cake mix into prepared dishpan.
Cover top of cake mix with wax paper (to prevent cake from burning).
Bake in a 350° oven 4 hours or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool completely in pan before pouring it out.

title: buckeye candy
directions: Mix butter, peanut butter and confectioners sugar.
Roll into balls.
In a double boiler, melt wax and chocolate bits.
Place toothpicks in center of ball and dip into chocolate mixture.
Cool on wax paper.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and peanut butter.
Add eggs.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Sometimes use more flour to handle the mix better.
Roll small amount in hand and pat down with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cheese tempters
directions: Let margarine soften.
Add cheese, salt and cayenne; mix well. Add flour; shape into 3 rolls, 1 1/2 inches.
Chill well.
Cut in 1/8-inch slices. Bake on ungreased pan at 350° until light tan.

title: chili burgers
directions: Place all ingredients in saucepan; stirring constantly.
Cook until well done.
If ground chuck is used, add small amounts of water during cooking.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: blueberry corn muffins
directions: Grease 24 (2 1/2-inch) muffin cups or line with paper bake cups. Combine all dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
In a small bowl, combine eggs, butter and buttermilk. Stir egg mixture into dry ingredients gently until just mixed.
Gently fold in blueberries.
Fill muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake in a 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden and firm.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: chess pie
directions: Blend eggs and sugar with 1 stick butter. Add vinegar and vanilla. Sprinkle cornmeal on bottom of 9-inch unbaked pie shell and pour in the egg mixture into pie shell. Bake 40 minutes at 325°.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients in a medium size bowl.
Grease pan with cooking oil, sides included.
Pour in mixture and cook for about 30 minutes at 350°.

title: 6 week raisin bran muffins
directions: In large bowl mix all dry ingredients.
Add milk, beaten eggs, oil and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Keep refrigerated.
Bake as needed at 400°.

title: holiday eggnog
directions: Pour everything except the quart of milk into a blender and set at high speed.
When everything is all frothy, pour it into the punch bowl and mix in the quart of milk.
Now sprinkle on nutmeg.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Use a package of refrigerator crescents.
Cut each triangle of dough into two smaller triangles.
Roll up and bake as directed. Makes 16 small crescents.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: coleslaw
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Adjust vinegar, sugar and pepper to taste.
Chill.
Serve cold.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast cake in cold water. Melt Crisco in boiling water. Add sugar and salt. Stir together well until all dissolved. Let cool to lukewarm. Add yeast water mixture. Add flour. You now have a soft dough. Put in greased bowl and refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine
all ingredients; heat through.
This sauce can be used as a barbecue sauce on any meat about 15 to 20 minutes before the meat is done.

title: butterfinger ice cream
directions: Beat half and half, eggs, sugar, vanilla and salt until well mixed.
Pour mixture into ice cream freezer.
Add Butterfingers and add enough milk to reach the fill line on the freezer.
Freeze according to manufacturer's directions.

title: low calorie spaghetti and meat balls
directions: Spray a
x
13-inch
roasting
pan with cooking spray. Shape meat
in 20 small meat balls.
Arrange in single layer and broil
or bake uncovered in preheated very hot oven, about 10 minutes until browned and rendered of fat.	Drain and discard fat. Stir
water
into	meat
balls.
Break
uncooked spaghetti into 4 inch
lengths and stir into pan, making sure there are
no clumps.
Add
remaining
ingredients,
place in preheated 425° oven and bake uncovered 25 to 30 minutes.
Stir several times while
baking.
Spaghetti
is done when most of liquid has evaporated and spaghetti and meat balls are tender and coated with
thick sauce.	Makes 4 servings, contains 295 calories each.

title: baked vidalia onions
directions: Wash and quarter onions to desired size.
Place onions in oblong baking dish with lid.
Add about 1/2-inch water in dish. Sprinkle onions with garlic salt.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: blackberry dumplings
directions: Mix water, sugar and butter and bring to a boil.
Set aside. Roll out each biscuit in a small amount of flour into the size of a small circle. Put blackberries in each circle and bring edges together, pinching to hold them together.
Do not seal edges completely.
Place in baking dish and pour sugar water over all. Bake at 375° until biscuits are brown.
Baste syrup over biscuits when done.
Extra blackberries can be put in syrup before baking.

title: easy stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and take off stems and put them aside.
Chop the stems and brown them in melted margarine in skillet.
Slowly add Parmesan cheese; stir and add bread crumbs, parsley, garlic powder and pepper until mixture is almost dry.
Stuff into mushroom caps and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Top with cheese, if you like.

title: almond float
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup of the water.
In saucepan, bring remaining 4 cups of water to a boil.
Stir in gelatin mixture. Lower heat and add milk and sugar; heat to just below boiling point.
Remove from heat.
Stir in almond extract.
Pour into two (9-inch) square pans.
Refrigerate until set.
Cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Serve with fruit mixed with gelatin.
Use at least 3 cans of any of the following: fruit cocktail, pineapple tidbits, peach halves, mandarin oranges, lychee and/or maraschino cherries.

title: black bean salad
directions: Sort and wash beans; place them in a large saucepan.
Cover with water 2 inches above beans; let soak at least 8 hours.
Drain beans and cover with fresh water; cook 1 hour or until tender. Drain well and let beans cool.
Combine beans, corn, green pepper, red pepper, jalapeno pepper, green onions and parsley in a large bowl.
Add olive oil, lime juice, salt and pepper; stir gently to combine.
Serve on lettuce leaves, if desired.
Serves 6.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken and save broth.
Pam bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover bottom of pan with flour tortillas.
Layer chicken, then onion and then cheese.
Layer chicken, onion and cheese until all used.
Mix soup and broth in separate bowl and pour on top.
Cover with flour tortillas and add Ro-Tel tomatoes on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli; put into greased pan.
Mix mayonnaise, egg, soup and onion.
Pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese.
Mix melted butter and stuffing and layer on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: no-cook play dough
directions: Mix together dry tempera colors with either liquid detergent or liquid starch and use as finger paint.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Mix milk with instant pudding.
Mix in oranges and pineapple. Fold in Cool Whip.
Fold in cookies.
Chill well.

title: maxines apple salad
directions: Sift flour and sugar together.
Mix in cream and pineapple. Cook in double boiler or heavy saucepan until thick.
Remove from fire and add oleo and cool.
Pour over diced apples and nuts. Dressing may be made in advance and refrigerated.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Pour soup and wine over chicken and cheese.
Put stuffing on top; drizzle 1 stick of butter or margarine on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is done.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well, then add eggs one at a time.
Mix well.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheesy pork chops and potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spoon cheese spread into 8 x 12-inch baking dish; place in oven just until cheese melts, 5 minutes.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Put oranges in blender and mix well. Add all ingredients and mix with mixer. Bake in pan that has been greased and floured at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Put all ingredients in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cajun stuffed round steak
directions: Place crumbs in bowl.
Combine in blender the onion, pepper, parsley and garlic.
Add milk, egg, ketchup and 1 tablespoon Worcestershire sauce.
Pour mixture over crackers.
Stir in salt, allspice, black pepper and red pepper.
Add hamburger; mix well. Remove bone from steak and trim off any fat.
Pound until very thin.
Sprinkle meat with salt, black pepper and red pepper. Place hamburger mixture on steak; roll up from large end down and tie with string.
Place steak seam side down in large casserole dish.
Combine soup mix, mushroom soup and 1 tablespoon Worcestershire sauce; pour over all.

title: salmon broiled
directions: Line baking dish with foil.
Place celery and onion on foil. Lay salmon on top of vegetables.
Pour white wine over salmon. Sprinkle paprika, salt and pepper on salmon.
Broil for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: choco mint candy
directions: Melt one pound almond bark and chocolate chips together.
Pour half of mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Let stand for 20 minutes.
Melt half pound almond bark.
Add flavoring, food coloring and milk.
Pour over first layer and let stand until firm.
Then pour remaining chocolate mixture over top and let set.

title: egg nog pie
directions: Soften 2 envelopes of unflavored gelatin in 2 cups of egg nog in top of double boiler.
Add 1/4 cup sugar and place over boiling water.
Stir until the sugar and gelatin are thoroughly dissolved. Then add 2 more cups of egg nog, nutmeg and rum or rum flavoring. Chill until consistency of unbeaten egg white.
Whip until light and fluffy.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix sugars, peanut butter, shortening, margarine and egg. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat oven to 375°. Shape dough into 1 1/4-inch balls. Place about 3-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten in crisscross pattern with fork dipped in flour.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes.
Cool before removal of cookies off cookie sheet.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat together the salad oil, sugar and eggs until creamy. Sift dry ingredients together.
Add slowly to the batter.
Add vanilla.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Batter will be stiff.
Bake in a tube pan (I line pan) for 1 hour at 350°.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix dressing with oil and vinegar according to package (in cruet).

title: moms beer mop
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan. Heat the mop and use it warm.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Mix together and grill or broil.
Makes 25 burgers.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Blend in flour and cheese.
Add milk and cook, stirring, until boiling.
Stir in broccoli.
Place in 1-quart casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs.

title: corn chowder(heart healthy)
directions: This pureed corn lends the soup its thick and silky texture. Use fresh corn in season; substitute frozen corn only when fresh isn't available.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and remove stems.
Brown onion and garlic in olive oil.
Finely chop mushroom stems and saute with onions and garlic.

title: mock kahlua
directions: Mix sugar, water and instant coffee.
Simmer for 30 minutes, then cool.
Add vodka and vanilla.
Bottle in 1/2 gallon container.
Can be used right away.

title: drop cookies
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Drop on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix ingredients and store in covered container.
Use 1 rounded teaspoonful mix for each cup of boiling water.

title: sour cream raisin bars
directions: Mix like pie crust.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups for top.
Press the rest into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream together the first 4 ingredients.
Add, alternating with next 4 ingredients.
The next 3 ingredients are the filling.
Pour half batter and half filling, then add remaining batter and filling.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar after baking.
Bake in well-greased angel food cake pan.
Great served hot or cold.

title: apea cake(breakfast)
directions: Mix the ingredients together and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Roll out sugar cookie dough to fit pizza pan (or press it into the pan) and bake by directions until chewy.
Do not overbake. Mix softened cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Or you can use flavored soft-spread cream cheese right from the container. Spread over cookie pizza.
Arrange fruit on top in geometric designs.
Cut like pizza pieces.

title: kentucky pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar; add eggs and butter.
Then add chips and nuts.
Fold in vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30-35 minutes, or until crust looks done.
Let pie set 4 hours before slicing.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook tomatoes and garlic together and then strain.
Cut onions and pepper together and cook in 1 pint of oil for 1/2 hour or until soft.
Then put through strainer and add this juice to tomato juice.
Add tomato paste, sugar, salt, sweet basil and oregano.
Cook until thick, then put in jars.

title: lime pineapple mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Stir in remaining ingredients and pour into 1-quart mold.
Chill until firm.
Makes 8 servings.
Serve with yogurt instead of whipped cream for less calories and fat.

title: buttermilk chess pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Add eggs and buttermilk, stirring until blended.
Stir in oleo and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.
Cool.

title: wedding punch
directions: Cut orange slices in half.
Line bottom of a 6 1/2-cup ring mold with half of orange slices and cherries.
Pour in a thin layer of ginger ale and freeze until firm. Arrange remaining orange slices and cherries alongside of ring mold and pour in another thin layer of ginger ale. Freeze until firm.
Pour in remainder of bottle of ginger ale and freeze until firm.

title: mrs. harriett's asparagus casserole
directions: Heat soup, milk, butter, pimento and juice of asparagus in a heavy boiler until well blended.
Grease casserole bowl; cover bottom with Ritz crackers; add layer of asparagus, boiled eggs, grated cheese and layer of sauce.
Repeat and put cheese on top (can also crumble up some cracker crumbs on top).
Bake at 350° until bubbling.

(You can melt 2 or 3 tablespoons butter; add 2 or 3 tablespoons flour to thicken and then add milk and asparagus juice to the consistency of a thick soup and use in place of the mushroom soup, butter, milk and asparagus juice.
It is quite good this way, also.)
I never really liked asparagus until I ate this casserole.
Delicious!

title: cheesy pasta primavera
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions in unsalted water.
Meanwhile, in a large skillet, heat butter.
Add bell pepper; cook and stir occasionally until barely tender.
Add squash and mushrooms.
Cook and stir occasionally, until barely tender, about 4 minutes.
Drain pasta; toss with vegetables in skillet.
Cover and keep warm.

title: cheese-bacon rolls
directions: Put cheese, bacon and onion through food grinder.
Mix other ingredients.
Shape in 5 rolls, 12 inches long and 1/2-inch wide. Cut each roll into 3 pieces.
Roll in crepe and chill.
Just before serving, place in broiler pan; brush with butter.
Broil at 4 inches until hot and bubbly (3 minutes).
Turn occasionally. Cut each crosswise in 4 pieces.
Spear with toothpicks.

title: gingerbread man recipe
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar; add molasses and blend.
In a separate bowl, blend all other ingredients and then combine with butter mixture.
Cover dough and chill until firm.
Roll out chilled dough on a floured surface.
Cut out gingerbread man shapes with cookie cutter.
Place on buttered cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
After cooked, decorate and ice.

title: pineapple carrot cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot and spicy sauce
directions: In a saucepan heat the oil.
Add the onion, garlic and ginger root.
Cook until soft.
Add spices.
Cool 1 minute.
Stir in vinegar, ketchup, brown sugar, hot sauce and mustard.
Simmer 4 to 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Add egg yolks, salt, milk and butter; cream together.
Add vanilla.
Bake in uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 50 minutes, then at 350° for 10 more minutes.

title: cream cheese casserole
directions: Spray 9-inch cooking dish with Pam.
Place 1 roll of crescent rolls in bottom of dish.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, lemon juice and vanilla together.
Spread evenly over rolls.
Top with other package of crescent rolls.
Brush rolls with the egg yolk.
Cook at 400° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Glaze with confectioners sugar and milk mixed.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: In a small skillet, melt 2 tablespoons butter.
Remove skillet from heat and stir in bread crumbs; set aside.
In a medium saucepan, over low heat, melt 1/4 cup butter.
Add milk; gradually stir in undiluted soup until blended.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Put the cooked macaroni in a 2 1/2-quart greased casserole; add the hot sauce mixture and mix well.
Sprinkle with the buttered crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, in a preheated 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: madeline's fruit cake
directions: Put whole nuts, dates and cherries into a large bowl.
Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt over nuts and fruit.
Mix until coated.
Beat eggs until foamy and add vanilla. Stir into mixture until well blended. Grease or spray pans for baking:
