8 x 4-inch loaf pan at 300° for 70 to 80 minutes; 9 x 5-inch loaf pan at 300° for 60 to 70 minutes; 10-inch Bundt pan at 300° for 65 to 75 minutes; 4 small 3 1/2 x 5 1/2-inch pans at 300° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Mixture has to be pushed into corners because there is very little batter.

title: petite blueberry cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar, eggs, lemon juice and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Line muffin pan with paper bake cups and place a vanilla wafer full with cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until set.
Do not brown.
Top each with about 1 tablespoon pie filling.
Chill.
Makes 2 dozen.
May serve with whipped cream.

title: mexican chicken stew
directions: In covered microwave pan, combine oil, chicken and bouillon. Cook on High 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, except onion, and cook for 10 minutes.
Stir well, then add onion and cook for 5 more minutes.
Serves 6.

title: irish stew
directions: In medium kettle, combine lamb and salt with boiling water. Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Add onion, potato, turnip and carrot; bring to boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer, covered, for 20 minutes or until vegetables and lamb are tender.
In small bowl, combine flour and 1/4 cup water.
Mix to form a smooth paste.
Stir flour mixture into hot stew.
Add parsley.
Bring to boiling, stirring.
Boil until stew is thickened.
Makes 6 servings.

title: caponata(sicilian eggplant spread)
directions: Peel eggplant and cut into 1/4-inch cubes.
Saute in 4 tablespoons olive oil on medium-high.
Drain eggplant on paper towel and season with salt and pepper.
Add 2 tablespoons oil to pan and saute carrot and celery over medium heat until tender. Add garlic.
Return eggplant and add tomato sauce, capers, vinegar, bay leaf, oregano, salt and pepper.
If too dry, add water.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Transfer to bowl to cool.
Keep refrigerated until needed.
Serve with bread or crackers.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Cut up zucchini, tomatoes and onion and put in casserole dish with meat.
Add seasoned salt, salt and pepper to taste.
Put margarine on top.
Bake in 350° oven about 20 minutes.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; set
aside.
Cream together shortening, brown sugar and sugar in bowl until light and fluffy, using electric mixer at medium speed. Add
eggs	one
at
a time, beating after each. Blend in vanilla. Gradually stir dry ingredients into creamed mixture.
Stir
in oats,
chocolate pieces and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on greased baking sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 6 1/2 dozen.

title: easter eggs with onion skins
directions: You will also need cheesecloth and thread.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add juice.
Add cheese and stir over low heat until nearly melted.
Add pineapple.
Pour into baking dish.
Cover top with crumbs.
Drizzle melted margarine over top. Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Enough for small family.
I used 2 cans pineapple.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Cream together oil, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spread in greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: near dirty rice
directions: Saute ground meat, onion and bell pepper.
Mix with rice, mushroom and chicken soup.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350° in 3-quart casserole.
Yields 10 servings.

title: cheesy chowder
directions: Put the carrots, celery and onion in blender.
Add to broth. Mix in the remaining ingredients.
Simmer until done.

title: zesty pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles and drain. Add cucumbers and tomatoes. Then pour dressing over noodles. Refrigerate and enjoy.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Crushed seasoned croutons mixed with butter.
Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Pour into large casserole dish.
Covered with foil and bake at 350 for 45 min.
Uncover. Add crushed croutons on top.
Brown.
(About 10 minutes.)

title: egg souffle(make a day ahead.)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch glass pan. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Put 1/2 of batter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Melt caramels and milk until creamy.
While cake is hot, pour caramels over top.
Sprinkle on chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour on rest of cake batter.
Continue baking for 30 to 35 minutes, until done.

title: crabmeat tossed with pasta
directions: In a large saucepan, saute garlic and zucchini in oil for a minute or two.
Add tomatoes and simmer until zucchini and tomatoes soften.
Add next 5 ingredients and simmer about 5 minutes or until sauce thickens.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Combine with all other ingredients except flour.
Mix together and then add flour.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Cook sausage.
Separate dough into 8 triangles.
Place in an ungreased 12-inch pizza pan with points toward the center.
Press over bottom and up sides to form crust.
Sprinkle with potatoes. Top with cheese.

title: pineapple corn bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, sugar, salt and corn meal.
Mix well and add egg, butter, pineapple and milk.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: canned chili (no beans) with portuguese sausage(lazy day)
directions: Heat Portuguese sausage in microwave on High for 5 minutes or until done.
Place on paper towel to remove oil.
Using a microwavable container, mix together chilies and Portuguese sausage.
Place onion, pepper and celery on top of meats and microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Mix meats with vegetables and heat on High for 5 minutes.

title: impossible pumpkin pie(makes its own crust)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat all ingredients until smooth.
Pour into greased 10-inch pie plate.
Cook at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: easy oriental chicken and rice
directions: Melt enough margarine or butter to generously coat bottom of skillet.
Chop chicken into bite-sized pieces and lightly brown in skillet, probably 5 or 10 minutes, being careful not to overcook because meat will become dry.
Add can of rice and approximately 1 tablespoon soy sauce.
Simmer all together for 10 minutes.
Enjoy.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs; beat 3 minutes at medium speed. Blend in flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and vanilla.
Fold in chopped apples and nuts.
Bake in tube pan which has been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool for 20 minutes.
Top with sauce.

title: trifle pudding(dessert)
directions: Slice cake into 3/4-inch thick slices.
Spread raspberry jam evenly on each slice.
Layer a flat dish (approximately 3-inches deep) with the cake.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine cake mix, vegetable oil and eggs in large bowl. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts, if using. Drop by rounded tablespoon onto ungreased baking sheets. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes or until centers are just set. Let stand for 2 minutes; remove to wire racks to cool completely. Makes about 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: chicken soup
directions: In a large kettle seasoned with salt and pepper, simmer chicken in water until tender.
Remove meat, debone and slice in bite sized pieces.
Return to kettle.
Add vegetables and rice or noodles.
Cook until done.
Serve with soda crackers.
Straining and omitting the rice or noodles makes a rich chicken stock.

title: pan-chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix oleo, egg, water, vanilla and sugars.
Cream.
Add flour, salt and soda to creamed mixture.
Put into greased cookie sheet pan (not a large one), a 9 x 13-inch.
You will have to spread with spoon.
Sprinkle top with chocolate chips.
(I go ahead and mix chips in batter.)
Bake in 375° oven for 12 minutes.
Cut into squares while warm.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Fry sausage and crumble.
Drain, reserving 3 tablespoons fat. Saute onion, green pepper, celery and green chilies in the reserved fat.
Mix all ingredients and place in 9 x 13-inch greased baking pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serves 10.

title: baked ham with pineapple slices
directions: Score ham.
Bake 20 minutes per pound.
When meat is hot, baste with honey and pineapple juice from the canned slices.
A half-hour before ham is done, lay pineapple slices on top and finish baking.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in casserole dish.
Cover with Ritz crackers and dot with butter, paprika and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: steak and gravy
directions: Flour cube steaks well; brown in oil.
Remove from pan.
Using drippings, add soup, water, onions and peppers.
Bring to a boil. Put steaks in casserole dish.
Pour soup mixture over steaks. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cook together broth, broccoli and onion for about 10 minutes after it comes to a boil.
In a saucepan, brown butter and flour. Add milk and soup.
Add both mixtures together.
Simmer.

title: creamy potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until onion is tender.
Stir halfway through cooking time.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Sprinkle rice in bottom of greased casserole dish. Add celery and chicken soup, plus water.
Place chicken pieces on top. Pour onion soup over chicken. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, covered.

title: lemonade angel dessert
directions: Pour evaporated milk into freezer tray.
Freeze until soft ice crystals form around edges.

title: low-fat pasta salad
directions: Cook spaghetti by package directions; chill.
Mix the dressing together with veggies; toss together with the noodles.

title: fresh apple nut bread
directions: Grease and flour two loaf pans, 7 1/2 x 3 1/2-inch or one larger pan.
Thoroughly stir together flour, baking soda and salt. In the large bowl of electric mixer, beat together at medium speed the oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla until well blended.
Gradually add flour mixture until smooth. Fold in apples and nuts. Turn into prepared pans.
Bake about 45 to 50 minutes at 350° or until a cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: good brownies fast
directions: Combine.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: taco beef soup
directions: In a large pan, cook ground chuck and onions; drain.
Add water, undrained tomatoes, undrained kidney beans, tomato sauce and taco seasoning mix.
Simmer, covered, 15 to 20 minutes. Top each bowl of soup with cheese, corn chips and sour cream.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: autumn's soup
directions: Mix V8, water, veggies, browned ground meat or stew chunks, and white pepper.
Heat and eat.

title: shrimp and grits
directions: Wash shrimp and pat dry.
Dice bacon and cook until just crisp in a large skillet. Drain bacon and reserve. Add enough oil to bacon fat to make a thin layer.
When hot, add shrimp.
Stir about and add scallions and garlic.
Season to taste with lemon, hot sauce, parsley, salt and pepper. Divide grits. Spoon shrimp over grits and top with bacon.
Serves 4.

title: double chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar, oleo, egg, water and vanilla. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful, about 2-inches apart.
Bake until almost no indentation remains when touched, about 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: holiday nut cake
directions: Preheat over to 250°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add flour and mix well.
Add nuts and fruit to mixture and stir with a spoon.
Grease a cake pan.
Pour batter into pan and bake for 1-1/2 to 2 hours.

title: raisin pie
directions: Cook raisins in water until tender.
Add mixture of sugar and flour.
Add oleo, molasses and vinegar to raisin mixture.
Cook until thick; cool slightly.
Pour into pie shell and cover with top crust.
Bake in moderate oven until done at 350°, about 30 minutes.

title: pecan fudge pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan, over low heat, melt chocolate and margarine.
Stir in sweetened condensed milk, hot water and eggs; mix well.
Remove from heat and stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until center is set.
Cool.
Chill for 3 hours.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Add all ingredients to cooked macaroni and bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: bundt cake
directions: Cream margarine; add eggs and beat well after each addition. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Use well-greased and floured Bundt or angel tin.
Bake at 275° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Cool in pan outside of oven for 5 hours.
Freezes well.
Good served cold. Dust top with xxx sugar.
For brunch, coffees, dessert, etc.

title: hearty potato soup
directions: Put all vegetables in pan with enough water to cover.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until tender. Don't drain off cooking water.

title: curry shrimp
directions: Peel shrimp; devein and rinse.
In wok or large skillet over high heat, add olive oil.
When oil is hot, add shallots, ginger and garlic.
Stir-fry until shallots are limp, about 3 minutes. Add curry powder and turmeric to shallot mixture; stir-fry 30 seconds.
Add onion and coconut milk; stir until onion is limp, about 5 minutes.
Season with cayenne.
Add shrimp; stir until pink and opaque in center, about 4 minutes.
Mound rice onto a large platter; top with shrimp mixture and cilantro.
(Can be served separately, if desired.)
Makes 4 servings.

title: cheese bread
directions: In large bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add shortening, sugar, salt and 2 cups of the flour.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed.
Scrape bowl constantly.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed. Stir in the remaining flour and cheese.
Scrape batter down. Cover bowl, let rise until double (approximately 30 minutes).

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in bottom of baking pan or large baking dish. Add milk (do not stir).
Sift flour and sugar.
Add to dish (do not stir).
Add fruit and bake at 325° to 350° until crust rises to top and browns.

title: lentil soup
directions: Rinse lentils.
Boil in 6 cups of water until tender.
Drain. Rinse.

title: mile high pie
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients in a large bowl at highest speed for 20 minutes.
Fold in the Cool Whip.
Freeze in 2 pie shells or 13 x 9-inch pan.
May freeze without crust, if desired.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add chili mix to meat and add water as directed on package.
Add soup and taco sauce.
Mix well. Oil a 9 x 13-inch pan and line the pan with 5 tortillas; two whole ones on the bottom and break 3 others in half and put flat side toward the side of the pan.
Top with 1/2 of the meat mixture and 1/2 of the shredded cheese.
Repeat process. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1/2 hour.

title: seaside candy roll
directions: Mix together margarine, corn syrup, maple flavoring and salt. Add sugar all at once.
Knead until smooth, adding in 1/2 cup of the nuts.
Shape into 2 rolls.
Brush with additional corn syrup and roll in remainder of nuts.
Wrap and chill.
Slice into rounds before serving.

title: fried corn
directions: Cut the corn from the cob and scrape the cob with the back of a knife to get all of the milk. In a heavy skillet, fry the bacon and remove to paper towels to drain and crisp, leaving the drippings in the skillet. Add corn and water and bring to the boil. Stir well; reduce the heat and simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Season with salt and pepper. Crumble the bacon and use as a garnish. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: In fry pan put oil, butter, garlic, oregano and parsley. When all is melted and bubbly, then put in shrimp that was cleaned and cooked.
Then thicken with bread crumbs.
Cook linguine and drain, then mix together.

title: apple dessert
directions: Cream together sugar, oleo and eggs.
Add apples, flour, nutmeg, cinnamon, soda and nuts.
Put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Melt oleo.
Add 1/2 cup sugar, 4 tablespoons flour, brown sugar, evaporated milk and vanilla.
Cook until thick (scorches easily).
Serve cake with warm sauce.

title: gingerbread
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Add to brown sugar, molasses and oil. Combine and sift together the dry ingredients; add to egg mixture. Lastly, stir in boiling water.
Pour into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pastel cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add jello and sugar creaming until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in flavorings.
Add flour and soda alternately with milk (small amount at a time), beating until smooth after each.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet and flatten.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until golden around edge.

title: pineapple nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350°
for 35 to 45 minutes.
Great with a cream cheese frosting.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Place drained string beans in baking dish.
Dot with margarine.
Salt and pepper.
Pour soup over beans.
Arrange onion rings on top.
Place in oven and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: monkey bread
directions: Shake biscuits in Baggie with sugar and cinnamon.
Grease Bundt pan generously and layer biscuits in pan.
Heat 1/2 cup sugar, brown sugar and butter to boil.
Add nuts if desired.
Pour hot mixture over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
When light brown remove from oven.
Cool 5 minutes.
Turn out on plate.

title: crock-pot macaroni
directions: Cook and drain macaroni. Mix all ingredients together. Spray crock-pot with olive oil spray. Put mixture in crock-pot and place thin slices of cheese on top. Sprinkle with paprika. Cook 3 to 3 1/2 hours on low.

title: corned beef macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Return to pan.

Cut cheese into cubes and add to macaroni. Add 2 cans of soup with 1 can of water. Cook and stir on low until cheese is melted. Crumble corned beef in and stir. Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan and add cracker crumbs and a little melted butter or margarine on top.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 1/2 hour.

title: fresh salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Let stand at least 30 minutes at room temperature.
Can be stored refrigerated up to 2 weeks. Yield:
3 cups.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix together.
Place in Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Slice in 3 rounds and frost.

title: mint tea
directions: Steep tea bags in boiling water for at least 5 minutes.
Stir in sugar and lemonade.
Add water to make one gallon.

title: beef and bean casserole
directions: Cook
beef
until red disappears;
drain.
Use	drained liquid to saute onion and bell pepper in;	drain.	Mix all the ingredients together and bake until bubbly.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together and form a ball.

title: meat and vegetable casserole
directions: In a greased 2-quart casserole dish, put a thin layer of meat and potatoes.
Sprinkle on rice, carrots, celery, onion, salt and pepper.
Layer in this order until all used up.
Pour tomato sauce and water on top and dot with butter.
Bake, covered, at 350°
for 1 1/2 hours.

title: easy yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, oil, egg and 1 cup self-rising flour.
Put over pan of hot water; cover and let rise 15 minutes.
Add remaining flour.
If sticky, add more flour to make soft dough and knead slightly.
Shape into rolls; let rise 1/2 hour.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: meat and vegetable leftovers casserole
directions: Microwave in 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Cook onion, garlic, vegetables and butter for 5 minutes on High.
Stir in cornstarch, soup, water, meat and rice.
Cover and cook for 10 minutes on High, stirring twice.
Fluff rice and serve.

title: fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan, over low heat, melt chips with milk. remove from heat; stir in remaining ingredients. Spread into wax paper lined 8-inch
sq pan.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Cream butter, sugar and flour.
Separate eggs.
Mix yolks with sugar and butter. Grate rind of lemon.
Add juice and rind and cup of milk.
Then add beaten egg whites.
Bake in unbaked crust at 350°.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients; top with bacon slices.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until thickened to desired thickness.

title: mary lou's easy swiss chicken breasts
directions: Arrange chicken in a lightly greased baking dish.
Top with cheese slices.
Combine soup and wine, spoon over chicken. Sprinkle with stuffing mix.
Drizzle butter over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Garnish with parsley.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Rinse kraut well with cold water and drain well.
Mix in onion, celery, celery seed, mangoes and pimentos.
Make brine of remaining ingredients.
Cook until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over kraut mixture.
Chill.
Better if made a day ahead of serving.

title: auntie mimo's chocolate cake
directions: In a large mixer bowl, sift together the dry ingredients. Make a well in center; pour in remaining ingredients.
Beat on low for 2 minutes, then on medium for 6 to 7 minutes, to be sure oil is well blended.
You will get a thin batter.
Pour into ungreased bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch or 10-inch round, 2-inch deep pan, lined with wax paper.
Grease sides of pan very lightly.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cucumber pickles #2
directions: Peel
and
core cucumbers;
slice into rings or sticks. Soak in	lime
water
24 hours.	Drain and soak in ice water 3 hours. Drain and put in mixture of vinegar, alum and coloring with enough water to cover.
Simmer 2 hours;
drain and throw away liquid. Mix the vinegar and remaining ingredients.	Heat to
boiling point.
Pour over cucumbers and let set 24 hours. Drain;
save liquid.
Pack pickles in jars; bring liquid to a boil and pour over pickles.
Seal.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all together and pour in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: banana delight
directions: Put in pan in order as follows:

title: sweet and sour beef stew
directions: Brown stew meat in 2 Tbsp vegetable oil.
Add rest of ingredients and cook over low heat until meat is tender, about 2 hours.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook pasta and drain.
Heat butter; add flour and pepper slowly.
Stir in broth and bring to a boil.
Simmer until thick. Stir in half and half, chicken and 3/4 cup cheese.
Saute mushrooms in butter and lemon juice until juice cooks off.
Add pasta to cream mixture.

title: no-bake almond balls
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch together over medium heat. Remove.
Add sugar, sour cream, peel and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Mix. Blend in crumbs.
Chill for 30 minutes; shape into 1-inch balls. Roll in chopped nuts.
Store in a tightly sealed container. Yields approximately 42 balls.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water.
When firm, add to heated berries; add wine.
When cool, add celery, nuts, orange rind and apple or pineapple.
Pour into mold.
Chill.
Great with Thanksgiving turkey.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate until time to serve.
You may add grated carrots and have a very good carrot salad, also.

title: orange glazed carrots
directions: Warm carrots.
In another saucepan, combine next 4 ingredients.
Add orange juice and stir, cooking until thick. Stir in butter at least and pour over drained carrots.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: fettucine alfredo
directions: Cook and drain fettucine.
In a saute pan, add pasta, butter, cream and cheese, bring to a boil.
Cook over medium heat until mixture starts to thicken.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Do not make any substitutions in ingredients.
Serves 10.

title: dirt cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, butter and powdered sugar.
Mix milk and pudding together.
Blend in whipped topping.
Combine these two mixtures.
Crush cookies.
In a clean, new 8-inch clay pot or plastic flour pot, make layers of cookies, then creamy mixture. Line with foil if using new clay pot or cover hole with small plastic lid.
End with 1 1/2-inch layer of cookies.
"Plant" an artificial flower in center.
Cover the stem with plastic wrap. Chill several hours or overnight.
Serve with new, clean shovel.

title: monkey cake
directions: Mix 1 cup of sugar and cinnamon.
Put this mixture in a plastic bag and shake the quartered biscuits in the mix.
Heavily butter a Bundt pan.
Put the biscuits in the pan.
In between layers, put pats of butter and brown sugar.
Sprinkle leftover sugar and cinnamon over biscuits.

title: the "best" brownies
directions: Blend oil, sugar and vanilla in a mixing bowl.
Add eggs. Beat well with spoon.
Combine flour, cocoa and baking powder. Gradually add to egg mixture until well blended.
Stir in nuts. Spread in greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cool in pan.

title: baptist rice
directions: Place first 4 ingredients together in medium size heavy weight saucepan.
Mix well.
Bring to boil over medium heat; stir well. Cover and cook over low heat until tender and water is absorbed, 12 to 14 minutes.
Stir.
Do not overcook.
Sprinkle grated orange peel on top.
Makes 4 to 5 cups.
Serve hot with Beef Stroganoff Supreme.

title: sweet and sour salad
directions: Cook macaroni; add cucumbers, pepper, onion, pimentos and salt to taste.
Combine sugar, vinegar and oil.
Pour over other ingredients.
Mix well.
Marinate overnight; stir once in a while.

title: red lobster biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 400 degrees.
In a mixing bowl, combine baking mix, milk, and cheese until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously for 30 seconds.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake for 10-12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Mix remaining ingredients; brush over warm biscuits before moving from baking sheets.

title: tuna salad
directions: Shred all ingredients except tuna; drain tuna and add to other ingredients.
Add enough salad dressing or mayonnaise to moisten. Makes delicious sandwiches.

title: classic con queso dip
directions: Heat cheese and salsa in 1 1/2-quart saucepan over low heat 10 minutes, stirring occasionally until cheese is melted.
Keep warm in heatproof dish.
Serve with snacks.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Stir together the first 7 ingredients.
Cook spaghetti and stir into mixture.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Top with sprinkles of paprika and Parmesan cheese while hot.

title: coconut balls
directions: Melt butter in frying pan.
Add dates, eggs, salt and sugar; mix well.
Cook for 10 minutes, stirring over low heat to prevent burning.
Add Rice Krispies, nuts and vanilla.
Cool and shape into small balls; roll in coconut.

title: st. michael's alley white chili
directions: Saute garlic and onions until onions are clear.
Add remaining ingredients and cook on medium heat, stirring every 10 minutes or until mixture is hot and well blended, about 45 minutes.
Top with finely chopped green pepper, red onion, cilantro, chopped tomato and grated Monterey Jack cheese.

title: blueberry tart
directions: Bake first 4 ingredients for 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Next combine next 4 ingredients and pour over cooled crust.
Top filling with blueberry pie filling.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; let drain excess fat.
Boil noodles according to package directions; drain.
In large mixing bowl, mix hamburger, noodles, soups, peas and cheese.
Place in casserole and bake 30 minutes in oven at 350°.

title: grog
directions: In a glass or mug, combine the juice of 1/2 lemon, sugar, a slice of lemon studded with cloves, a strip of orange peel and rum.
Add boiling water to fill the mug.
Stir with a cinnamon stick.

title: chili beans
directions: Brown and drain hamburger and onions in skillet. Combine with all other ingredients in large pot. Cook over low heat until thick and all vegetables are completely heated.

title: delicious quick dessert
directions: Dissolve 1 tablespoon instant coffee in 1 tablespoon hot water.
Let cool, then stir fudge and coffee into 8 ounces Cool Whip.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Brown
hamburger
with	onion.	Mix
cornbread mixes as directed.
Pour half
of mix in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Layer
hamburger
meat, cheese, corn, then rest of the cornbread mix.
Bake at 375°, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: empanada's
directions: Mix margarine and cheese together.
Add flour until crumbly. Add enough water to make soft dough.
Mix all remaining ingredients for meat mixture and chill.
Roll out dough, cut with 6-inch diagonal circle cutter.
Put about 2 tablespoons of meat into middle of dough circle and lap over and pinch together. Continue with remaining dough.
Makes about 20.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until browned.

title: sloppy joes
directions: In large skillet, brown ground beef, green pepper and onion; drain well. Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover; simmer 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally, until thoroughly heated.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Stir with fork the apples and egg.
Add sugar and oil; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in a greased and floured 8 x 8-inch baking dish for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: confetti bean casserole
directions: Fry bacon, lift out bacon leaving grease in skillet.
Add onion to grease and saute until transparent.
Lift out and hold. Add ground beef and fry until all pink is gone.
Add all other ingredients to skillet mixture, plus bacon and onion, and heat. Place in casserole dish and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: beef porcupines
directions: Mix beef, rice, onions and seasonings.
Shape into small balls. Cook on low heat, turning frequently, until light brown but not crusty.
Add sauce and water; mix well.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes until done.
Stir frequently to prevent burning.

title: hot wassail
directions: Put juices in the bottom of a percolator.
Put sugar, cinnamon and cloves in percolator basket.
Percolate!

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise.
In small bowl, mix egg yolks, salt, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and salad dressing.
Dip into egg whites.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Refrigerate until served.

title: reese's cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, stir together flour and baking soda.
In large mixer bowl, beat shortening, granulated sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Add eggs.
Beat well. Gradually add flour mixture, blending in well.
Stir in peanut butter chips and chocolate chips.
Spoon dough onto ungreased cookie sheet, (approximately 1 rounded teaspoonful).
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool slightly.
Remove from cookie sheet.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: reefie's taco salad
directions: Add small bag Dorito chips and 8 ounce bottle creamy Italian dressing right before serving.

title: four and four
directions: Beat all ingredients well and pour into 2 ice cube trays. Freeze.
When frozen, take out and whip in blender.
Return to trays and refreeze.
Great snack for kids.

title: "south of the border" beans
directions: Combine all ingredients into slow cooker.
Cook slowly all day.
If time permits, soak beans in water overnight.

title: jingles
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg, and combine with flour and baking soda.
Blend into a creamed mixture.
Stir in baking bits, raisins and nuts.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough onto cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 13 minutes.

title: mushroom strudel
directions: Cook onion in 2 tablespoons butter, covered, 10 to 15 minutes. Add chopped mushrooms, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook, over very low heat until there is no liquid left in pan (but fat remains). Stir to prevent burning.
Let this mixture cool to room temperature.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Beat egg yolks.
Add yolks and whites to mixture.
Add bread crumbs.
Spread filling on strudel sheets at one end.
Sprinkle with remaining melted butter.
Roll strudel very loosely so eggs can expand.
Place in buttered baking dish or pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes until crisp and golden.

title: baked ham in foil
directions: Pour water in crock-pot. Wrap ham in foil and place in crock-pot.
Cover and cook on high 1 hour, then on low 6 to 7 hours or until ham is hot.
If desired, sprinkle ham with liquid smoke before wrapping in foil.

title: chocolate chip peanut butter squares
directions: Cook brownie mix per directions on mix in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
While brownies are cooking, mix honey and peanut butter on medium heat until blended together.
When brownies are done and still hot, put chocolate bits over the brownies, then drizzle honey mixture over the chocolate bits.
Cover with chopped walnuts or almonds.

title: ribs and sauerkraut
directions: Boil ribs.
About halfway through cooking, add sauerkraut and any seasonings or spices to your taste. Finish cooking.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix well together and store in a dry airtight container, indefinetly.
Mix with 1/4 c. with hot water.

title: easy spiced peaches(low-fat)
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil in large pot.
Reduce heat and gently boil 20 to 30 minutes until liquid is slightly thickened.

title: cranberry honey butter
directions: Beat together butter and honey.
Add sauce; blend well.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes.
Pat dry.
Prick skins with a fork.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cut hot potatoes in half.
Scoop out potatoes, leaving 1/4 inch thick shells. Set-aside.
In a medium size mixing bowl, combine scooped out potato, margarine, milk, salt, pepper, and garlic powder.
Whip potatoes with electric mixer until smooth. Fill shells with potato mixture.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top or freeze at this stage and add cheese later.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix well and refrigerate overnight. Good with chips or vegetables.

title: shrimp, chicken, sausage creole
directions: Boil chicken and pick off bones.
Set aside.
In a large pot, put tomato paste and chicken stock plus water to half fill pot. Add finely chopped onions, celery, bell pepper and garlic.
Add all seasoning and simmer for 1 hour.

title: danish pastry apple bars
directions: In medium bowl, combine flour and salt.
Cut in Crisco.
Beat egg yolk in measuring cup; add enough milk to make 2/3 cup liquid. Mix well.
Stir egg mixture into flour mixture.
On floured surface, roll half the dough to a 17 x 12-inch rectangle.
Line a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan with half the pastry.
Sprinkle with cornflakes; top with apples.
Combine sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over apples.
Roll remaining dough to make top crust; place over apples.
Seal edges of dough.
Cut slits in top for escape of steam.
Beat egg white until frothy.
Brush on crust.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.
While still warm, drizzle with confectioners sugar glaze.
Cut into bars.

title: garden macaroni salad
directions: In a large bowl, stir first 6 ingredients together until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Toss to coat well.
Cover; chill.
Makes 5 cups.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and debone.
Set aside.
Mix soups and spice packet from stuffing together.
In a casserole dish, layer the bottom with chicken, then a layer of soups, then chicken and remainder of soup mix.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into a greased tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: seasoned crackers
directions: Place all ingredients in a large grocery bag and shake well. Store in closed container.

title: kir sorbet
directions: Puree grapes in processor.
Strain juice into measuring cup. Add water, if necessary, to measure 1 1/2 cups.
Blend grape juice, wine and 1/2 cup water, lemon juice and cassis.
Transfer mixture to ice cream maker and process according to manufacturer's instructions.

title: evelyn barrett's sour cream pie
directions: Mix well and pour into 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until firm and a toothpick inserted in center of pie comes out clean (doneness test), approximately 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cold with whipped cream, vanilla ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix cheese and sausage.
Gradually mix in the biscuit mix. Roll into small balls and bake in 325° oven about 15 minutes.

title: summer pasta
directions: Melt butter and saute garlic until just tender.
Add mushrooms and cook for 7 to 8 minutes; set aside.
Cook pasta in salted water according to package directions.
While pasta is cooking, chop the tomatoes and add olives, artichoke hearts and basil.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Drain pasta and add mushroom mixture, tomato mixture and olive oil.
Toss and top with cheese.

title: pat's chili
directions: Saute hamburger and onion in shortening.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.

title: creole corn burger
directions: Brown ground beef in a large skillet.
Drain off fat.
Add the rest of ingredients and cook 15 minutes, covered, stirring occasionally.
Vary amounts of corn, celery and tomatoes to suit taste.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes on an ungreased cookie sheet.
May be frozen until ready to bake.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Mix all except crackers in blender.
Pour over crackers in brown bag or can put in sheet cake pan and put in oven for a few minutes to soak in oil.

title: sauerkraut chop suey
directions: Fry first 4 ingredients until browned; drain any excess grease.
Mix
this
and all other ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
This
recipe
could
be cut in half if you have a small family.
Can be frozen.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Butter a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Mix blueberries, pineapple and 1/2 cup sugar.
Spread over bottom of pan.
Spoon dry cake mix over berry mixture.
Then sprinkle chopped nuts over cake mix.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar over mixture.
Drizzle melted margarine over top and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until sides are brown and it is crusty.
Halfway through baking time, cut through mixture and let juices penetrate.

title: polish sausage and potato
directions: Boil potatoes until almost ready.
Chuck up and set aside. Slice sausage; fry with onion until brown.
Place in Dutch oven the sausage, potatoes and green beans.
Blend together sugar and vinegar; pour over ingredients in Dutch oven.
Stir constantly until liquid becomes thick, on medium heat.
Add parsley.
Remove from heat and serve.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Blend, then beat for 2 minutes.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan and bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meat with chili powder and garlic powder.
Drain fat.
Layer the following:
Place half of tortillas in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pour ground meat mixture over tortillas. Add beans, then spread chopped onions over beans.
Cover with cheese.
Place remaining tortillas on top.
Add soup and just enough water to rinse the can.
Put tomatoes over all.
Cover tightly with foil or lid and bake at least 30 minutes.

title: texas chili
directions: Sear meat in olive oil until gray colored.
Simmer in water to barely cover meat, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add spices and cook 30 minutes longer.
Mix cornmeal with 1 cup cool water.
Add to mixture and cook 5 minutes longer.
